\mt2 The second summary of the
\mt1 Kings of Yisrael and Yehudah
\is1 Introduction
\ip \bk The second summary of the kings of Yisrael/Israel and Yehudah/Judah\bk* is a continuation of the first summary about the northern kingdom of Yisrael and the Southern kingdom of Yehudah (Judah). This account can be divided into two: \bd 1.\bd* The account about the two kingdoms from around 850 before Yeshua/Jesus (B.C.) through to the defeat of Shomron (Samaria) and the fall of the northern king in 721 before Yeshua/Jesus (B.C.) \bd 2.\bd* The account about the Southern kingdom of Yehudah from the defeat of the northern kingdom of Yisrael through to the capture and destruction of Yerushalem (Jerusalem) by the Babylonian King Nevukadnetstsar in 586 before Yeshua/Jesus (B.C.) This account ends with Gedalyah governing Yehudah under Babylonian instructions, and then the release of King Yehoyakin who'd been imprisoned in Babylon.
\ip Those disasters and destruction occurred because the leaders and inhabitants of the divided kingdom didn't obey God. The demolition of Yerushalem and the exile of most of the people of Yehudah was a major tragedy in Yisrael's history.
\ip Prophet Elisha is highlighted here in this second summary. Elisha was the dominant prophet who continued on after Eliyah's death.
\iot Main components of this account
\io1 The divided kingdom (1:1вҖ“17:41)
\io2 a. The prophet Elisha (1:1вҖ“8:15)
\io2 b. The kings of Yehudah and Yisrael (8:16вҖ“17:4)
\io2 c. The defeat of Shomron/Samaria (17:5-41)
\io1 The kingdom of Yehudah (18:1вҖ“25:30)
\io2 a. From Hizkiyah going to Yoshiyyah (18:1вҖ“21:26)
\io2 b. The kingdom of Yoshiyyah (22:1вҖ“23:30)
\io2 c. Yehudah's final king (23:31вҖ“24:20)
\io2 d. The defeat of Yerushalem (25:1-30)
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\s1 Yahweh punishes King Ahazyah
\rem /s1 Elisha and the house of Ahab; Elijah and King Ahaziah; The Lord's Judgment on Ahaziah; Elijah Denounces Ahaziah; Elijah Confronts King Ahaziah
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 1 After the deathВҰ171792 of \add Yisrael'sВҰ171790 King\add* AhabВҰ171793, MoabВҰ171789 rebelledВҰ171788 against Yisrael.
\p
\v 2 \add One day, King\add* AhazyahВҰ171796 fell throughВҰ171797 a latticeВҰ171798 in his upperВҰ171799 room in ShomronВҰ171801 \add (Samaria)\add* and was injuredВҰ171802, \add вүҲso\add* he sentВҰ171803 messengersВҰ171804 to goВҰ171807 and ask Ekron'sВҰ171812 godВҰ171811 Baal-Zevuv if he would recover.
\v 3 \add вүҲButВҰ171820\add* Yahweh's messenger told EliyahВҰ171825 (from TishbeВҰ171826), вҖң\add вүҲLeave here\add* \add and\add* goВҰ171828 and meet the ShomronВҰ171833 king's messengers and \add вүҲask\add* them, вҖҳIs it becauseВҰ171836 there'sВҰ171837 no god inВҰ171840 YisraelВҰ171840 that you're all goingВҰ171842 to inquireВҰ171843 from Ekron'sВҰ171847 god Baal-Zevuv?
\v 4 \add вүҲBecause of that,\add* YahwehВҰ171853 says that \add the king\add* won'tВҰ171859 get out of the bed that he's lying inвҖ”he's definitely going to die.вҖқ
\p \add вүҲSoВҰ171849\add* EliyahВҰ171867 \add told them andВҰ171849\add* \add вүҲcontinued\add* on his way.
\v 5 \add вүҲWhenВҰ171869\add* the messengersВҰ171870 returned to \add @the king\add*, he \add вүҲasked\add* them, вҖңWhat's this? \add вүҲWhy are youВҰ171877 back here\add* \add so soon\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 6 вҖңA manВҰ171881 \add вүҲcameВҰ171883\add* to meet us,вҖқ they told him, вҖңand he said to us, вҖҳGo \add and\add* returnВҰ171888 to the kingВҰ171891 who sent you, and tell him that YahwehВҰ171900 says this: Is it becauseВҰ171901 there's no god in YisraelВҰ171905 that you are sendingВҰ171907 \add messengers\add* to inquireВҰ171908 from Ekron'sВҰ171912 god Baal-Zevuv? Therefore you'll never leave that bed that you're lying in butВҰ171879 you'll certainly die \add in it\add*.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 7 вҖңWhatВҰ171938 was the manВҰ171932 \add вүҲlike\add*,вҖқ the king \add вүҲasked\add* them, вҖңwho met you andВҰ171936 \add вүҲgave you all that message\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 8 вҖң\add вүҲHe had a cloak made of animal\add* hair,вҖқ they \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖңandВҰ171943 \add вүҲwas wearing a leather beltВҰ171948\add*.вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Ah,\add*вҖқ said \add @the king\add*. вҖңThat's EliyahВҰ171953 \add вүҲfrom TishbeВҰ171954\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ171957\add* he sentВҰ171957 a captain with his fifty soldiers to look for \add @Eliyah\add* andВҰ171957 they found him sittingВҰ171966 on the top of a hill. The captain \add вүҲcalled out\add*, вҖңMan of GodВҰ171974, the kingВҰ171975 \add вүҲwants to see you\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲButВҰ171979\add* EliyahВҰ171980 replied, вҖң\add вүҲWell,\add* if I am a man of GodВҰ171989, let fire come down from the sky and consumeВҰ171996 you and your \add вүҲmen\add*,вҖқ and fire came down from the sky, and it \add вүҲburnt up the captain and his men\add*.
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲSoВҰ172012\add* \add @the king\add* sent anotherВҰ172018 captain with his fifty men and they went to where Eliyah was and called out to him, вҖңProphet, the king commandsВҰ172015 that you come \add вүҲwith us right now\add*.вҖқ
