\v 12 \add Again\add* EliyahВҰ172033 replied, вҖңIf I am a man of God, let fire come down from the sky and consumeВҰ172046 you and your \add вүҲmen\add*,вҖқ and God's fire came down from the sky, and it \add вүҲburnt up the captain and his men\add*.
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲSoВҰ172064\add* \add @the king\add* sentВҰ172065 a third captain withВҰ172098 his fifty men. They wentВҰ172072 to where EliyahВҰ172083 was and the officer knelt down inВҰ172098 front of him and \add вүҲpleaded\add*, вҖңProphet, I \add вүҲbeg\add* you, be kind to me and my fifty soldiers, and don't kill us.
\v 14 Listen, fireВҰ172102 came down from the sky and burnt up the firstВҰ172112 twoВҰ172109 captains and theirВҰ172115 \add вүҲmen, butВҰ172106 please treat my lifeВҰ172118 as valuable inВҰ172119 yourВҰ172119 sightВҰ172119\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 Then Yahweh's messengerВҰ172123 told EliyahВҰ172127, вҖңGo with \add #them\add*. Don't be afraidВҰ172132 of him.вҖқ
\p So Eliyah went with \add #them\add* to the kingВҰ172139
\v 16 andВҰ172141 told him, вҖңYahwehВҰ172146 says that you sent messengersВҰ172151 to inquire from Ekron'sВҰ172156 god Baal-Zevuv, \add вүҲas if\add* there's no god in YisraelВҰ172161 to \add вүҲask\add*. Therefore, \add he says,\add* \add вүҲyou certainly won'tВҰ172157 get off that bed that you're onВҰ172153\add* because you'll die \add in it\add*.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Death of Ahaziah
\p
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ172179\add* \add @King Ahazyah\add* died \add вүҲjust as YahwehВҰ172181 had said via\add* EliyahВҰ172186. ThenВҰ172179 \add Ahazyah's younger brother\add* Yehoram \add (Joram)\add* becameВҰ172187 king in his placeВҰ172189, because \add @Ahazyah\add* \add вүҲdidn'tВҰ172200 have any sons\add*. \add This happened\add* in the second year \add of the reign\add* of Yehoshafat'sВҰ172196 son King Yehoram over YehudahВҰ172198.
\v 18 \add вүҲEverything else thatВҰ172209 AhazyahВҰ172208 said andВҰ172206 did is writtenВҰ172214 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ172220 of YisraelВҰ172221.
\c 2
\s1 Eliyah is taken up to heaven
\rem /s1 Elijah Taken into Heaven; Elijah Taken Up to Heaven; Elijah Is Taken Up to Heaven; Elijah Ascends to Heaven
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲOne day as\add* Eliyah and ElishaВҰ172234 \add вүҲhad left\add* GilgalВҰ172237, YahwehВҰ172226 took Eliyah up to heavenВҰ172231 inВҰ172225 a storm.
\v 2 EliyahВҰ172240 had told ElishaВҰ172243, вҖңNow, you stay here because Yahweh has \add вүҲtold me to go\add* to Beyt-El.вҖқ
\p вҖңBy the life of Yahweh,вҖқ Elisha \add вүҲhad respondedВҰ172239\add*, вҖңandВҰ172239 by the life of yourВҰ172263 spirit, I won't leaveВҰ172266 you.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ172239 they'd headed\add* to Beyt-El.
\p
\v 3 \add вүҲAlso\add* the \add вүҲprophets-in-training\add* who were in Beyt-El had gone out to ElishaВҰ172283 andВҰ172272 told him, вҖңDo you know that today YahwehВҰ172293 is going to take yourВҰ172295 masterВҰ172293 \add вүҲaway from you\add*?вҖқ
\p вҖңI \add вүҲalready know that\add*,вҖқ he'd \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖң\add вүҲDon't say anything\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 ThenВҰ172303 EliyahВҰ172305 \add вүҲhad informed\add* ElishaВҰ172306, вҖңYahweh has sent me to YerichoВҰ172327 \add (Jericho)\add*. You stay here.вҖқ
\p He'd \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖңBy the life of Yahweh andВҰ172303 the life of yourВҰ172322 spirit, I won't leaveВҰ172325 you.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ172303 they'd gone\add* to Yericho.
\p
\v 5 The \add вүҲprophets-in-training\add* who were in YerichoВҰ172335 \add вүҲhad approached\add* ElishaВҰ172338 andВҰ172329 \add вүҲbriefed\add* him, вҖңDo you know that today YahwehВҰ172348 is taking yourВҰ172350 masterВҰ172348 \add вүҲaway from you\add*?вҖқ
\p вҖң\add вүҲYes, I realise that\add*,вҖқ he'd \add вүҲrespondedВҰ172339\add*. вҖң\add вүҲSay no more\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲAgain\add* EliyahВҰ172360 had told him, вҖңYou stay here, because Yahweh has sent me to the YordanВҰ172368.вҖқ
\p And he'd \add вүҲcountered\add*, вҖңBy the life of Yahweh andВҰ172358 the life of yourВҰ172375 spirit, I won't leaveВҰ172378 you.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ172358 the two of them had gone there together\add*.
\v 7 \add вүҲFifty of the prophets-in-training had also gone, butВҰ172382 they'd stood back watching from a distanceВҰ172389, so the twoВҰ172390 of them had stood there\add* by the YordanВҰ172394.
\v 8 ThenВҰ172396 EliyahВҰ172397 had taken off his cloak and \add вүҲdoubled it over\add* and hit the river \add withВҰ172411 it\add*. The waterВҰ172405 dividedВҰ172406 \add вүҲleaving a dry path and the two of them had walked across\add* \add to the otherВҰ172408 side\add*.
\v 9 As they'd crossedВҰ172414 over, EliyahВҰ172415 had told ElishaВҰ172419, вҖң\add вүҲTell me what you'd like me to do for you beforeВҰ172425 I get takenВҰ172426 away\add*.вҖқ
\p вҖңPlease,вҖқ Elisha \add вүҲhad answered\add*, вҖң\add вүҲI'd like a\add* double amount of \add вүҲthe spiritВҰ172436 that you have\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 вҖң\add Oh,\add* \add вүҲthat's a difficultВҰ172440 request\add*,вҖқ \add @Eliyah\add* \add вүҲhad respondedВҰ172439\add*. вҖң\add Well,\add* if you seeВҰ172444 me being takenВҰ172446 \add вүҲaway\add* from you, \add вүҲthenВҰ172439 you'll get what you askedВҰ172441 for, butВҰ172439 if you miss seeing me go, you won'tВҰ172454\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 Then it had happened \add while\add* they were walking and talkingВҰ172462 \add together\add*. Wow, a chariotВҰ172464 of fire and horsesВҰ172467 of fire \add drove\add* betweenВҰ172470 the two of them, \add вүҲseparatingВҰ172469 them\add*. Then EliyahВҰ172473 went up to the heavensВҰ172475 inВҰ172474 the gale.
\v 12 Elisha was watching, and he cried out, вҖңMy father, my father, Yisrael'sВҰ172485 chariotВҰ172484 and its horsemenВҰ172486!вҖқ
\rem /s1 Elisha Succeeds Elijah
\p \add вүҲButВҰ172477 thenВҰ172477\add* \add @Elisha\add* could no longer see him, and he grabbed his \add own\add* \add вүҲcloak\add*, and tore \add #it\add* inВҰ172491 half,
\v 13 and he pickedВҰ172496 up Eliyah'sВҰ172500 cloakВҰ172499 thatВҰ172501 had fallenВҰ172502 \add вүҲdown to the ground\add*. ThenВҰ172496 he wentВҰ172504 back and stoodВҰ172505 on the bank of the YordanВҰ172509,
\v 14 and he tookВҰ172511 Eliyah's cloakВҰ172514 and \add вүҲhit the river\add* \add with it\add*, saying, вҖңWhere is Eliyah's godВҰ172527 YahwehВҰ172526?вҖқ \add вүҲThenВҰ172511 as\add* he hit the water, \add вүҲthe river dividedВҰ172537 into two parts\add* and ElishaВҰ172541 crossedВҰ172540 \add вүҲthrough the middle\add*.
\v 15 The \add вүҲprophets-in-training\add* who were \add вүҲonВҰ172549 the YerichoВҰ172549 side, affirmed\add*, вҖң\add вүҲElishaВҰ172557 now has the spiritВҰ172553 that EliyahВҰ172554 had\add*.вҖқ ThenВҰ172543 they cameВҰ172558 \add forward\add* to meet him andВҰ172543 \add вүҲknelt down in front of him\add* \add as a sign of respect\add*,
\v 16 and they \add вүҲrequested\add*, вҖңListen please, \add вүҲfiftyВҰ172575 of us here have military training\add*. Please, let them goВҰ172580 to search for your masterВҰ172585, inВҰ172592 case Yahweh's spiritВҰ172589 lifted him and \add вүҲdropped\add* him onВҰ172592 \add вүҲa hillВҰ172593 somewhere\add* or into one of the valleysВҰ172596.вҖқ
\p вҖң\add вүҲDon't waste your time\add*,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\v 17 ButВҰ172602 they \add вүҲkept insisting so much that Elisha was embarrassed\add* and he saidВҰ172608, вҖң\add вүҲOk thenВҰ172602\add*.вҖқ
\p \add вүҲSoВҰ172602\add* they sentВҰ172610 fiftyВҰ172611 men, and they searched for threeВҰ172614 daysВҰ172616, butВҰ172602 they didn'tВҰ172617 find \add @Eliyah\add*.
\v 18 \add вүҲWhenВҰ172620\add* they returnedВҰ172620 to \add @Elisha\add* (he was staying inВҰ172624 YerichoВҰ172624), he saidВҰ172625 to them, вҖңDidn't I \add вүҲtell you not to bother\add*?вҖқ
\rem /s1 Miracles of Elisha; Healing of the Water; Elisha Performs Miracles; Elisha's First Miracles
\p
\v 19 ThenВҰ172635 the \add вүҲleaders\add* of \add Yericho\add* city said to ElishaВҰ172640, вҖңPlease, \add вүҲthis city is a good place to live\add*, just as my masterВҰ172648 can see, butВҰ172635 the waterВҰ172650 \add supplies around here\add* are bad \add вүҲso our crops don't thrive\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 вҖңBring me a \add brand\add* new bowl,вҖқ he saidВҰ172655, вҖңandВҰ172655 put salt thereВҰ172662.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ172655\add* theyВҰ172664 brought \add вүҲone\add* to him,
\v 21 and he wentВҰ172667 out to the \add вүҲspring\add* and threwВҰ172672 the salt at it, and \add вүҲannounced\add*, вҖңYahwehВҰ172680 saysВҰ172679 that he's healedВҰ172681 theseВҰ172683 waterВҰ172682 \add supplies\add* and \add вүҲthey'll no longer cause\add* deathВҰ172689 or barrenness.вҖқ
\v 22 \add вүҲSoВҰ172692 now those waterВҰ172693 supplies have been healthy andВҰ172692 beneficial untilВҰ172694 this dayВҰ172695, just as ElishaВҰ172698 had said\add*.
\rem /s1 Elisha Is Jeered
\p
\v 23 From thereВҰ172704 \add @Elisha\add* wentВҰ172714 to Beyt-El, and as he was goingВҰ172710 up onВҰ172711 the road, \add some\add* youngВҰ172713 men cameВҰ172714 out from the cityВҰ172717, and \add вүҲstarted\add* mocking him, saying, вҖң\add вүҲKeep moving, baldy. Keep moving, baldy\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 24 ThenВҰ172728 \add @Elisha\add* turnedВҰ172728 \add вүҲback around\add* and \add вүҲlooked at\add* them, and he cursedВҰ172731 them in Yahweh's nameВҰ172732. \add вүҲJust thenВҰ172728,\add* two femaleВҰ172736 bearsВҰ172736 cameВҰ172734 out from the forest and mauledВҰ172740 forty-two of \add *them\add*.
\p
\v 25 \add @Elisha\add* carried on from there to MtВҰ172750. KarmelВҰ172751, andВҰ172746 from there, he returnedВҰ172753 to ShomronВҰ172754 \add (Samaria)\add*.
\c 3
\s1 The war between Yisrael and Moab
\rem /s1 Jehoram Reigns over Israel; War between Israel and Moab; Moab Revolts
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 1 Ahab'sВҰ172760 son Yehoram \add (Jehoram)\add* becameВҰ172761 king over YisraelВҰ172764 inВҰ172765 the eighteenthВҰ172767 year of KingВҰ172761 Yehoshafat'sВҰ172769 \add reign over\add* YehudahВҰ172771, and he reigned from ShomronВҰ172765 \add (Samaria)\add* for twelve years.
\v 2 He did \add вүҲwhat YahwehВҰ172781 had said\add* was evil, \add вүҲbutВҰ172778 not as bad as\add* his father and motherВҰ172785 \add had been\add*, and he did removeВҰ172786 the pillarВҰ172789 of BaalВҰ172790 thatВҰ172791 his father had made.
\v 3 \add вүҲHowever,\add* he \add вүҲcommitted similar sinsВҰ172796 to those\add* of Nebat'sВҰ172800 son Yarave'amВҰ172797 who had causedВҰ172803 YisraelВҰ172806 to sinВҰ172803 and didn'tВҰ172808 \add вүҲstop doing\add* them.
\rem /s1 War with Moab
\v 4 \add вүҲNow\add* Moab'sВҰ172817 KingВҰ172815 MeshaВҰ172814 was a sheepВҰ172819 breeder, and he would \add вүҲpay an annual tribute\add* to Yisrael'sВҰ172823 king of a hundred thousand young rams, plus the wool of a hundred thousand rams.
\v 5 \add вүҲHowever,\add* after KingВҰ172837 AhabВҰ172835 died, Moab'sВҰ172839 king rebelledВҰ172836 against Yisrael'sВҰ172841 \add вүҲcontrol over them\add*.
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ172843\add* KingВҰ172844 YehoramВҰ172845 set out from ShomronВҰ172848 andВҰ172849 musteredВҰ172849 all \add вүҲof Yisrael'sВҰ172854 fighters\add*.
\v 7 ThenВҰ172856 he sent this message to KingВҰ172861 YehoshafatВҰ172860 of YehudahВҰ172863, вҖңMoab'sВҰ172866 king has rebelledВҰ172867 against me. Will you \add вүҲjoin inВҰ172868 battle withВҰ172868 me against them\add*?вҖқ
\p вҖңI'll \add вүҲjoin you\add*,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖң\add вүҲYou and me are together. My people are your people, and my horses are your horses\add*.
\v 8 \add вүҲWhat's our strategy? Which way should we go in\add*?вҖқ he \add вүҲasked\add*.
\p вҖң\add вүҲThrough\add* the EdomВҰ172893 wildernessВҰ172892,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ172895\add* the kings of YisraelВҰ172897, YehudahВҰ172900, andВҰ172895 EdomВҰ172903 \add took their armies\add* onВҰ172915 a sevenВҰ172906 day trip \add circling around\add*, butВҰ172895 they \add вүҲdidn'tВҰ172908 find enough\add* waterВҰ172911 for the men or their animalsВҰ172913,
\v 10 andВҰ172917 Yisrael'sВҰ172919 kingВҰ172918 \add вүҲcomplained\add*, вҖңOh \add dear\add*, \add вүҲit seems that\add* YahwehВҰ172924 \add вүҲhas sent inВҰ172931 us\add* threeВҰ172925 kingsВҰ172927 to \add вүҲallow MoabВҰ172933 to defeat us\add*.вҖқ
\v 11 \add вүҲButВҰ172935\add* YehoshafatВҰ172936 \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңIsn't thereВҰ172937 one of Yahweh's prophets here, so we might inquireВҰ172941 from Yahweh throughВҰ172945 himВҰ172945?вҖқ
\p вҖңThere's ElishaВҰ172954,вҖқ one of the servantsВҰ172948 of Yisrael'sВҰ172951 kingВҰ172949 answeredВҰ172946, вҖңShafat'sВҰ172957 son, \add the prophet\add* who \add вүҲwas Eliyah'sВҰ172965 assistant\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 вҖң\add Yes,\add* \add вүҲhe receives Yahweh's messagesВҰ172971\add*,вҖқ saidВҰ172967 YehoshafatВҰ172968.
\p SoВҰ172967 the kings of YisraelВҰ172977, Yehudah, andВҰ172967 EdomВҰ172980, wentВҰ172974 to see him.
\v 13 \add вүҲButВҰ172982\add* ElishaВҰ172983 \add вүҲasked\add* Yisrael'sВҰ172987 king, вҖңWhat \add вүҲdo you and me have inВҰ173015 common\add*? Go \add and inquire from\add* your father's prophets and your mother'sВҰ173000 prophets.вҖқ
\p вҖңNo,вҖқ the king of Yisrael said. вҖң\add We came\add* because YahwehВҰ173009 has called for \add вүҲus\add* threeВҰ173010 kingsВҰ173011 to \add вүҲallow us to be defeated by\add* MoabВҰ173017.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 вҖң\add вүҲAs army commander YahwehВҰ173023 lives\add*,вҖқ ElishaВҰ173020 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ173019\add*, вҖң\add вүҲthe one who I serve\add*, I wouldn't \add вүҲbe talking to you or even faceВҰ173030 you, if I hadn't recognised\add* KingВҰ173032 Yehoshafat of YehudahВҰ173034.
\v 15 \add вүҲSoВҰ173045 now\add* bring me a \add вүҲmusician\add*.
\p ThenВҰ173045 whileВҰ173051 the musician playedВҰ173051, YahwehВҰ173057 \add вүҲspoke to him\add*
\v 16 andВҰ173059 he saidВҰ173059, вҖңYahweh saysВҰ173061 that this valley \add вүҲwill store lots of water\add*.\f + \fr 3:16 \ft It's not really clear if he's saying that Yahweh will fill natural pools in the valley with water, or if he's instructing the armies to dig trenches or scrape pools that Yahweh will then fill with water.\f*
\v 17 \add *He\add* saysВҰ173074 that you all won'tВҰ173076 see any windВҰ173079 or rain, \add вүҲyet\add* this valley will be filledВҰ173086 with waterВҰ173087, and you and your animalsВҰ173091 \add will have plenty\add* to drinkВҰ173088.
\v 18 \add вүҲThat's a piece of cake\add* for YahwehВҰ173096. \add вүҲWhat's more, he'll give youВҰ173101 victory over\add* MoabВҰ173100.
\v 19 You'll all \add вүҲattackВҰ173103 everyВҰ173104 important city, including their fortifiedВҰ173107 ones\add*. You can chop down their fruit trees, block up their springsВҰ173119, andВҰ173103 ruin their good land withВҰ173127 stonesВҰ173127.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲThe next day atВҰ173130 the timeВҰ173131 of the morningВҰ173130\add* sacrificeВҰ173132, \add вүҲto their amazement\add* there was water flowing from EdomВҰ173138 andВҰ173129 covering the ground.
\p
\v 21 \add By thenВҰ173145\add*, \add вүҲthe people of\add* MoabВҰ173147 had heardВҰ173148 that the kingsВҰ173152 had comeВҰ173151 to battle them, \add вүҲso\add* they summonedВҰ173155 \add вүҲeveryoneВҰ173157 who could wear a sword andВҰ173145 stationed them\add* beside the borderВҰ173163.
\v 22 \add вүҲButВҰ173165\add* when they got up earlyВҰ173165 the next morningВҰ173166 andВҰ173165 the sunВҰ173167 rose, from \add вүҲthe direction where they were, the water appeared to be\add* red like bloodВҰ173179.
\v 23 вҖңThat's bloodВҰ173182,вҖқ they \add вүҲexclaimed\add*. вҖңThose \add three\add* kingsВҰ173186 \add вүҲmust have turned against each other and killedВҰ173187 each other. SoВҰ173181 let's go, MoabВҰ173194, and collect the spoilВҰ173193\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 24 \add вүҲButВҰ173196\add* when they reached the \add вүҲallied\add* camp, the \add вүҲallies attacked\add* and they fled \add вүҲaway\add*. ThenВҰ173196 the \add вүҲallies entered MoabВҰ173206 and attacked there\add*.
\v 25 They tore down the citiesВҰ173218, and \add вүҲeach person threwВҰ173224 a stone onto the good land, making it useless\add*. They \add вүҲblocked up\add* every springВҰ173231, and they \add вүҲchopped down\add* every good tree. \add Eventually,\add* only \add their capital city of\add* Kir-Hareset remained standing \add вүҲwithВҰ173245 its stone walls, butВҰ173218 they attackedВҰ173249 that as well using slingshotsВҰ173248\add*.
\p
\v 26 \add вүҲWhenВҰ173251\add* Moab'sВҰ173253 king saw that the \add вүҲattackers\add* were strongerВҰ173256 than them, he took a team of sevenВҰ173261 hundredВҰ173263 swordsmenВҰ173266 to try to breakВҰ173267 throughВҰ173267 to the king of EdomВҰ173271, \add вүҲbutВҰ173251 they failed\add*.
\v 27 \add вүҲSoВҰ173275\add* he tookВҰ173275 his oldest son (who would have become the next king) and sacrificed him \add publicly on top of the city\add* wall. \add вүҲThisВҰ173276 made theirВҰ173299 people crazy furious\add* againstВҰ173297 YisraelВҰ173295, so they left and returnedВҰ173298 home.
\c 4
\s1 Elisha helps a poor widow
\rem /s1 Elisha and the Widow's Oil; Elisha Helps a Poor Widow; The Widow's Oil
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add One day\add* a womanВҰ173302 \add вүҲwho was a wife of one of the prophets-in-training\add*, called out to ElishaВҰ173311, вҖңYour servant, my husbandВҰ173314, died, and you yourself know that your servant \add вүҲserved\add* YahwehВҰ173324. \add вүҲNow\add* the moneylender has come to take two of my childrenВҰ173331 \add вүҲin payment to become his\add* slavesВҰ173333.вҖқ
\p
\v 2 вҖң\add Hmmh,\add* what could I do to help you?вҖқ ElishaВҰ173337 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ173335\add*. вҖңTell me, what have you got in your house?вҖқ
\p вҖңYour servant'sВҰ173353 got nothing in the house except a flask of oil,вҖқ she \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 3 He told her, вҖңGo \add andВҰ173362\add* askВҰ173364 for emptyВҰ173378 containers from all of yourВҰ173374 neighboursВҰ173374. \add вүҲMake sure you get plenty of them\add*.
\v 4 ThenВҰ173383 goВҰ173383 and shut the doorВҰ173385 behind you and your sonsВҰ173389, and pour oil into all those containers. \add вүҲOnce each one's full, set it\add* asideВҰ173397.вҖқ
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ173399\add* she wentВҰ173399 and she shut the doorВҰ173402 \add of her house\add* \add вүҲwith her and her sons inside\add*. They would bringВҰ173407 \add the empty containers\add* to her, and she poured \add the oil\add*.
\v 6 \add вүҲEventually when she told one of her sons to bringВҰ173421 the next container, he told her that thereВҰ173427 wasn't any more, andВҰ173413 at that point, the oilВҰ173431 stoppedВҰ173430 flowing\add*.
\p
\v 7 Then she wentВҰ173433 and informed the manВҰ173435 of GodВҰ173436, and he told her, вҖңGo \add and\add* sell the oilВҰ173442 and pay off your debt. Then you and your sonsВҰ173449 can liveВҰ173451 onВҰ173452 the rest.вҖқ
\s1 Elisha brings a child back to life
\rem /s1 Elisha and the Rich Woman from Shunem; The Shunammite's Son Restored to Life; Elisha and the Woman from Shunem; Elisha Raises the Shunammite's Son
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲOne\add* dayВҰ173456, ElishaВҰ173458 went to ShunemВҰ173461, and there was a \add вүҲwealthy\add* womanВҰ173463 there who \add вүҲinvited him in for a meal\add*. \add вүҲAfter that, he dropped in there for a meal whenever he was going past\add*,
\v 9 andВҰ173480 the woman said to her husbandВҰ173483, вҖң\add вүҲYou know, I'm sure that this man who often drops in on us\add* is a holy man of GodВҰ173490.
\v 10 Please, \add вүҲcan we make a smallВҰ173503 upstairsВҰ173500 roomВҰ173500 onВҰ173512 our flat roof\add*? And we could put a bed and a lampstand inВҰ173512 it for him, plus a tableВҰ173508 and chairВҰ173509. \add вүҲThen whenever he's passing through here, he'll have his own spot to stay\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲAnother\add* dayВҰ173518 when Elisha arrived, he wentВҰ173521 up to his roomВҰ173524 andВҰ173517 lay down.
\v 12 ThenВҰ173529 he told his servantВҰ173533 GehaziВҰ173532 to call the ShunammiteВҰ173535 \add woman\add*, \add вүҲso\add* he calledВҰ173537 her and she \add came and\add* stoodВҰ173540 in front of \add @Elisha\add*.
\v 13 He told \add @Gehazi\add*, вҖңNow tell her \add вүҲthat we've noticed how she looks after us, and ask her what we can do for her? Can we\add* speakВҰ173563 to the kingВҰ173568 for her or to the captain of the army?вҖқ
\p \add вүҲButВҰ173543\add* she \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖң\add вүҲI have family and friends all around me\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 \add After she'd left again,\add* heВҰ173592 asked \add GehaziВҰ173585\add*, вҖң\add Well\add*, what can I do for her?вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Hmmh,\add*вҖқ Gehazi \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖңShe doesn't have a son, andВҰ173580 her husbandВҰ173591 is old.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 вҖңCall her thenВҰ173594,вҖқ Elisha saidВҰ173594. \add вүҲSoВҰ173594\add* he calledВҰ173598 her and she came and stoodВҰ173601 inВҰ173602 the doorwayВҰ173602,
\v 16 andВҰ173613 \add @Elisha\add* told her, вҖң\add вүҲIn due course after the normal months\add*, you'll have a son to hold.вҖқ
\p вҖңNo, my masterВҰ173616, manВҰ173617 of GodВҰ173618,вҖқ she \add вүҲstammered\add*. вҖңDon't lie to yourВҰ173622 female servantВҰ173622.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 ThenВҰ173624 the womanВҰ173625 became pregnantВҰ173624 andВҰ173624 gave birthВҰ173626 to a son after the normal time, just as ElishaВҰ173630 had told her.
\p
\v 18 The childВҰ173639 grew up andВҰ173638 \add вүҲone dayВҰ173641\add* he wentВҰ173642 out to his fatherВҰ173645 who was with the harvesters,
\v 19 andВҰ173650 he \add вүҲcalled\add* to his father, вҖңMy head, my head.вҖқ
\p \add @His father\add* told one of the servantsВҰ173660, вҖңCarry him \add home\add* to his motherВҰ173664.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲSoВҰ173666\add* \add @the servant\add* \add вүҲcarriedВҰ173666 him back\add* to his motherВҰ173670, andВҰ173666 he satВҰ173671 on herВҰ173674 knees untilВҰ173675 noon when he diedВҰ173678.
\v 21 \add @His mother\add* \add вүҲcarried him\add* up andВҰ173680 laid him on the bed of the manВҰ173685 of GodВҰ173686, \add вүҲshutting the door behindВҰ173688 her as\add* she went out.
\v 22 ThenВҰ173691 she calledВҰ173691 her husbandВҰ173694 and told \add >him\add*, вҖңPlease send one of the young men and one of the donkeysВҰ173704 to me \add вүҲso I can run and see\add* the man of GodВҰ173709 and \add вүҲthenВҰ173691 come back\add*.вҖқ
\v 23 вҖңWhy are youВҰ173714 goingВҰ173716 there today?вҖқ he \add вүҲasked\add*. вҖңIt's not a \add вүҲreligious holiday\add*.вҖқ
\p вҖң\add вүҲIt'll be okay\add*,вҖқ she \add вүҲanswered\add*,
\v 24 and she saddledВҰ173728 the donkeyВҰ173729, and told the young man, вҖң\add Now, let's\add* goВҰ173735! You lead and don'tВҰ173736 \add вүҲslacken off for my comfort\add* unless I tell you to.вҖқ
\v 25 SoВҰ173748 \add #they\add* \add вүҲset off to seek\add* out the man of GodВҰ173753 at MtВҰ173756. KarmelВҰ173757.
\p WhenВҰ173748 \add @Elisha\add* saw her \add coming\add* from a distanceВҰ173764, he told GehaziВҰ173768, вҖңLookВҰ173762, there'sВҰ173770 the ShunammiteВҰ173771 woman.
\v 26 Now, pleaseВҰ173777, runВҰ173775 to meet her and \add вүҲaskВҰ173779\add* her, вҖҳAre you all right? Is your husbandВҰ173785 all right? Is your childВҰ173787 all right?вҖҷ вҖқ
\p вҖң\add вүҲEverything's all right\add*,вҖқ she \add вүҲanswered\add*.
\v 27 ThenВҰ173791 she got to the mountainВҰ173798 and to the man of God, and she \add knelt and\add* grabbed his feetВҰ173800. GehaziВҰ173802 came over to push her away, \add вүҲbut\add* the man of God said, вҖңLeave her because \add вүҲshe's upset\add*, but YahwehВҰ173816 has hiddenВҰ173817 \add @the problem\add* from meвҖ”he hasn't informed me.вҖқ
\p
\v 28 вҖңDid I askВҰ173824 for a son from \add youВҰ173831\add*, my masterВҰ173827?вҖқ she saidВҰ173823. вҖң\add No, butВҰ173823\add* didn'tВҰ173828 I sayВҰ173829, вҖҳDon't \add вүҲmislead me\add*?вҖҷ вҖқ
\v 29 ThenВҰ173834 he told GehaziВҰ173835, вҖң\add вүҲTuck in your robe\add* and takeВҰ173838 my staff in your handВҰ173840, and goВҰ173841 \add quickly\add*. If you \add вүҲmeet anyone\add*, \add just keep going and don't stop to\add* bless them, and if someone blesses you, \add don't stop to\add* answerВҰ173853 them. \add WhenВҰ173834 you get there,\add* lay my staff onВҰ173840 the young man's faceВҰ173858.вҖқ
\p
\v 30 \add вүҲButВҰ173861\add* the motherВҰ173862 of the young man said, вҖңBy the life of YahwehВҰ173866 and the life of yourВҰ173869 spirit, I won't leaveВҰ173872 \add without\add* you.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ173861\add* he got \add вүҲready\add*, and went \add вүҲwith\add* her.
\v 31 \add вүҲHowever,\add* Gehazi \add вүҲhad gone ahead\add* and he put the staffВҰ173883 on the young man's faceВҰ173886, butВҰ173877 he didn't \add вүҲopen his eyes or make a\add* soundВҰ173889. \add вүҲSoВҰ173877\add* he returnedВҰ173892 to meet \add @Elisha\add* and told him that the young man didn't wake up.
\p
\v 32 \add вүҲWhenВҰ173902\add* ElishaВҰ173903 reached the houseВҰ173904, \add вүҲit was a shock to see\add* the young man lying on his bed, deadВҰ173907.
\v 33 He wentВҰ173913 in and he shut the doorВҰ173915 behindВҰ173916 the \add вүҲother\add* two, and he prayedВҰ173918 to YahwehВҰ173921.
\v 34 Then he \add вүҲgot on the bed\add*, and he lay on the child and bent down near him, putting his mouth on his mouth, and his eyes on his eyes, and his palms on his palms. Then the child's bodyВҰ173945 \add вүҲstarted getting warmer\add*,
\v 35 and he \add вүҲgot down\add* and walked \add вүҲaround the room several times\add*. ThenВҰ173948 he \add вүҲgot onВҰ173950 the bed\add* \add again\add*, and bent down near him. TheВҰ173966 young man gasped \add вүҲseveral\add* times, and thenВҰ173948 openedВҰ173964 his eyesВҰ173968.
\v 36 ThenВҰ173970 he called to GehaziВҰ173973, and \add вүҲtold him to call the\add* ShunammiteВҰ173978 woman, and he called her, and she cameВҰ173981 and \add @Elisha\add* told \add >her\add*, вҖң\add вүҲHere, takeВҰ173984\add* your son.вҖқ
\v 37 Then she cameВҰ173987 in and \add вүҲfell to her knees in front of him with her face\add* to the groundВҰ173993. Then she pickedВҰ173994 up her son and wentВҰ173998 out,
\v 38 and ElishaВҰ174001 returnedВҰ174002 to GilgalВҰ174003.
\s1 Two more miracles
\rem /s1 Elisha Purifies the Pot of Stew; Death in the Pot; Miracles during a Famine; Two More Miracles
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p At that time, there was a drought and the \add вүҲprophets-in-training\add* were sittingВҰ174008 facing himВҰ174009, and Elisha told his servantВҰ174011, вҖңGet the largeВҰ174014 pot and boil a stew for \add вүҲthese prophets-in-training\add*.вҖқ
\v 39 One \add person\add* wentВҰ174020 out to the countrysideВҰ174024 to gatherВҰ174025 herbsВҰ174026, and he foundВҰ174027 a \add вүҲwild\add* vineВҰ174028, and he collected \add вүҲwild\add* fruit from itвҖ”\add вүҲas many as he could hold in the fold of his robe\add*. ThenВҰ174020 \add вүҲnot realising that they were poisonous\add*, he cameВҰ174036 and he \add вүҲsliced\add* them into the pot of stew.
\v 40 ThenВҰ174047 they \add вүҲservedВҰ174047\add* it up for the menВҰ174048 to eat, \add вүҲbutВҰ174047\add* when they ate it, they called out, вҖңManВҰ174058 of GodВҰ174059, there's \add вүҲpoison\add* inВҰ174057 that pot!вҖқ
\v 41 вҖңBring me some flourВҰ174067,вҖқ \add @Elisha\add* said. ThenВҰ174064 he threwВҰ174068 it into the pot, and said, вҖң\add вүҲServe it up\add* for the peopleВҰ174074 to eatВҰ174075,вҖқ and no one was harmed.
\rem /s1 Elisha Feeds One Hundred Men; Feeding of a Hundred
\p
\v 42 \add One day\add* a man came from Baal-Shalishah, and he broughtВҰ174087 to the man of GodВҰ174089 \add вүҲan offering from the beginning of his harvest\add*: twentyВҰ174092 loaves of barleyВҰ174095 breadВҰ174090, and \add вүҲnewly-harvested\add* corn inВҰ174097 his sack, and \add @Elisha\add* said \add to his servant\add*, вҖңGive it to \add &our\add* peopleВҰ174100 \add вүҲso they can\add* eat.вҖқ
\p
\v 43 вҖңHow \add вүҲcan I divide that out to\add* one hundredВҰ174109 men?вҖқ asked his servantВҰ174104.
\p вҖңGive them to the peopleВҰ174113 \add вүҲso\add* they can eat,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңbecause YahwehВҰ174118 says \add вүҲthat they can eat andВҰ174103 have left-overs\add*.вҖқ
\v 44 \add вүҲSoВҰ174122\add* he \add вүҲlaid it out in front of them\add* and they ateВҰ174124 and had left-overs, \add вүҲjust like YahwehВҰ174127 had said would happen\add*.
\c 5
\s1 Na'aman's healing
\rem /s1 Naaman Is Cured; Naaman Healed of Leprosy; The Healing of Naaman
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲNow\add* Na'aman \add was\add* the captain in Aram's army. \add He\add* was \add вүҲhighly respected by Aram's kingВҰ174134\add*, and was \add вүҲpromoted to a high position\add* because \add вүҲYahwehВҰ174141 had helped Aram (SyriaВҰ174136) win many battles because of him\add*. \add вүҲHowever, despite his\add* military prowess, \add вүҲhe suffered from a serious skin diseaseВҰ174156 called leprosy\add*.\x + \xo 5:1-14: \xt Luk 4:27.\x*
\v 2 \add Previously\add* troops that had been sent out from Aram, had taken a youngВҰ174165 IsraeliВҰ174162 girlВҰ174164 captive andВҰ174158 she \add вүҲhad become Na'aman's wife's servant\add*.
\v 3 \add One day\add* she saidВҰ174171 to herВҰ174174 mistressВҰ174174, вҖң\add вүҲI wish that my masterВҰ174176 would go and see\add* the prophetВҰ174178 who \add lives\add* inВҰ174180 ShomronВҰ174180, and thenВҰ174171 he would \add вүҲcure him of\add* his leprosyВҰ174184.вҖқ
\v 4 \add In due course, Na'aman heard\add* and wentВҰ174186 and told \add вүҲhis masterВҰ174188 what the young IsraeliВҰ174195 girlВҰ174193 had said\add*.
\v 5 The king of AramВҰ174201 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ174198\add*, вҖң\add вүҲOk, I'll write a letterВҰ174206 to the king of YisraelВҰ174210 for you to take\add*.вҖқ
\p \add вүҲSoВҰ174198\add* \add @Na'aman\add* \add вүҲset off, taking along\add* 70kg of goldВҰ174220, 300kg of silverВҰ174217, andВҰ174198 ten sets of \add fine\add* clothes,
\v 6 andВҰ174225 he took the letter to the kingВҰ174229 of YisraelВҰ174230. \add The letter\add* said, вҖң\add вүҲGreetings\add*. WhenВҰ174225 this letter gets to you, see, I've sent my servantВҰ174243 Na'aman to you \add вүҲso that you can heal\add* his skin disease.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲHowever\add* when Yisrael'sВҰ174251 king read the letterВҰ174254, he tore his clothesВҰ174256 \add in despair\add*, and he said, вҖң\add вүҲDo they think that I'm GodВҰ174258 who ends people's lives and gives life to others? Why's this person\add* sendingВҰ174265 a man \add here for me\add* to take away his skin disease? Surely \add вүҲhe must be creating a situation so he has an excuse to attack me!\add*вҖқ
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲLater\add* when ElishaВҰ174286 the man of GodВҰ174289 heardВҰ174284 that Yisrael'sВҰ174295 king had torn his clothes, he sent \add вүҲa message\add* to the king, вҖңWhy did you tear your clothes? Please, let \add вүҲthat man\add* come to me \add вүҲso he can\add* know that thereВҰ174313 \em is\em* a prophetВҰ174314 inВҰ174315 Yisrael.вҖқ
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ174317\add* Na'amanВҰ174318 cameВҰ174317 onВҰ174319 his chariotsВҰ174321 and horsesВҰ174319, and he stoodВҰ174322 atВҰ174319 the entranceВҰ174323 to Elisha'sВҰ174326 houseВҰ174325.
\v 10 ElishaВҰ174330 sentВҰ174328 a messengerВҰ174331 \add out\add* to him to tell him, вҖңGo and wash sevenВҰ174335 timesВҰ174337 inВҰ174338 the YordanВҰ174338 \add river\add*, and \add вүҲthenВҰ174328 you'll be better and yourВҰ174340 skin will goВҰ174333 back to normal\add*.
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲButВҰ174344\add* Na'aman was furious, and he left, saying, вҖңListen, I said to myself that he'd surelyВҰ174353 come out and standВҰ174354 \add there\add* and call on the nameВҰ174356 of his godВҰ174359 YahwehВҰ174358, thenВҰ174344 he'd wave his handВҰ174361 \add вүҲover my body\add* and take away the skin diseaseВҰ174366.
\v 12 Aren't the DamascusВҰ174374 rivers Abanah and PharparВҰ174372 better than \add вүҲany river in\add* YisraelВҰ174377? Can't I bathe in them \add instead\add* and \add вүҲget healedВҰ174382\add*?вҖқ \add вүҲSo\add* he turnedВҰ174383 and he wentВҰ174384 \add вүҲoff angrily\add*.
\v 13 ThenВҰ174387 \add some of\add* his servantsВҰ174388 \add вүҲapproached him and suggested\add*, вҖңMy \add вүҲmaster\add*, if the prophetВҰ174395 \add вүҲhad told you to do something more significant\add*, wouldn'tВҰ174392 you have done it? \add вүҲSoВҰ174387 maybe you could do the simple thingВҰ174393 that\add* he told you: wash and \add вүҲget better\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ174408\add* \add @Na'aman\add* went down to the YordanВҰ174410 river and dippedВҰ174409 inВҰ174410 \add *it\add* sevenВҰ174411 timesВҰ174412 \add вүҲlike the manВҰ174414 of GodВҰ174415 had told him to\add*. ThenВҰ174408 his skin \add вүҲbecame clear again,\add* like the skin of a youngВҰ174420 boy, and he was \add вүҲhealed\add*.
\v 15 ThenВҰ174423 he returnedВҰ174423 to the manВҰ174426 of GodВҰ174442 \add вүҲalong withВҰ174449 his entireВҰ174429 retinue\add*. \add вүҲStanding in front of him\add*, he saidВҰ174435, вҖңLook, please. I knowВҰ174439 that thereВҰ174441 is no godВҰ174442 in all the earthВҰ174445 except in YisraelВҰ174449. Now, please, \add вүҲacceptВҰ174451\add* a blessingВҰ174454 from your servantВҰ174456.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 вҖңBy the lifeВҰ174459 of YahwehВҰ174461 \add вүҲwho I serve\add*,вҖқ he \add вүҲrespondedВҰ174458\add*, вҖңI won't take \add anything\add*.вҖқ
\p \add @Na'aman\add* urgedВҰ174469 him to take \add >something\add*, butВҰ174458 he kept refusingВҰ174473.
\v 17 ThenВҰ174475 Na'aman said, вҖң\add вүҲWell\add* if not, pleaseВҰ174480, \add at least\add* may \add вүҲwe load a pair of mulesВҰ174485 with some soil\add* \add to take back with us\add*, because \add from now on,\add* your servant will no longer make a burntВҰ174493 offeringВҰ174490 or a sacrificeВҰ174494 to otherВҰ174496 godsвҖ”only to YahwehВҰ174500.
\v 18 \add вүҲHowever,\add* \add I'll ask in advance:\add* May Yahweh forgive your servant when my masterВҰ174508 goes to the house of \add the god\add* Rimmon to prostrate himself thereВҰ174513, and he's leaningВҰ174516 onВҰ174507 my hand, and I prostrate myself in the house of Rimmon. When I prostrate myself in the house of Rimmon, please may Yahweh forgive your servant \add вүҲfor this one activity\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 вҖңGo in peaceВҰ174538,вҖқ \add @Elisha\add* \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\rem /s1 Gehazi's Greed; The Greed of Gehazi
\p \add вүҲAfter they'd gone a short distanceВҰ174541,\add*
\v 20 Elisha'sВҰ174549 servantВҰ174548 saidВҰ174546 \add to himself\add*, вҖң\add вүҲHmmh\add*, my masterВҰ174556 \add вүҲwouldn't take anythingВҰ174579 from that\add* Na'aman the ArameanВҰ174560. By the lifeВҰ174568 of YahwehВҰ174556, \add вүҲI think I should runВҰ174575 afterВҰ174576 him and take something that he broughtВҰ174567\add*.вҖқ
\v 21 \add вүҲSoВҰ174581\add* GehaziВҰ174582 \add вүҲhurried\add* after Na'amanВҰ174584. \add вүҲWhenВҰ174581\add* Na'aman sawВҰ174585 a person running after him, he got down from his chariotВҰ174591 to meet him, andВҰ174581 he saidВҰ174593, вҖң\add вүҲIs there a problem\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 22 вҖңPeace,вҖқ he saidВҰ174596, вҖңMy masterВҰ174599 sentВҰ174600 me to tell you that two youngВҰ174609 \add вүҲprophets-in-training arrived\add* from the hill country of EfrayimВҰ174611. \add Can we\add* pleaseВҰ174616 have 30kg of silverВҰ174620 andВҰ174596 two sets of clothing for them?вҖқ
\p
\v 23 вҖң\add вүҲSure\add*,вҖқ saidВҰ174625 Na'aman. вҖңTake 60kg,вҖқ he urgedВҰ174630 him. ThenВҰ174625 he \add вүҲseparated\add* 60kg of silverВҰ174635 into two bags along withВҰ174636 two sets of clothes, thenВҰ174625 he gaveВҰ174641 them to two of hisВҰ174647 young men \add вүҲto carry back for him\add*.
\v 24 WhenВҰ174649 \add @Gehazi\add* reached the hill, he sentВҰ174657 the menВҰ174660 back and they \add вүҲreturned\add* \add to Na'aman\add*. ThenВҰ174649 he tookВҰ174653 \add @the sacks that they'd brought\add* and \add вүҲhid\add* them inВҰ174656 the houseВҰ174656.
\v 25 \add вүҲWhenВҰ174663 he wentВҰ174665 back in to\add* his masterВҰ174669, ElishaВҰ174672 \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖң\add вүҲWhere did you go\add*, GehaziВҰ174675?вҖқ
\p вҖңYour servantВҰ174680 \add вүҲhasn't been anywhere\add*,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 26 вҖң\add вүҲWasn't I there in spirit when\add* a manВҰ174693 turnedВҰ174691 from on his chariotВҰ174695 to meet you?вҖқ \add @Elisha\add* saidВҰ174684 to him, вҖңIs this a timeВҰ174697 to take silver or clothingВҰ174703, or to take oliveВҰ174704 trees or vineyardsВҰ174705, or sheepВҰ174706 or cattle, or male or femaleВҰ174709 servants?
\v 27 \add Because of that,\add* Na'aman's leprosyВҰ174711 will \add вүҲtransfer\add* to youВҰ174715 and to yourВҰ174716 offspring forever.вҖқ WhenВҰ174711 \add @Gehazi\add* \add вүҲleft the room, his skin had gone white as snow and he was now a leper\add*.
\c 6
\s1 The floating axe head
\rem /s1 The Recovery of the Ax Head; An Axhead Floats; The Floating Ax Head; The Miracle of the Ax Head
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add One day,\add* the \add вүҲprophets-in-training\add* saidВҰ174724 to ElishaВҰ174730, вҖңPlease look, The placeВҰ174734 whereВҰ174735 we're sitting \add вүҲto learn from you\add* is too narrow \add вүҲto fit us all in\add*.
\v 2 Please, let us go \add вүҲdown by\add* the YordanВҰ174748 \add river\add*, and let \add вүҲeach of us cut down and bring back a log\add* from there \add вүҲto make a new classroom for us to sit in\add*.вҖқ
\p вҖңGo \add ahead\add*,вҖқ he \add вүҲanswered\add*.
\p
\v 3 One of them \add вүҲinsisted\add*, вҖңPlease, \add вүҲsay that you'll\add* come with your servantsВҰ174771.вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Okay thenВҰ174764,\add* I'll come,вҖқ he said.
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ174776\add* he wentВҰ174776 with them to the YordanВҰ174779 valley to cut down \add some\add* treesВҰ174781,
\v 5 \add вүҲbutВҰ174783\add* while one of them was chopping down a tree, suddenly the axe head separated from the handle andВҰ174783 \add вүҲwent flying\add* into the waterВҰ174793. \add @The man\add* called out to Elisha, вҖңOh, MasterВҰ174797, what should I do? \add вүҲIt's not my axe\add*вҖ”I borrowed it!вҖқ
\p
\v 6 вҖңWhere did it fall in?вҖқ the man of GodВҰ174804 \add вүҲasked\add*. \add вүҲAfter the man had shown him the placeВҰ174810\add*, \add @Elisha\add* cut off \add a stick\add* and threwВҰ174814 it thereВҰ174816, and the iron \add axe head\add* \add вүҲrose to the surface\add*.
\v 7 вҖң\add вүҲNow get it out\add*,вҖқ he saidВҰ174820, and the man stretched out and grabbed it.
\s1 The Syrian army is defeated
\rem /s1 The Aramean Attack Is Thwarted; Elisha Traps Blinded Arameans; The Syrian Army Is Defeated; Elisha Traps the Arameans
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 8 \add In those days,\add* the kingВҰ174828 of AramВҰ174829 was fightingВҰ174831 against YisraelВҰ174832, and he'd instruct his servants, вҖң\add вүҲSet up\add* \add #our\add* camp inВҰ174832 such and such a placeВҰ174840.вҖқ
\v 9 \add вүҲHowever,\add* the manВҰ174846 of GodВҰ174847 sentВҰ174845 to Yisrael'sВҰ174851 kingВҰ174850 \add вүҲto warn him\add*, вҖңBeware of passing by such andВҰ174845 such a placeВҰ174855, because the Aramean \add army\add* \add вүҲwill be attacking thereВҰ174859\add*.вҖқ
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ174863\add* the kingВҰ174864 would send messengers to the people at thatВҰ174869 placeВҰ174868 \add вүҲto warn them to watch andВҰ174863 be prepared\add*.
\p \add вүҲThatВҰ174865 happened several timesВҰ174883\add*
\v 11 and the Aramean king \add вүҲgot very upset about it\add*. He calledВҰ174894 in his servantsВҰ174897 and demanded, вҖң\add вүҲWhich one of you\add* \add is a traitorвҖ”passing military intelligence\add* to the king of YisraelВҰ174908?вҖқ
\p
\v 12 вҖңNo, my masterВҰ174914 the king,вҖқ a servantВҰ174912 \add вүҲanswered\add*. вҖңIt's the prophetВҰ174919 ElishaВҰ174918 in YisraelВҰ174921 who tellsВҰ174922 their king the things thatВҰ174928 you say \add even\add* in yourВҰ174930 bedroom.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 вҖңGo and find out whereВҰ174936 he is,вҖқ he \add instructed\add*, вҖңand I'll sendВҰ174938 some \add men\add* thereВҰ174944 to captureВҰ174939 him.вҖқ
\p вҖңHe's inВҰ174945 DothanВҰ174945,вҖқ he was told \add later\add*.
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ174947\add* he sentВҰ174947 chariotsВҰ174951 and horsesВҰ174950 and a large contingent, and theyВҰ174954 \add вүҲarrived thereВҰ174949\add* at nightВҰ174955 and surroundedВҰ174956 the townВҰ174959.
\p
\v 15 Early \add the next morning\add*, the servant of the manВҰ174963 of God got up, and going outside he was \add вүҲshocked to see\add* chariotsВҰ174975 and horsesВҰ174974 and an army surroundingВҰ174970 the townВҰ174973, \add вүҲso he called\add* \add @Elisha\add*, вҖңOh, my masterВҰ174980! What will we do?вҖқ
\p
\v 16 вҖңDon't \add вүҲbe afraidВҰ174987\add*,вҖқ he saidВҰ174984, вҖңbecause \add вүҲwe have many more than that on our side\add*.вҖқ
\v 17 Then Elisha prayedВҰ174995, вҖңYahweh, pleaseВҰ175001 \add вүҲenable\add* his \add вүҲsight so he can\add* see.вҖқ Then Yahweh \add вүҲenabled\add* the eyes of the young man, and he \add вүҲwas stunned to see\add* that the hillВҰ175014 was \add вүҲcovered with\add* chariotsВҰ175017 of fire and horsesВҰ175016 all aroundВҰ175019 Elisha.
\p
\v 18 \add вүҲWhenВҰ175022 the Arameans approached to swoop inВҰ175038\add*, Elisha prayedВҰ175024 to Yahweh, вҖңPlease, strikeВҰ175030 \add вүҲthose warriors\add* with blinding light.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ175022\add* \add @Yahweh\add* struckВҰ175039 them with blinding light \add вүҲjust as Elisha had requestedВҰ175024\add*,
\v 19 and ElishaВҰ175046 told them, вҖңThis isn't the \add right\add* wayВҰ175049, and this isn't the townВҰ175052. \add вүҲFollow\add* me, and let me lead you to the manВҰ175059 you're looking for.вҖқ
\p ThenВҰ175044 he led them to ShomronВҰ175064 \add (Samaria)\add*,
\v 20 and when they'd enteredВҰ175067 \add *the city\add*, ElishaВҰ175070 said, вҖңYahweh, open the eyes of theseВҰ175077 people \add вүҲso they can\add* see.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ175066\add* Yahweh openedВҰ175079 theirВҰ175083 eyes, and thenВҰ175066 they \add вүҲwere stunned to see\add* that they were in the middleВҰ175086 of Shomron.
\p
\v 21 WhenВҰ175089 he saw them, the kingВҰ175090 of YisraelВҰ175092 \add вүҲasked\add* ElishaВҰ175095, вҖңShould I \add вүҲkill\add* them? Should I \add вүҲkill\add* them, my fatherВҰ175100?вҖқ
\v 22 вҖң\add No,\add* don'tВҰ175103 \add вүҲkill\add* them,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖң\add вүҲWould you cold-bloodedly kill your prisoners of war\add*? \add No,\add* \add вүҲgive them\add* bread and waterВҰ175113 and \add вүҲlet them\add* eatВҰ175115 and drinkВҰ175116, and thenВҰ175102 they can \add вүҲreturn\add* to theirВҰ175120 masterВҰ175120.вҖқ
\v 23 \add вүҲSoВҰ175122\add* \add @the king\add* preparedВҰ175122 a \add вүҲlarge meal\add* for them, and theyВҰ175135 ate and drank, and he sentВҰ175128 them \add вүҲoff to return\add* to their masterВҰ175132. \add вүҲAfter that,\add* the Aramean troops didn'tВҰ175133 continue \add вүҲtheir ventures\add* into YisraelВҰ175141.
\s1 Ben-Hadad besieges Shomron/Samaria
\rem /s1 Ben-Hadad Besieges Samaria; Ben-hadad's Siege of Samaria; The Siege of Samaria; Famine in Besieged Samaria
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 24 \add вүҲSometime afterВҰ175145 that,\add* KingВҰ175152 BenВҰ175149-HadadВҰ175151 of AramВҰ175154 assembled all of his \add вүҲwarriors\add* and \add вүҲattacked\add* ShomronВҰ175164 \add (Samaria)\add*, and besieged it.
\v 25 \add вүҲBeingВҰ175169 surrounded like that\add* \add caused\add* a terrible famineВҰ175167 inside \add *the city\add*, untilВҰ175173 a donkey'sВҰ175177 head would be \add вүҲsold for\add* eightyВҰ175178 silver \add coins\add*, andВҰ175166 a \add вүҲcup\add* of doves'ВҰ175183 droppings was \add вүҲsold\add* for five silver \add coins\add*.
\p
\v 26 \add вүҲOne day as\add* the king of YisraelВҰ175193 was \add вүҲwalking past\add* on the \add top of the city\add* wall, a womanВҰ175198 criedВҰ175199 out to him, вҖңSave \add me\add*, my masterВҰ175203, the king!вҖқ
\p
\v 27 вҖң\add If\add* YahwehВҰ175210 won'tВҰ175207 save you, \add вүҲhow could I possibly\add* save you?вҖқ he \add вүҲsnapped\add*. вҖң\add Some grain\add* from the threshingВҰ175215 floorВҰ175215 or \add some wine\add* from the winepress?вҖқ
\v 28 ThenВҰ175221 he \add вүҲasked\add* her, вҖң\add Okay,\add* \add вүҲwhat's your problem\add*?вҖқ
\p вҖңThis womanВҰ175229 said to me, вҖҳ\add вүҲLet's have\add* your son andВҰ175221 we'll eat him today, thenВҰ175221 we'll eat my son tomorrowВҰ175243,вҖҷ вҖқ she \add вүҲanswered\add*.
\v 29 вҖң\add вүҲSoВҰ175245\add* we boiled my son and ateВҰ175249 him, and thenВҰ175245 the next dayВҰ175252 I saidВҰ175250, вҖҳ\add вүҲHand over\add* your son and we'll eatВҰ175258 him,вҖҷ butВҰ175245 she'd hiddenВҰ175259 \add *him\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 30 WhenВҰ175264 he heardВҰ175265 \add *that\add*, the kingВҰ175266 (standing up on the wall) tore his clothesВҰ175274, andВҰ175264 the peopleВҰ175281 could see \add вүҲto their astonishment that he was wearing sackclothВҰ175283 underneathВҰ175287\add*,
\v 31 and he saidВҰ175289, вҖңMay GodВҰ175295 do that to me and more, if Shafat'sВҰ175305 son ElishaВҰ175302 \add вүҲstill has his head on him by the end of the dayВҰ175307\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 32 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* Elisha was sitting \add вүҲat home\add*, joined by the \add city\add* elders. \add @The king\add* \add вүҲhad sent a warrior ahead of him\add*, \add вүҲand beforeВҰ175318 he'd arrived at the houseВҰ175311\add*, \add @Elisha\add* had told the elders, вҖң\add Well now,\add* \add вүҲthat son of a murdererВҰ175334 has sent an assassin to separate me from\add* my head. Listen, when that \add вүҲhit-man\add* arrives, shut the door and \add вүҲlean against\add* \add *it\add*. \add вүҲHis masterВҰ175352 won'tВҰ175349 be far\add* behindВҰ175353 him.вҖқ
\v 33 He was stillВҰ175373 talkingВҰ175356 with them, when, \add вүҲwow, the warrior was comingВҰ175360 towards the house\add* \add soon followed by the king who\add* saidВҰ175362, вҖң\add вүҲListen, YahwehВҰ175368 caused this disaster so why should I trust\add* \add *him\add* any longer?вҖқ
\c 7
\p
\v 1 вҖң\add вүҲListen to what Yahweh says\add*,вҖқ ElishaВҰ175377 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ175376\add*, вҖңYahweh says that at this timeВҰ175386 tomorrowВҰ175388, a \add вүҲdrum\add* of flourВҰ175391 will be \add вүҲsold\add* for a shekel, and two \add вүҲdrums\add* of barleyВҰ175394 will be \add вүҲsold for\add* for a shekel at the \add вүҲcity\add* gateВҰ175396.вҖқ
\p
\v 2 вҖң\add вүҲThat's impossible\add*,вҖқ \add вүҲinterjected\add* the captainВҰ175400 \add вүҲatВҰ175417 the king's side\add*. вҖңYahwehВҰ175414 \add вүҲwould have to make\add* windowsВҰ175416 inВҰ175417 the sky.вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Oh, it'll happenВҰ175418\add*,вҖқ the manВҰ175410 of GodВҰ175411 \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖң\add andВҰ175399 you'll seeВҰ175423 it withВҰ175417 your own eyesВҰ175424, butВҰ175399 you won'tВҰ175426 get to eatВҰ175427 any of it\add*.вҖқ
\rem /s1 The Siege Lifted; The Arameans Flee; The Syrian Army Leaves; Lepers Visit the Enemy Camp
\p
\v 3 \add That day,\add* fourВҰ175430 menВҰ175431 \add who were isolated due to\add* a skin diseaseВҰ175433 \add вүҲwere at the city\add* gateВҰ175435, and they \add вүҲasked each other\add*, вҖңWhy are we \add just\add* sittingВҰ175443 here untilВҰ175445 we \add вүҲstarve\add*?
\v 4 If we \add вүҲgo into the city, we'll starve to death inВҰ175455 thereВҰ175457, but\add* if we sit here, we'll die \add anyway\add*. \add вүҲWhy don't we go into the Aramean army camp\add*вҖ”if they kill us then we'll die, but if they let us live, then we'll live.вҖқ
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ175479 as it was getting dark\add*, they wentВҰ175486 to goВҰ175481 into the camp, \add вүҲbutВҰ175479 as\add* they cameВҰ175486 to the edge of \add *it\add*, \add вүҲto their surprise there wasn't a person inВҰ175480 sight\add*.
\v 6 \add It turned out that\add* the masterВҰ175498 had causedВҰ175499 the Aramean \add вүҲarmy\add* to hear the sounds of chariotsВҰ175506 and horsesВҰ175508 and a largeВҰ175511 army, \add вүҲso\add* they'd said \add вүҲto each other that the king of YisraelВҰ175522 must have hiredВҰ175518 the HittiteВҰ175526 and Egyptian kings to join together to fight them\add*.
\v 7 \add вүҲAs a result,\add* they'd taken off and fled inВҰ175536 the twilightВҰ175536. They'd abandonedВҰ175537 their tentsВҰ175540 and horsesВҰ175543 and donkeysВҰ175546вҖ”leaving the camp just as itВҰ175550 was, and fled for their livesВҰ175554.
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲSoВҰ175556\add* those \add four\add* \add вүҲmen with leprosy approached\add* the edge of the camp and went \add вүҲinto the first\add* tent, and ateВҰ175568 and drankВҰ175569. Then they \add вүҲtook some\add* goldВҰ175573 and silverВҰ175572 and clothesВҰ175574 out, and they went and hid it. Then they returnedВҰ175577 and went into anotherВҰ175582 tent, and \add вүҲstole some stuff\add* from that one, and went and hid that.
\v 9 ThenВҰ175588 they said \add вүҲto each other\add*, вҖң\add вүҲWe shouldn'tВҰ175593 really be doingВҰ175598 this today\add*. It's a day of good news, butВҰ175588 we've been \add вүҲkeeping it to ourselves\add*. \add If\add* we wait untilВҰ175608 the lightВҰ175610 of the morningВҰ175611, \add вүҲwe'll get punishedВҰ175613 for it\add*, \add вүҲso\add* let's go now andВҰ175588 inform the king'sВҰ175619 householdВҰ175618.вҖқ
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ175621\add* they went and calledВҰ175622 out to one of the cityВҰ175626 gatekeepersВҰ175625, and they informed them, вҖңWe went to the Aramean camp, butВҰ175621 listen, there \add вүҲwasn't anyone there, or any voicesВҰ175640\add*. The horsesВҰ175645 and donkeysВҰ175647 were still tethered, and the tentsВҰ175649 were left just as they were.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 The gatekeepersВҰ175655 calledВҰ175654 out, andВҰ175656 \add вүҲthe news was reported to the palace\add*.
\rem /s1 Israel Plunders the Camp
\v 12 \add вүҲAlthough it was already night-time,\add* the king got up and \add вүҲwarned\add* his servantsВҰ175667, вҖң\add вүҲI'll tell you what's going onВҰ175688 here\add*: The ArameansВҰ175677 know that we're hungryВҰ175681, \add вүҲso\add* they left their camp to go and hide inВҰ175688 the countryside, \add вүҲthinking that we'd go out from the city, and thenВҰ175661 they could capture us and take over\add* the city.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲButВҰ175704\add* one of his servantsВҰ175706 answered, вҖң\add Sir,\add* pleaseВҰ175710, let us take five of the remaining horsesВҰ175714. \add вүҲThey're pretty much finished anyway, like the remaining\add* population of YisraelВҰ175725, \add so there's not much to lose\add*. Let us \add вүҲgo andВҰ175704 investigate\add*.вҖқ
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ175741 with the king's permission,\add* theyВҰ175741 tookВҰ175741 twoВҰ175742 chariotВҰ175743 horsesВҰ175744 andВҰ175741 \add вүҲwent to check out\add* the ArameanВҰ175750 camp.
\v 15 They wentВҰ175755 \add вүҲas far as\add* the YordanВҰ175759 \add river\add*, and \add вүҲwere amazed that\add* the whole road was full of clothingВҰ175765 and equipmentВҰ175766 that the ArameansВҰ175770 had thrownВҰ175769 off inВҰ175771 theirВҰ175771 rush, and the messengersВҰ175774 returnedВҰ175773 and informed the kingВҰ175776.
\v 16 \add вүҲSoВҰ175778\add* the peopleВҰ175779 wentВҰ175778 out and plunderedВҰ175780 the camp. ThenВҰ175778 it happened: a \add вүҲdrum\add* of fine flourВҰ175787 was \add вүҲsold\add* for a shekel, and two \add вүҲdrums\add* of barleyВҰ175790 \add вүҲfor the same amount, just as YahwehВҰ175793 had said would happen\add*.
\p
\v 17 The king had appointedВҰ175796 the captainВҰ175799 who \add вүҲhad argued withВҰ175811 Elisha to be inВҰ175811 charge atВҰ175811\add* the \add city\add* gate, butВҰ175795 the peopleВҰ175810 trampledВҰ175809 him \add *there\add* andВҰ175795 he died, just as the man of GodВҰ175816 had said when the king \add вүҲhad gone to his place\add*.
\v 18 WhenВҰ175842 the manВҰ175825 of GodВҰ175826 had told the kingВҰ175829 that twoВҰ175831 \add вүҲdrums\add* of barleyВҰ175832 \add вүҲwould be sold\add* for a shekel, andВҰ175834 a \add вүҲdrum\add* of flourВҰ175836 \add вүҲalso sold for\add* a shekel the next morning atВҰ175833 the \add *city\add* gateВҰ175841,
\v 19 the captainВҰ175845 \add was the one who'd\add* answeredВҰ175844 the manВҰ175848 of GodВҰ175849 and had said that YahwehВҰ175852 would have to make windowsВҰ175854 inВҰ175855 the sky to do that, and \add @Elisha\add* had told him that he'd see it, butВҰ175844 wouldn't be able to eatВҰ175865 any of it.
\v 20 That'sВҰ175872 exactly what happened, \add вүҲbecause\add* he got trampledВҰ175871 by the \add rush of\add* peopleВҰ175873 atВҰ175874 the gateВҰ175874 andВҰ175867 diedВҰ175875.
\c 8
\s1 The Shunammite woman gets her land back
\rem /s1 The Shunammite Woman's Land Restored; The Shunammite's Land Restored; The Woman from Shunem Returns; The Woman from Shunem Returns Home
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲOne day\add* ElishaВҰ175878 spokeВҰ175879 to the \add Shunammite\add* womanВҰ175882 whoseВҰ175888 son he'd \add вүҲbrought back to lifeВҰ175885\add*, вҖң\add вүҲPack up and leave here\add*, you and your householdВҰ175894, and \add вүҲgoВҰ175891 and stay somewhere else\add*, because Yahweh's \add вүҲgoing to send a seven-year drought\add*.вҖқ
\v 2 \add вүҲSoВҰ175912\add* the womanВҰ175913 got up, and she did \add вүҲwhat the man of GodВҰ175917 told her\add*: She \add вүҲpacked up her householdВҰ175920 and left to go and live\add* in the Philistines' \add вүҲregionВҰ175922\add* for sevenВҰ175925 yearsВҰ175926.
\p
\v 3 \add вүҲThenВҰ175928 eventually after\add* sevenВҰ175930 yearsВҰ175931, the womanВҰ175933 returnedВҰ175932 from the Philistines' \add вүҲregionВҰ175934\add* and she wentВҰ175936 \add вүҲto petition\add* the kingВҰ175940 \add вүҲabout\add* herВҰ175943 houseВҰ175943 and land.
\v 4 \add WhenВҰ175948 she arrived,\add* the king \add вүҲhad asked\add* GehaziВҰ175952, the servantВҰ175953 of the man of God, вҖңPlease tell me all the \add вүҲincredible\add* things thatВҰ175966 ElishaВҰ175969 has done.вҖқ
\v 5 Then \add @Gehazi\add* was telling the king that \add @Elisha\add* had made the dead live, and how the woman who he made her son live was \add вүҲpetitioning\add* the king on behalf of her houseВҰ175996 and her fieldВҰ175999. Then Gehazi \add вүҲexclaimed\add*, вҖңMy masterВҰ176002, the king, this is the woman, and that's her son, who Elisha made live!вҖқ
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ176015\add* the king questioned the womanВҰ176017 andВҰ176015 she told him \add her story\add*. ThenВҰ176015 the king appointedВҰ176021 a courtВҰ176025 official to \add вүҲattend to her case\add*, saying, вҖңReturn everything that belongs to her \add вүҲplus the profit from her\add* fieldВҰ176040 from the dayВҰ176041 she left until now.вҖқ
\s1 Haza'el murders Ben-Hadad
\rem /s1 Elisha and King Benhadad of Syria; Hazael Murders Ben-Hadad; Death of Ben-hadad
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 7 ElishaВҰ176052 wentВҰ176051 to \add Aram'sВҰ176059 capital\add* DamascusВҰ176053 at a time when KingВҰ176057 Ben-Hadad of Aram \add (SyriaВҰ176059)\add* was \add very\add* sickВҰ176060, and someone told him that the manВҰ176066 of GodВҰ176067 was in town.
\v 8 The kingВҰ176073 \add вүҲinstructed\add* \add an official named\add* Haza'el, вҖңTake a giftВҰ176079 \add вүҲwithВҰ176078 youВҰ176078\add* and goВҰ176080 \add вүҲand\add* meet the manВҰ176082 of GodВҰ176083. ThenВҰ176072 inquireВҰ176084 from YahwehВҰ176088 throughВҰ176089 himВҰ176089 \add вүҲto find out if I'll\add* recoverВҰ176091 from this sickness.вҖқ
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ176095\add* Haza'el went to meet \add @Elisha\add* and \add вүҲtook presents withВҰ176100 him loaded onВҰ176100\add* fortyВҰ176106 camelsВҰ176107вҖ”\add some of\add* every good thingВҰ176103 \add that he could find\add* in DamascusВҰ176104. He went and stoodВҰ176109 in front of him and \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңYour servant, KingВҰ176117 BenВҰ176114-HadadВҰ176116 sent me to \add вүҲask you if he'll recoverВҰ176123 from hisВҰ176100\add* sickness?вҖқ
\p
\v 10 вҖңGo \add andВҰ176127\add* tell him that he'll surely live,вҖқ ElishaВҰ176129 \add вүҲanswered\add*. вҖңButВҰ176127 YahwehВҰ176138 has shownВҰ176137 me that he'll definitely die.вҖқ
\v 11 ThenВҰ176144 \add @Elisha\add* \add вүҲstared at him untilВҰ176149\add* \add @Haza'el\add* \add вүҲfelt embarrassed\add*, andВҰ176144 thenВҰ176144 the manВҰ176153 of GodВҰ176154 started to cry.
\p
\v 12 вҖңWhy are you crying, my masterВҰ176159?вҖқ Haza'el asked.
\p вҖңBecause I knowВҰ176164 what evil things you'll do to the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ176170\add*,вҖқ he said. вҖңYou'll \add вүҲburn down\add* their fortressesВҰ176172 and killВҰ176177 their youngВҰ176175 menВҰ176175 withВҰ176174 the swordВҰ176176. You'll smash their children's \add heads onВҰ176174 rocks\add*, and rip open \add the bellies of\add* their pregnantВҰ176180 women.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 Haza'elВҰ176184 \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңButВҰ176183 \add вүҲhow could\add* yourВҰ176187 servantВҰ176187 \add be in a position to\add* do such a major thingВҰ176191 \add вүҲwhen he's only minor, like a\add* dog \add in the palace\add*?вҖқ
\p вҖңYahwehВҰ176197 has let me see youВҰ176198 as kingВҰ176199 over AramВҰ176202.вҖқ ElishaВҰ176195 \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 14 ThenВҰ176204 he left Elisha andВҰ176204 \add вүҲwent back\add* to his masterВҰ176211 \add вүҲwho asked\add* him, вҖңWhat did Elisha tell you?вҖқ
\p And he \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖңHe told me \add вүҲthat\add* you'll certainlyВҰ176222 live.вҖқ
\v 15 \add вүҲthe very next\add* dayВҰ176226, \add @Haza'el\add* dippedВҰ176229 \add @Ben-Hadad's\add* blanket in waterВҰ176230 and held it over his face \add until\add* he diedВҰ176235, and thenВҰ176225 Haza'el \add вүҲstarted to reign\add* in his placeВҰ176238.
\s1 Yehoram reigns over Yehudah
\rem /s1 Jehoram King of Judah; Jehoram Rules in Judah; King Jehoram of Judah; Jehoram Reigns over Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 21:1-20)
\p
\v 16 In the fifth year of \add the reign of\add* Ahab'sВҰ176246 son YoramВҰ176243 as king of YisraelВҰ176248, Yehoshafat'sВҰ176249 son YehoramВҰ176253 becameВҰ176252 king of YehudahВҰ176258.
\v 17 He was thirty-two when he becameВҰ176266 kingВҰ176266 and he reignedВҰ176270 from YerushalemВҰ176271 for eightВҰ176267 yearsВҰ176268.
\v 18 He \add вүҲfollowed\add* inВҰ176274 the \add evil\add* ways of the kingsВҰ176276 of \add the northern kingdom of\add* YisraelВҰ176277, just as Ahab's \add вүҲdescendants\add* had done, because \add вүҲhe'd married\add* \add one of\add* Ahab's daughtersВҰ176283. He did what YahwehВҰ176293 \add вүҲhad said was\add* evil,
\v 19 \add вүҲbutВҰ176295\add* YahwehВҰ176298 wasn't willingВҰ176297 to destroyВҰ176299 Yehudah, for the sake of his servantВҰ176305 DavidвҖ”he'd \add вүҲpromised\add* David that \add вүҲhis descendants would always rule Yehudah\add*.
\p
\v 20 \add It was\add* \add вүҲduring\add* \add @King Yehoram's\add* \add вүҲtime that\add* EdomВҰ176320 rebelledВҰ176319 from Yehudah'sВҰ176324 \add вүҲcontrol\add*, and they \add вүҲappointed theirВҰ176326 own king\add*.
\v 21 \add SoВҰ176329\add* YehoramВҰ176330 \add took his army and\add* chariots and crossed the valley towards Zair \add in EdomВҰ176344\add*. \add вүҲThey attackedВҰ176341\add* at nightВҰ176340, \add вүҲbutВҰ176329 as the Edomite army and chariots started to\add* surroundВҰ176345 them, \add *they\add* \add had to\add* \add вүҲretreat back\add* to theirВҰ176352 tentsВҰ176352.
\v 22 \add вүҲSoВҰ176354\add* EdomВҰ176355 has been out from underВҰ176356 the control of YehudahВҰ176359 to this dayВҰ176361. ThenВҰ176354 LivnahВҰ176365 revoltedВҰ176354 atВҰ176366 the sameВҰ176367 timeВҰ176366.
\p
\v 23 \add вүҲEverything else that Yehoram said andВҰ176372 did is writtenВҰ176379 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ176385 of YehudahВҰ176386.
\v 24 ThenВҰ176388 YehoramВҰ176389 \add вүҲdied\add* and was buriedВҰ176393 withВҰ176397 his ancestorsВҰ176392 inВҰ176397 the cityВҰ176397 of DavidВҰ176398, and his son AhazyahВҰ176400 \add вүҲreplaced himВҰ176402 as kingВҰ176399\add*.
\s1 Ahazyah reigns over Yehudah
\rem /s1 Ahaziah Rules in Judah; Ahaziah Reigns over Judah; King Ahaziah of Judah; Ahaziah King of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 22:1-6)
\p
\v 25 In the twelfth year of Ahab'sВҰ176413 son Yoram'sВҰ176410 \add reign\add* over YisraelВҰ176415, Yehoram'sВҰ176420 son AhazyahВҰ176417 \add (AhaziahВҰ176417)\add* becameВҰ176416 the king of YehudahВҰ176422.
\v 26 AhazyahВҰ176429 was twenty-two when he becameВҰ176430 king, and he \add вүҲreignedВҰ176433 from YerushalemВҰ176434 for\add* one year. (His mother'sВҰ176436 name was Atalyah \add (AthaliahВҰ176437)\add*, the daughterВҰ176438 of KingВҰ176430 OmriВҰ176440 of YisraelВҰ176442.)
\v 27 He \add вүҲfollowed Ahab's customs\add* andВҰ176444 did what YahwehВҰ176451 \add вүҲhad said was\add* evilВҰ176449 like Ahab's descendants, because he was a son-in-law of \add вүҲa descendant\add* of Ahab.
\v 28 He \add вүҲjoined\add* Ahab'sВҰ176467 son Yoram to \add вүҲbattleВҰ176468 against\add* Aram'sВҰ176474 KingВҰ176472 Haza'el atВҰ176475 Ramot-Gilead, butВҰ176461 the ArameansВҰ176474 \add вүҲwoundedВҰ176477\add* Yoram.
\v 29 King Yoram returnedВҰ176483 to Yizre'el \add (Jezreel)\add* to \add вүҲrecover\add* from the wounds thatВҰ176491 ArameansВҰ176493 had \add вүҲgiven\add* him atВҰ176487 RamahВҰ176494 when he'd foughtВҰ176495 withВҰ176487 Aram'sВҰ176493 King Haza'el. \add Later,\add* King AhazyahВҰ176501 of YehudahВҰ176506 (Yehoram'sВҰ176504 son), wentВҰ176507 down to seeВҰ176508 (Ahab'sВҰ176514 son) Yoram inВҰ176487 Yizre'el because he was wounded.
\c 9
\s1 Yihu is selected to rule Yisrael
\rem /s1 Anointing of Jehu; Jehu Is Anointed King of Israel
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 1 Then the prophetВҰ176523 ElishaВҰ176522 called to one of the \add вүҲprophets-in-training\add* and told him, вҖң\add вүҲTuck your robe in\add*, takeВҰ176532 this flaskВҰ176533 of oilВҰ176534, and \add вүҲhurry\add* to RamotВҰ176538-GileadВҰ176539.
\v 2 \add вүҲWhenВҰ176541 you get\add* there, you'll see YehuВҰ176546 \add (Jehu)\add* (the son of Nimshi'sВҰ176552 son YehoshafatВҰ176549) there. \add вүҲTake himВҰ176554 into a private inner room, away from\add* his brothers,
\v 3 and pour \add some of\add* the olive oilВҰ176566 over his head and tell him that YahwehВҰ176575 saysВҰ176574 that he's anointedВҰ176576 him as kingВҰ176577 over YisraelВҰ176580. ThenВҰ176563 open the doorВҰ176582 and \add вүҲget out of there fast\add*.вҖқ
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ176587\add* the youngВҰ176588 prophetВҰ176590 wentВҰ176587 to RamotВҰ176591-GileadВҰ176592,
\v 5 andВҰ176594 \add вүҲwhen he arrivedВҰ176594, he was surprised to see\add* the army captains sittingВҰ176598 there. He said, вҖң\add вүҲI need to talk to\add* you, captain.вҖқ
\p вҖң\add вүҲWhich one of us\add*?вҖқ YehuВҰ176605 \add вүҲasked\add*.
\p вҖң\add вүҲIt's a messageВҰ176600 for\add* \em you\em*, captain,вҖқ he said.
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ176614\add* \add @Yehu\add* got up, and \add вүҲwentВҰ176615 over\add* to the houseВҰ176616 \add вүҲwhere\add* \add @the prophet\add* pouredВҰ176617 the oilВҰ176618 on his head and told him, вҖңYisrael'sВҰ176629 godВҰ176628 Yahweh saysВҰ176626 that he's anointedВҰ176630 youВҰ176630 as kingВҰ176631 over Yahweh's peopleВҰ176634вҖ”over Yisrael.
\v 7 You should attack the houseВҰ176643 of AhabВҰ176644 your masterВҰ176645 so \add @Yahweh\add* can avenge the \add вүҲmurder\add* of his servants, the prophetsВҰ176650, andВҰ176640 \add вүЎavenge\add* the \add вүҲmurder\add* of all his servants \add вүҲwho were killed by\add* Izevel \add (Jezebel)\add*.
\v 8 All of Ahab'sВҰ176663 householdВҰ176662 \add вүҲshould be killed\add*, andВҰ176659 \add @Yahweh\add* \add вүҲwon't allow any of his male descendants to live, either before or after they've left home\add*.
\v 9 \add @Yahweh\add* \add вүҲwants Ahab'sВҰ176676 descendants to be eliminated like the descendants of Nebat'sВҰ176681 son Yarave'amВҰ176678 andВҰ176682 Ahiyah'sВҰ176686 son BaashaВҰ176683 were\add*.
\v 10 The dogs will eat Izevel's \add body\add* \add вүҲwhere she dies inВҰ176693\add* Yizre'elвҖ”\add вүҲshe won't be buriedВҰ176696\add*.вҖқ ThenВҰ176688 he openedВҰ176697 the doorВҰ176698 andВҰ176688 \add вүҲrushed away\add*.
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲWhenВҰ176701\add* Yehu came back \add to the room where\add* the servantsВҰ176705 of his mastersВҰ176706 were, and \add #they\add* \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖң\add вүҲIs everything okay\add*? \add вүҲWhat did that madmanВҰ176713 want with\add* you?вҖқ
\p вҖңYou yourselves know \add вүҲthat man and the sort of stuff that he says\add*,вҖқ he said.
\p
\v 12 вҖң\add вүҲYou're lying\add*,вҖқ they insisted. вҖңTell us \add what he told you\add*.вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Well,\add* he said \add вүҲseveral things\add*,вҖқ \add @Yehu\add* \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖң\add вүҲandВҰ176727 thenВҰ176727 he told me that YahwehВҰ176741 says he's\add* anointedВҰ176742 me as kingВҰ176743 over YisraelВҰ176746.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ176748 they all spreadВҰ176752 their cloaks on the stepsВҰ176757 of the building \add вүҲfor Yehu to walk out on\add*, and they blew a trumpetВҰ176759 and \add вүҲshouted\add*, вҖңYehu is \add now\add* the kingВҰ176761!вҖқ
\s1 The killing of Yoram and Ahazyah
\rem /s1 King Joram of Israel Is Killed; Joram of Israel Killed; Jehu Kills Joram and Ahaziah
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ176764\add* YehuВҰ176765 (the son of Nimshi'sВҰ176771 son, YehoshafatВҰ176768) conspiredВҰ176764 againstВҰ176772 Yoram. Yoram was \add busy\add* \add вүҲwithВҰ176778 the army\add* guarding Ramot-Gilead from KingВҰ176786 Haza'el of AramВҰ176788.
\v 15 ThenВҰ176790 King Yoram returnedВҰ176790 to Yizre'el to heal from the woundsВҰ176797 from the ArameansВҰ176800 when he'd foughtВҰ176801 withВҰ176794 their King Haza'el.
\p \add вүҲSoВҰ176790\add* YehuВҰ176808 told \add >his men\add*, вҖңIf \add вүҲyou all want me as king, thenВҰ176790 don'tВҰ176813 let anyone leave\add* this city \add of Ramot-Gilead\add* \add вүҲinВҰ176794 case they go to Yizre'el city andВҰ176790 tell them\add* \add >our plans\add*.вҖқ
\v 16 ThenВҰ176825 YehuВҰ176826 rode to Yizre'el \add himself\add* because YoramВҰ176830 \add вүҲwas recuperating thereВҰ176832 in bed\add*, andВҰ176825 KingВҰ176834 AhazyahВҰ176833 had gone up \add north\add* from YehudahВҰ176835 to visit \add *him\add*.
\p
\v 17 The watchman was standingВҰ176843 onВҰ176847 the watchtower in Yizre'el, and he could see Yehu'sВҰ176852 party \add in the distance\add* as they \add вүҲbegan approaching\add* \add the city\add*, and he \add вүҲreported\add*, вҖңI can see a \add вүҲlarge group\add*.вҖқ
\p \add King\add* YoramВҰ176859 \add вүҲordered\add*, вҖң\add вүҲSend out a chariot and go and ask them if they're coming in peaceВҰ176865\add*.вҖқ
\v 18 \add вүҲSoВҰ176867\add* the horseВҰ176869 and chariot wentВҰ176890 \add вүҲout to meet them and called out\add*, вҖңThe kingВҰ176875 \add вүҲwants to know if you're all coming in\add* peace?вҖқ
\p \add вүҲButВҰ176867\add* YehuВҰ176878 \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖңWhat's \add вүҲthat got to do with you\add*? Turn aroundВҰ176883 \add вүҲand follow us\add*.вҖқ
\p \add вүҲMeanwhile\add* the watchmanВҰ176888 \add вүҲannounced\add*, вҖңThe messengerВҰ176892 has \add вүҲmet\add* them, butВҰ176867 he isn'tВҰ176896 returning.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲSoВҰ176900\add* \add @the king\add* sent out a secondВҰ176903 horseВҰ176902 and chariot, and he \add вүҲapproached\add* and \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖң\add вүҲThe king wants to know if you're all coming in\add* peace?вҖқ
\p \add вүҲAgain\add* YehuВҰ176913 \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңWhat's \add вүҲthat got to do with you\add*? Turn aroundВҰ176918 \add вүҲand follow us\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 ThenВҰ176923 the watchmanВҰ176924 declared, вҖңHe \add also\add* \add вүҲmet withВҰ176940 them butВҰ176923 didn'tВҰ176930 return\add*. \add вүҲThe leader is riding\add* like Nimshi'sВҰ176938 son YehuВҰ176935, because he's riding \add вүҲlike crazy\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 вҖң\add Quick,\add* get \add вүҲmy chariot readyВҰ176946!\add*вҖқ Yoram \add вүҲordered\add*. \add #They\add* harnessedВҰ176945 his chariot and King Yoram of YisraelВҰ176952 and Yehudah'sВҰ176956 King AhazyahВҰ176953 \add both\add* went outвҖ”each man inВҰ176958 his chariot. They went out to \add вүҲmeet\add* YehuВҰ176961 and they found him atВҰ176958 Navot's field (the Yizre'elite).
\v 22 WhenВҰ176967 YoramВҰ176969 saw Yehu, he \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖң\add Have you come in\add* peace, Yehu?вҖқ
\p вҖңHow \add вүҲcould there be\add* peace,вҖқ he \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖң\add вүҲwhen your motherВҰ176983 Izevel is serving idols andВҰ176967 embracing witchcraft\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 23 ThenВҰ176987 YoramВҰ176988 \add вүҲswung the chariot reigns around\add* andВҰ176987 fled, \add вүҲshouting\add* to Ahazyah, вҖң\add вүҲIt's treason\add*, Ahazyah!вҖқ
\v 24 Yehu \add вүҲgrabbed his\add* bow, and the arrowВҰ177009 struck YoramВҰ177005 betweenВҰ177006 his \add вүҲshoulderВҰ177007 blades\add* and came out from his heartВҰ177010, and he slumpedВҰ177011 down \add dead\add* inВҰ177001 his chariotВҰ177012.
\v 25 ThenВҰ177014 \add @Yehu\add* said to his third officer BidkarВҰ177017, вҖң\add вүҲPick up his body and throwВҰ177021 it out into\add* the fieldВҰ177023 of Navot, the Yizre'elite. \add вүҲI'm sure you rememberВҰ177028 how\add* you and I were ridingВҰ177032 as pairsВҰ177033 after his fatherВҰ177036 AhabВҰ177035, when YahwehВҰ177037 \add вүҲsaid this\add* against him:
\v 26 вҖҳYesterday I sawВҰ177056 Navot and his sonsВҰ177055 \add вүҲkilled here\add*, declared Yahweh, and I will repayВҰ177061 you inВҰ177063 this \add вүҲvery place\add*, declares Yahweh.вҖҷ \add вүҲSo now, throwВҰ177070 his body down here because Yahweh declared that it would happen\add*.вҖқ
