\p
\v 27 Yehudah'sВҰ177078 KingВҰ177076 Ahazyah sawВҰ177079 \add thatВҰ177098 happen\add*, andВҰ177075 he \add вүҲsped away through the garden by a\add* houseВҰ177082 \add вүҲwithВҰ177095 YehuВҰ177086 chasing afterВҰ177085 him shouting\add*, вҖң\add вүҲGet him too inВҰ177095 his chariotВҰ177094 when he starts climbing upwards to\add* GurВҰ177097 near Yibleam.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ177075 as\add* he fled towards MegiddoВҰ177103, he \add вүҲwas killed\add* thereВҰ177105,
\v 28 andВҰ177111 his servantsВҰ177109 \add вүҲtook his body\add* to YerushalemВҰ177110, \add вүҲwhere\add* they buriedВҰ177111 him in his ancestral tombВҰ177113 in the City of DavidВҰ177118.
\p
\v 29 (AhazyahВҰ177130 had becomeВҰ177129 kingВҰ177129 over YehudahВҰ177133 in the eleventh year of the reign of Ahab'sВҰ177128 son YoramВҰ177125 \add over Israel\add*.)
\s1 The killing of Queen Izevel
