\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 32 \add вүҲDuring that period\add*, YahwehВҰ177952 beganВҰ177951 to \add вүҲreduceВҰ177953 the size of Yisrael'sВҰ177954 territoryВҰ177959\add* andВҰ177955 \add Aram's King\add* Haza'el \add вүҲattacked along their border\add*
\v 33 from the YordanВҰ177964 \add вүҲriver in the east\add* \add as far south as\add* AroerВҰ177975 city on the ArnonВҰ177980 riverвҖ”\add capturing\add* \add вүҲthe GileadВҰ177971 and BashanВҰ177982 regionsВҰ177970 where the tribes of Gad, Reuben, and MenashshehВҰ177974 lived\add*.
\p
\v 34 \add вүҲEverything else that YehuВҰ177986 said andВҰ177984 did is writtenВҰ177997 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ178003 of YisraelВҰ178004.
\v 35 ThenВҰ178006 YehuВҰ178007 \add вүҲdied\add* and was buriedВҰ178011 in their ancestral tomb in ShomronВҰ178013 \add (Samaria)\add*, and his son YehoahazВҰ178015 \add вүҲreplaced him as\add* kingВҰ178014.
\v 36 YehuВҰ178022 had ruled from ShomronВҰ178030 as the king of YisraelВҰ178025 for twenty-eight years.
\c 11
\s1 Queen Ataliya's reign over Yehudah
\rem /s1 Athaliah Rules in Judah; Queen Athaliah of Judah; Athaliah Reigns over Judah; Athaliah and Joash
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 22:10вҖ“23:15)
\p
\v 1 When Ahazyah'sВҰ178035 motherВҰ178034 Atalyah saw that herВҰ178040 son \add вүҲhad been killed\add*, she went and had all \add вүҲof his descendants executed so that none of them could claim the throne\add*.
\v 2 \add вүҲHowever,\add* KingВҰ178053 Yehoram's daughterВҰ178051 Yehosheva tookВҰ178049 YoashВҰ178060, the son of her sisterВҰ178056 AhazyahВҰ178057, and hid him inВҰ178076 the bedroom along withВҰ178076 his wet-nurse. \add вүҲAlthough he was onВҰ178076 the list of\add* the king's sonsВҰ178067 to be executed, they hid him from Atalyah, and \add so\add* he wasn't killed.
\v 3 ThenВҰ178085 he was able to stay hidden with her in the \add вүҲtemple\add* for the sixВҰ178090 yearsВҰ178091 while AtalyahВҰ178088 ruled \add @Yehudah\add*.
\rem /s1 Revolt against Athaliah; Jehoiada Anoints the Child Joash
\p
\v 4 In the seventhВҰ178100 yearВҰ178099, Yehoyada \add the priest\add* sentВҰ178101 for the \add вүҲofficers over the royal bodyguards and the palace bodyguards to come to him inside Yahweh's temple\add*. \add вүҲHe made them agree to take an oath of\add* \add secrecy and loyalty\add* \add вүҲinВҰ178099 the temple, then he let them\add* see the king'sВҰ178130 son.
\v 5 ThenВҰ178132 he commandedВҰ178132 them, вҖңThis is \add вүҲwhat you all need to\add* do: On the Rest Day, one thirdВҰ178138 of you \add вүҲmust go andВҰ178132 guardВҰ178142 the king'sВҰ178145 palace\add*.
\v 6 The \add second\add* third \add вүҲmust guardВҰ178153\add* the Sur gate, and \add вүҲthe remainder must stay behindВҰ178152 the others roaming back and forth\add*,
\v 7 and the twoВҰ178161 \add вүҲoff-duty groups must guardВҰ178167 the temple and protect\add* the \add young\add* kingВҰ178176.
\v 8 You'll surroundВҰ178178 the kingвҖ”each man \add вүҲholding his weaponsВҰ178184 atВҰ178196 the ready right aroundВҰ178182 him\add*вҖ”killing any person who approaches your ranksВҰ178189, andВҰ178178 \add вүҲaccompanying\add* the king when he goes out or comes inВҰ178196.
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ178198 the officers over the royal bodyguards\add* did \add вүҲeverything\add* that the priest Yehoyada had commandedВҰ178199. \add вүҲBoth the on-duty andВҰ178198 the off-duty menВҰ178212 fulfilled their roles under Yehoyada's direction that Rest Day\add*.
\v 10 TheВҰ178240 priestВҰ178225 had \add taken\add* the spearsВҰ178231 and the shieldsВҰ178234 out of the temple thatВҰ178235 had belonged to KingВҰ178236 DavidВҰ178237 and given them to the \add вүҲofficers over the royal bodyguards\add*,
\v 11 and \add вүҲthey all stoodВҰ178242 in position\add*, each manВҰ178244 holding his weaponsВҰ178246 ready in his handВҰ178247, \add вүҲright around the palace and the templeВҰ178257\add* and the altarВҰ178256, and the kingВҰ178260.
\v 12 Then \add @the priest\add* broughtВҰ178263 \add young\add* Yoash out and put the crownВҰ178273 on his head. He \add вүҲhanded him the official scroll\add*, and they anointedВҰ178279 him and made him king. Then they \add вүҲclappedВҰ178280 their hands and shouted\add*, вҖң\add вүҲLong\add* live the king!вҖқ
\rem /s1 Death of Athaliah; The Death of Athaliah
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲWhen\add* Atalyah heardВҰ178288 the soundВҰ178292 of the people \add вүҲand the guardsВҰ178293\add*, she came to the people \add gathered\add* at Yahweh's temple
\v 14 and \add вүҲwas stunned to see\add* the \add young, new\add* king standingВҰ178305 near the pillarВҰ178308 as was the customВҰ178309, withВҰ178321 the captainsВҰ178310 and the trumpeters near the king, and all the peopleВҰ178317 of the land rejoicing and \add вүҲsounding\add* trumpets. ThenВҰ178302 Atalyah tore herВҰ178326 clothesВҰ178326 and \add вүҲshouted\add* out, вҖңTreachery! Treason!вҖқ
\v 15 Then Yehoyada the priest commandedВҰ178332 the \add вүҲofficials over the bodyguards and the army officersВҰ178341\add*, вҖңBring her out away from \add вүҲthese public buildings\add*. Don't kill her inВҰ178354 the temple, butВҰ178332 kill anyone who \add вүҲtries to rescue\add* her.
\v 16 \add вүҲSoВҰ178364\add* they \add вүҲgrabbed her by each arm and took her out through the entranceВҰ178370 for the horsesВҰ178371 to the palace\add*, and she was \add вүҲexecuted\add* thereВҰ178375.
\s1 Yehoyada's reforms
\rem /s1 Jehoiada's Reforms; Jehoiada's Religious Reforms
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 23:16-21)
\p
\v 17 Then Yehoyada \add вүҲled the making of an agreement\add* between Yahweh and the king and the people, \add вүҲfor the people to serve\add* Yahweh, and \add also\add* between the king and between the people.
\v 18 ThenВҰ178397 peopleВҰ178400 \add вүҲfrom all over the country wentВҰ178397 to the temple\add* of Baal and brokeВҰ178413 down the altars. They smashed his imagesВҰ178412 \add вүҲto pieces\add* and killedВҰ178419 MattanВҰ178416 the priest of the Baal \add вүҲin frontВҰ178420 of the\add* altars. \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* \add Yehoyada\add* the priest \add вүҲplaced guards over Yahweh's temple\add*.
\v 19 ThenВҰ178430 he \add вүҲorganised the officers over the royal guard and the palace guards\add* to bring the king down from the \add вүҲtempleВҰ178451\add* of YahwehВҰ178452, and along with all the peopleВҰ178445, they entered the \add вүҲpalace via the gateВҰ178456 usually used by the king's bodyguards\add*, and he sat on the throneВҰ178464.
\v 20 All the peopleВҰ178470 celebrated andВҰ178467 the cityВҰ178473 was quiet \add вүҲbecause Atalyah had been put to deathВҰ178478 withВҰ178479 the swordВҰ178479 atВҰ178479 the palace\add*.
\p
\v 21 Yoash was \add only\add* seven when he became king \add of Yehudah\add*.
\c 12
\s1 Yoash reigns over Yehudah
\rem /s1 King Joash of Judah; The Temple Repaired; Joash Repairs the Temple
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 23:16-23)
\rem /r (2 Chronicles 24.1-16)
\p
\v 1 Yoash became king in Yerushalem in the seventhВҰ178488 year of Yehu's \add reign over Israel\add*. (His mother was Tsivyah from Be'er-Sheva.) He reigned for forty yearsВҰ178489
\v 2 and all his life, \add *he\add* did \add вүҲwhat Yahweh had said was correct\add* because he was instructed by Yehoyada the priest.
\v 3 \add вүҲHowever,\add* they didn't remove the \add вүҲhilltop shrines\add* where the people continued sacrificing andВҰ178512 burning incense.
\p
\v 4 Then Yoash told the priests, вҖң\add вүҲYou all must collect\add* all the \add вүҲmoney that's donated to Yahweh's temple, whether it's the money they're required to pay or the money that they themselves decide to give as sacred offeringsВҰ178534 to buy things for the temple\add*.
\v 5 \add вүҲEach priestВҰ178542 must bringВҰ178567 what they've collected from their acquaintances, and use it to make repairs wherever they find thatВҰ178546 there's been damage to the temple\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲHowever,\add* \add when\add* the priestsВҰ178574 \add still\add* hadn't repairedВҰ178579 the damaged portions by the twenty-third year of Yoash's reign,
\v 7 \add *he\add* sent for Yehoyada the priest and the \add other\add* priestsВҰ178603, and \add вүҲquestioned\add* them, вҖңWhy aren'tВҰ178600 you all strengthening the \add вүҲtempleВҰ178607 where it was damaged\add*? \add вүҲFrom now on, you all won'tВҰ178600 take any money from acquaintances, butВҰ178593 you'll give it directly for repairingВҰ178602 the damage\add*.вҖқ
\v 8 \add вүҲSo\add* the priestsВҰ178615 agreed to not accept \add вүҲmoneyВҰ178630\add* from the people, and \add вүҲthat they themselves wouldn't be the ones to repairВҰ178620 the templeВҰ178636\add*.
\p
\v 9 Then Yehoyada the priest took a \add wooden\add* chest and he made a hole in \add вүҲthe top\add*, and he \add вүҲplaced\add* it at the right of the altar. When a person came into the \add вүҲtemple\add*, the priestsВҰ178641 guarding the \add вүҲentrance\add* would \add вүҲplace any donated moneyВҰ178645 into the chest\add*.
\v 10 \add вүҲWhenever they noticed the chestВҰ178659 getting full\add*, the king's secretary and the high priestВҰ178658 \add вүҲwould go and count the moneyВҰ178685 as they bagged it up\add*.
\v 11 TheyВҰ178712 \add вүҲused the funds to pay the supervisors and inspectors and the tradesmen doing the repair work\add*: carpenters and builders,
\v 12 and \add вүҲthe masons and stone-cutters\add*. \add вүҲThey also paid for the timber and stones, and everything else that was needed for the temple repairs\add*.
\v 13 HoweverВҰ178752, \add вүҲthey didn't use the donated silver coins that were brought to the temple to make silver bowls, snuffers, basins, or trumpets, or for any other gold or silver instruments within the temple\add*,
\v 14 because they \add вүҲpassed on the donations\add* to the people doing the work, andВҰ178777 \add вүҲin this way Yahweh's residence got repaired\add*.
\v 15 TheyВҰ178800 didn't audit the men who \add вүҲtook the silver coins to the workers because the whole system was based on trust\add*.
\v 16 TheВҰ178810 silver \add coins that came as part\add* of the guilt offering and the sin offerings were not \add вүҲused for temple repairs\add*вҖ”they belonged to the priests.
\rem /s1 Hazael Threatens Jerusalem; The End of Joash's Reign
\p
\v 17 Then Aram's King Haza'el \add вүҲattacked\add* Gat andВҰ178827 captured itВҰ178830, \add вүҲafter which\add* \add *he\add* \add вүҲdecided to attack Yerushalem\add*.
\v 18 Yehudah's King Yoash took all the sacred things that his ancestors Yehoshafat and Yehoram and Ahazyah, the \add previous\add* kings of Yehudah, had consecrated and his sacred things, and all of the gold that was found in Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add* treasuries and in the king's \add вүҲpalace\add*, and he sent them to Aram'sВҰ178842 King Haza'el \add вүҲwho then cancelled his planned attack on\add* YerushalemВҰ178854.
\rem /s1 Death of Joash
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲEverything else thatВҰ178866 Yoash said and did is written inВҰ178883 the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ178873 of YehudahВҰ178874.
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲHowever,\add* his servants got \add вүҲtogether and planned his assassination\add*, and theyВҰ178907 \add вүҲambushed\add* YoashВҰ178900 in Bet-Millo on the \add road\add* going down to Silla.
\v 21 His servantsВҰ178919 Yozavad (Shimeat's son) and Yehozabad (Shomer's son) struck him and he died, and theyВҰ178920 buried him \add вүҲin his ancestral tomb\add* in the city of David, and his son Amatsyah \add вүҲreplaced him as\add* king.
\c 13
\s1 Yehoahaz reigns over Yisrael
\rem /s1 Jehoahaz Reigns over Israel; Jehoahaz King of Israel; Jehoahaz Rules in Israel; King Jehoahaz of Israel
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 1 In the twenty-third year of Ahazyah'sВҰ178965 son YoashВҰ178962 \add reigning\add* over YehudahВҰ178967, Yehu'sВҰ178972 son YehoahazВҰ178969 becameВҰ178968 king over YisraelВҰ178975 \add вүҲand reigned seventeenВҰ178977 years from\add* ShomronВҰ178976 \add (Samaria)\add*.
\v 2 He did what YahwehВҰ178984 \add вүҲhad said was\add* evilВҰ178982 andВҰ178981 he \add вүҲimitated the customs\add* of Nebat'sВҰ178991 son Yarave'amВҰ178988 who had causedВҰ178994 YisraelВҰ178997 to sinВҰ178994вҖ”\add @Yehoahaz\add* didn'tВҰ178998 \add вүҲend them\add*.
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ179003\add* YahwehВҰ179006 \add вүҲgot angry withВҰ179007\add* YisraelВҰ179007 and he \add вүҲallowed them to be defeated by Aram'sВҰ179014 KingВҰ179012 Haza'el and his son BenВҰ179018-Hadad throughout Yehoahaz's reign\add*.
\v 4 ThenВҰ179026 YehoahazВҰ179027 \add вүҲprayed to Yahweh for help\add*, andВҰ179026 Yahweh listenedВҰ179032 to him because he sawВҰ179036 \add вүҲhow much YisraelВҰ179040 was being oppressedВҰ179039 by the Aramean\add* kingВҰ179045.
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ179048\add* YahwehВҰ179049 \add вүҲsent a saviour\add* to YisraelВҰ179050, and they \add вүҲwere able to stand up against the ArameansВҰ179056\add*, and \add only thenВҰ179048 were\add* the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ179060 able to live peacefully again from day to day\add*.
\v 6 \add вүҲDespite thatВҰ179073\add*, theyВҰ179068 didn'tВҰ179066 \add вүҲstop imitating the sinsВҰ179069 of Yarave'am's family\add* who causedВҰ179075 YisraelВҰ179079 to sinВҰ179075вҖ”\add no,\add* \add @Yehoahaz\add* \add вүҲkept doing them\add*, andВҰ179082 even the Asherah pole \add remainedВҰ179084\add* standing inВҰ179080 ShomronВҰ179085.
\p
\v 7 The Aramean kingВҰ179104 had \add вүҲthoroughly destroyedВҰ179103\add* \add much of Yisrael's forces\add* \add only\add* leaving fiftyВҰ179095 horsemenВҰ179096, ten chariotsВҰ179098, and ten thousandВҰ179100 footВҰ179101 soldiersВҰ179101 for YehoahazВҰ179090.
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲEverything else\add* that YehoahazВҰ179112 said andВҰ179110 did, \add вүҲincluding his great achievements\add*, is writtenВҰ179121 in the book of the \add вүҲevents\add* of the kingsВҰ179127 of YisraelВҰ179128.
\v 9 ThenВҰ179130 YehoahazВҰ179131 \add вүҲdied\add* and was buriedВҰ179135 inВҰ179136 ShomronВҰ179136, and his son YehoashВҰ179138 \add вүҲreplaced himВҰ179135 as\add* kingВҰ179137.
\s1 Yehoash reigns over Yisrael
\rem /s1 King Jehoash of Israel; Jehoash King of Israel; Jehoash Rules in Israel; Jehoash Reigns over Israel
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 10 In the thirty-seventh year of KingВҰ179148 YoashВҰ179147 \add reigning\add* over YehudahВҰ179149, Yehoahaz'sВҰ179154 son YehoashВҰ179151 becameВҰ179150 king over YisraelВҰ179157 and \add reigned\add* sixteen years from ShomronВҰ179158 \add (Samaria)\add*.
\v 11 He did what YahwehВҰ179166 \add вүҲhad said was\add* evilВҰ179164 andВҰ179163 he \add вүҲimitated the customs\add* of Nebat'sВҰ179175 son Yarave'amВҰ179172 who had causedВҰ179178 YisraelВҰ179181 to sinВҰ179178вҖ”\add @Yehoash\add* didn'tВҰ179167 \add вүҲend them\add*.
\v 12 \add вүҲEverything else\add* thatВҰ179193 Yehoash said andВҰ179185 did, \add вүҲincluding his great achievements\add* fighting along with Yehudah'sВҰ179199 KingВҰ179197 Amatsyah, is writtenВҰ179203 in the book of the \add вүҲevents\add* of the kingsВҰ179209 of YisraelВҰ179210.
\v 13 ThenВҰ179212 Yehoash \add вүҲdied\add* and was buriedВҰ179222 inВҰ179224 ShomronВҰ179224 withВҰ179224 the \add former\add* kingsВҰ179226 of YisraelВҰ179227, and \add his son\add* Yarave'am \add вүҲreplaced him\add* onВҰ179224 the throneВҰ179221.
\s1 Elisha's death
\rem /s1 Elisha's Final Prophecy; The Death of Elisha; Death of Elisha
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 14 \add вүҲMeanwhile\add* Elisha \add вүҲhad been sick and heading for hisВҰ179234 last days\add*, \add вүҲso\add* Yisrael's king Yehoash had been \add вүҲto see\add* him, and \add вүҲcried as he stood in front of him\add* and said, вҖңMy father, my father, Yisrael's chariotВҰ179252 and its horsemenВҰ179254!вҖқ\f + \fr 13:14 \ft This was the same as what Elisha had said when Eliyah had been taken to heaven. See 2:12.\f*
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ179256 ElishaВҰ179258 had told him, вҖңBring a bow andВҰ179256 arrows.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ179256 he'd brought\add* \add *them\add*,
\v 16 and he'd told Yisrael'sВҰ179270 king, вҖң\add вүҲGrab the bow ready to draw\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ179267 he did that\add*, and thenВҰ179267 ElishaВҰ179279 put his hands over the king'sВҰ179284 hands.
\v 17 ThenВҰ179286 he said, вҖңOpen that windowВҰ179288 facing east.вҖқ \add @The king\add* openedВҰ179290 it and Elisha said, вҖңShoot.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ179286\add* he shot \add >the arrow\add* and \add @Elisha\add* said, вҖң\add That's\add* an arrow of victory for YahwehВҰ179299 and an arrow of victory against Aram. You will \add вүҲthoroughly defeat\add* Aram atВҰ179302 AfekВҰ179307.вҖқ
\v 18 ThenВҰ179312 he \add вүҲcontinuedВҰ179312\add*, вҖңTake \add the rest of\add* the arrowsВҰ179314.вҖқ Yisrael'sВҰ179319 kingВҰ179317 tookВҰ179315 \add >them\add*, andВҰ179312 \add @Elisha\add* told him, вҖңStrike the ground \add with them\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ179312\add* he bangedВҰ179323 \add the arrows on the ground\add* threeВҰ179324 timesВҰ179326.
\v 19 \add вүҲButВҰ179329\add* the manВҰ179331 of GodВҰ179332 was angryВҰ179329 with him, andВҰ179329 said, вҖң\add вүҲYouВҰ179354 should have bashed them\add* five or six times, thenВҰ179329 you would have bashed AramВҰ179344 up \add вүҲcompletely\add*, \add вүҲbutВҰ179329\add* now you'll defeatВҰ179341 \add *them\add* threeВҰ179349 times.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 Then ElishaВҰ179358 diedВҰ179357 and was buriedВҰ179359.
\p \add вүҲEvery yearВҰ179365 in the spring\add*, bandsВҰ179360 of Moabites \add вүҲwould make raids on\add* Yisrael,
\v 21 and once there was \add a group of IsraelisВҰ179387\add* buryingВҰ179370 a man. WhenВҰ179367 they saw the raiding party, they \add quickly\add* threwВҰ179377 \add вүҲthe body\add* into Elisha'sВҰ179382 tomb, and when \add *it\add* touchedВҰ179384 his bonesВҰ179386, the man \add вүҲcame back to life and stood up\add*.
\s1 War between Yisrael and Aram/Syria
\rem /s1 Israel Recaptures Cities from Aram; War between Israel and Syria
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 22 Aram'sВҰ179397 KingВҰ179396 Haza'elВҰ179395 oppressedВҰ179398 YisraelВҰ179401 all \add вүҲthrough Yehoahaz'sВҰ179404 reign\add*,
\v 23 \add вүҲbutВҰ179406\add* YahwehВҰ179407 showed favour \add вүҲto the Israelis\add* and \add вүҲfelt compassionateВҰ179409 towardsВҰ179411\add* them. \add вүҲBecause of his agreement\add* with AbrahamВҰ179416, Yitshak, and YacobВҰ179418, he \add вүҲdidn'tВҰ179419 want\add* to destroyВҰ179421 them, and he \add вүҲhasn't tossed them out even to this day\add*.
\p
\v 24 \add вүҲWhenВҰ179432\add* Aram'sВҰ179436 KingВҰ179434 Haza'elВҰ179433 died, his son BenВҰ179438-HadadВҰ179440 \add вүҲreplaced him as\add* king.
\v 25 ThenВҰ179444 Yehoahaz's son YehoashВҰ179445 \add вүҲattacked Aram\add* threeВҰ179466 timesВҰ179467, andВҰ179444 he took \add back\add* the cities from Haza'el's son BenВҰ179456-Hadad thatВҰ179460 had been takenВҰ179461 in the war in his fatherВҰ179464 Yehoahaz's time.
\c 14
\s1 Amatsyah reigns over Yehudah
\rem /s1 King Amaziah of Judah; Amaziah Rules in Judah; Amaziah Reigns over Judah; Amaziah King of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 25:1-24)
\p
\v 1 In the second year of \add вүҲthe reign of\add* Yehoahaz'sВҰ179482 son YehoashВҰ179479 over YisraelВҰ179484, Amatsyah \add вүҲreplaced\add* his father YoashВҰ179489 as king of YehudahВҰ179491.
\v 2 He was twenty-five when he becameВҰ179499 kingВҰ179499, and he \add вүҲreignedВҰ179503 from\add* Yerushalem for twenty-nine years. (His mother'sВҰ179506 nameВҰ179505 was YehoaddanВҰ179507 from Yerushalem.)
\v 3 He did what YahwehВҰ179516 \add вүҲhad said was correct behaviour\add*, \add вүҲalthough not as thoroughly as\add* his ancestor DavidВҰ179519вҖ”\add вүҲhis behaviour was more like that of\add* his father YoashВҰ179525.
\v 4 \add вүҲHowever,\add* the \add вүҲhilltop shrines\add* weren't removedВҰ179533вҖ”peopleВҰ179535 were stillВҰ179534 sacrificingВҰ179536 andВҰ179537 burning incense atВҰ179538 \add *them\add*.
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲOnce he was firmly established as kingВҰ179552\add*, \add @Amatsyah\add* had the servantsВҰ179548 executed who had assassinated his fatherВҰ179553 Yoash,\x + \xo 14:5 \xt 12:20-21.\x*
\v 6 \add вүҲbutВҰ179555\add* he didn'tВҰ179559 have their sons executed, because inВҰ179562 the scroll where MoshehВҰ179565 had writtenВҰ179561 the laws, YahwehВҰ179569 had commandedВҰ179568, вҖңFathers shouldn'tВҰ179559 be executed for what their sons do, nor should sons be executed for the crimes of their ancestorsвҖ”rather an individual should only be executed for their own crime.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲHe led the victory over\add* tenВҰ179603 thousandВҰ179604 Edomites in the Salt ValleyВҰ179599, seizing SelaВҰ179608 in the battleВҰ179609 and renaming it as Yokthe'el which it's still calledВҰ179610 today.
\p
\v 8 Then Amatsyah sentВҰ179621 messengersВҰ179623 to Yisrael'sВҰ179634 KingВҰ179633 YehoashВҰ179626 (the son of YehoahazВҰ179629, the son of YehuВҰ179632) \add вүҲchallenging\add*, вҖңCome on, let's \add вүҲhave it out with each other\add*.вҖқ
\v 9 \add вүҲBut\add* King YehoashВҰ179641 \add вүҲreplied\add* to Yehudah'sВҰ179650 King Amatsyah, вҖңThe thistle that was in the Lebanon \add forest\add* sent to the cedarВҰ179658 that was in the Lebanon, saying, вҖҳGive your daughterВҰ179666 to my son as a wife.вҖҷ \add вүҲBut\add* a \add вүҲwild\add* animalВҰ179670 that was in the Lebanon passedВҰ179669 by andВҰ179640 it trampledВҰ179674 the thistle.
\v 10 \add вүҲIt's true that you won a battle with EdomВҰ179683 and you're feeling encouraged\add*. \add вүҲAccept that honourВҰ179686\add*, butВҰ179684 stayВҰ179687 \add вүҲhomeВҰ179688\add* \add now\add*. Why would you stir up troubleВҰ179691 \add вүҲonly to fall again\add*вҖ”you and \add all\add* Yehudah with you?вҖқ
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲButВҰ179697\add* Amatsyah wouldn't listenВҰ179699 \add вүҲso\add* \add the armies of\add* Yisrael'sВҰ179705 King YehoashВҰ179702 andВҰ179697 Yehudah'sВҰ179712 King Amatsyah \add вүҲfaced each other\add* in Yehudah at Beyt-Shemesh.
\v 12 \add вүҲHowever,\add* YehudahВҰ179719 was \add вүҲovercome\add* by YisraelВҰ179721, andВҰ179722 \add вүҲits warriors\add* had to flee \add вүҲhome\add* \add from the battlefield\add*.
\v 13 \add вүҲSoВҰ179727\add* Yisrael'sВҰ179742 King Yehoash captured Yehudah'sВҰ179731 King Amatsyah (the son of Yehoash, the son of AhazyahВҰ179737) inВҰ179749 Beyt-Shemesh. ThenВҰ179727 he wentВҰ179745 to YerushalemВҰ179747, andВҰ179727 he brokeВҰ179748 down the \add *city\add* wall from the EfrayimВҰ179752 Gate up to the Corner GateвҖ”\add вүҲalmost two hundredВҰ179758 metres of it\add*.
\v 14 He took all the goldВҰ179766 and silverВҰ179768, and all the equipment that was foundВҰ179773 in Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add* and in the \add вүҲpalace\add* treasuriesВҰ179777. ThenВҰ179761 \add вүҲtaking some hostagesВҰ179782 as well\add*, he returnedВҰ179783 to ShomronВҰ179784 \add (Samaria)\add*.
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲEverything else\add* thatВҰ179789 YehoashВҰ179788 said andВҰ179786 did, \add вүҲincluding his battleВҰ179793 with\add* Yehudah'sВҰ179798 KingВҰ179796 Amatsyah, is writtenВҰ179802 in the book of the \add вүҲevents\add* of the kingsВҰ179808 of YisraelВҰ179809.
\v 16 ThenВҰ179811 YehoashВҰ179812 \add вүҲdied\add* and was buriedВҰ179816 inВҰ179817 ShomronВҰ179817 withВҰ179817 the \add former\add* kingsВҰ179819 of YisraelВҰ179820, and his son Yarave'amВҰ179822 \add вүҲreplaced him as\add* king.
\s1 The death of Yehudah's King Amatsyah
\rem /s1 The Death of King Amaziah of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 25:25-28)
\p
\v 17 Yehudah'sВҰ179833 King Amatsyah (Yoash'sВҰ179831 son) livedВҰ179827 \add another\add* fifteen years afterВҰ179834 the deathВҰ179835 of Yisrael'sВҰ179841 King YehoashВҰ179836 (Yehoahaz'sВҰ179839 son).
\v 18 \add вүҲEverything else\add* that Amatsyah said is writtenВҰ179852 in the book of the \add вүҲevents\add* of the kingsВҰ179858 of YehudahВҰ179859.
\p
\v 19 \add Some people\add* in YerushalemВҰ179864 \add вүҲhad plotted to assassinate\add* him, \add вүҲbutВҰ179861\add* he fled to Lakish. \add вүҲHowever,\add* they followed him \add *there\add* andВҰ179861 killedВҰ179870 him \add вүҲin the city\add*.
\v 20 \add вүҲHis body was carried back\add* onВҰ179879 horsesВҰ179877, andВҰ179878 he was buriedВҰ179878 \add вүҲin his ancestral tomb\add* in YerushalemВҰ179879 in the cityВҰ179883 of DavidВҰ179884.
\v 21 ThenВҰ179886 all the peopleВҰ179889 of YehudahВҰ179890 tookВҰ179886 sixteen year old AzaryahВҰ179893 andВҰ179886 made him kingВҰ179900 \add вүҲto replace\add* his \add late\add* fatherВҰ179903 AmatsyahВҰ179904.
\v 22 \add @Azaryah\add* builtВҰ179907 up EylatВҰ179908 and he \add вүҲreestablished it as part of\add* YehudahВҰ179912 \add вүҲbefore he died\add*.
\s1 Yarave'am II reigns over Yisrael
\rem /s1 Jeroboam II Rules in Israel; Jeroboam II Reigns over Israel; King Jeroboam II of Israel; Jeroboam II King of Israel
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 23 In the fifteenth year of Yoash'sВҰ179930 son KingВҰ179931 Amatsyah's \add reign\add* over YehudahВҰ179932, Yehoash's son Yarave'am becameВҰ179933 king of YisraelВҰ179940 \add and reigned from\add* ShomronВҰ179941 \add (Samaria)\add* for forty-one years.
\v 24 He did what YahwehВҰ179949 \add вүҲhad said was\add* evilВҰ179947вҖ”he \add вүҲimitated the customs\add* of Nebat'sВҰ179958 son Yarave'amВҰ179955 who'd causedВҰ179960 YisraelВҰ179963 to sinВҰ179960.
\v 25 \add @Yarave'am\add* restoredВҰ179966 Yisrael's borderВҰ179969 from Lebo-HamatВҰ179972 \add through\add* to the Sea of the Desert, as Yisrael's godВҰ179979 YahwehВҰ179978 had foretold via his servantВҰ179985 YonahВҰ179986 \add (Jonah)\add*вҖ”the son of the prophetВҰ179990 AmittaiВҰ179989 from Gat-Hefer.
\v 26 \add ThatВҰ180011 was\add* because YahwehВҰ179998 had seen \add вүҲhow YisraelВҰ180002 had suffered badly and had been unable to control their own destinies\add*, and that \add вүҲno other country would help\add* \add *them\add*.
\v 27 \add вүҲButВҰ180013\add* YahwehВҰ180016 had \add вүҲsaid that he wouldn't allow YisraelВҰ180021 to be destroyed, so he'd used Yehoash's son Yarave'am to save\add* them.
\p
\v 28 \add вүҲEverything else\add* thatВҰ180039 Yarave'am said and did, \add вүҲincluding\add* how he fought and restoredВҰ180043 DamascusВҰ180046 and HamatВҰ180049 to Yisrael, is writtenВҰ180055 inВҰ180051 the book of the \add вүҲevents\add* of the kingsВҰ180061 of Yisrael.
\v 29 ThenВҰ180064 Yarave'am \add died and \add* was buried with the \add former\add* kingsВҰ180070 of YisraelВҰ180071, and his son Zekaryah \add вүҲreplaced him as\add* kingВҰ180072.
\c 15
\s1 Azaryah/Uzziyah reigns over Yehudah
\rem /s1 King Uzziah of Judah; Azariah Reigns over Judah; Azariah King of Judah; Uzziah Rules in Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 26:1-23)
\p
\v 1 In the twenty-seventh year of KingВҰ180083 Yarave'am's \add reign\add* over YisraelВҰ180084, Amatsyah's son Azaryah\f + \fr 15:1 \ft Azaryah was also known as Uzziyah, especially from v13 onwards.\f* becameВҰ180085 king of YehudahВҰ180091.
\v 2 He was sixteen when he becameВҰ180099 kingВҰ180099, and he reignedВҰ180103 from Yerushalem for fifty-two years. (His mother'sВҰ180106 nameВҰ180105 was Jeholyah from Yerushalem.)
\v 3 He did what YahwehВҰ180113 \add вүҲhad said was correct behaviour\add* like his fatherВҰ180119 Amatsyah had done,
\v 4 although the \add вүҲhilltop shrines\add* weren't removedВҰ180125вҖ”the peopleВҰ180127 continued to sacrificeВҰ180128 atВҰ180130 them andВҰ180129 burn incenseВҰ180129.
\v 5 YahwehВҰ180133 \add вүҲcaused Azaryah to become a leper\add* and he \add вүҲhad to live separatelyВҰ180145 from others for the rest of his life, so\add* \add *his\add* son Yotam \add вүҲran the palace\add* \add and\add* \add вүҲdealt with the people'sВҰ180156 problems\add*.
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲEverything else that AzaryahВҰ180161 said andВҰ180162 did is writtenВҰ180169 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ180175 of YehudahВҰ180176.
\v 7 AzaryahВҰ180179 \add вүҲdied\add* and was buriedВҰ180183 in \add вүҲthe ancestral tomb\add* in the cityВҰ180188 of DavidВҰ180189, and his son YotamВҰ180191 \add вүҲreplaced him as\add* kingВҰ180190.\x + \xo 15:7: \xt Isa 6:1.\x*
\s1 Zekaryah reigns over Yisrael
\rem /s1 Zechariah Reigns over Israel; King Zechariah of Israel; Zechariah Rules in Israel; Zechariah King of Israel
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 8 In the thirty-eighth year of KingВҰ180201 Azaryah'sВҰ180200 \add reign\add* over YehudahВҰ180202, Yarave'am's son Zekaryah becameВҰ180203 king over YisraelВҰ180210 \add and ruled for\add* six monthsВҰ180213 from ShomronВҰ180211 \add (Samaria)\add*.
\v 9 He did what YahwehВҰ180218 \add вүҲhad said was\add* evilВҰ180216, just as his ancestorsВҰ180221 had doneвҖ”he didn'tВҰ180222 \add вүҲavoid the kinds of behaviour\add* thatВҰ180229 had been done by Nebat'sВҰ180228 son Yarave'amВҰ180225 who had causedВҰ180230 YisraelВҰ180233 to sinВҰ180230.
\v 10 ThenВҰ180235 Yavesh'sВҰ180240 son ShallumВҰ180237 \add вүҲplotted to assassinate\add* him, and he \add вүҲattacked\add* him in frontВҰ180242 of the peopleВҰ180244 and killedВҰ180245 him, and he \add вүҲreplaced him as\add* king.
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲEverything else that Zekaryah said andВҰ180249 did is writtenВҰ180253 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ180259 of YisraelВҰ180260.
\p
\v 12 \add Previously\add* YahwehВҰ180265 had told \add King\add* YehuВҰ180270 that his descendantsВҰ180272 would sitВҰ180274 on the throneВҰ180278 for four generationsВҰ180273, andВҰ180280 that had come \add вүҲtrue\add*.\x + \xo 15:12: \xt 2Ki 10:30.\x*
\s1 Shallum reigns over Yisrael
\rem /s1 Shallum Reigns over Israel; Shallum King of Israel; Shallum Rules in Israel; King Shallum of Israel
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 13 Yavesh's son ShallumВҰ180285 becameВҰ180289 king inВҰ180301 the thirty-ninth year of KingВҰ180289 Azaryah's \add reign\add* over YehudahВҰ180296, \add вүҲbutВҰ180292\add* he \add only\add* reigned from ShomronВҰ180301 for one monthВҰ180298.
\v 14 ThenВҰ180303 Gadi'sВҰ180307 son MenahemВҰ180304 came to Shomron from Tirtsah, and he \add вүҲattacked\add* Yabesh'sВҰ180317 son ShallumВҰ180314 \add there\add* inВҰ180318 Shomron and killedВҰ180319 him, \add вүҲreplacing him as\add* kingВҰ180320.
\v 15 \add вүҲEverything else\add* thatВҰ180327 ShallumВҰ180325 said, \add вүҲincluding his assassination plot\add*, is writtenВҰ180330 in the book of the \add вүҲevents\add* of the kingsВҰ180336 of YisraelВҰ180337.
\rem /s1 Menahem Rules in Israel
\v 16 \add вүҲAt that time,\add* MenahemВҰ180343 \add вүҲattackedВҰ180341\add* TifsahВҰ180346 and \add вүҲeveryone inВҰ180353\add* \add the city\add*, and its borders from Tirtsah, because \add вүҲthey wouldn't open their gates\add*. Then he rippedВҰ180366 open \add >the bellies\add* of all the pregnantВҰ180365 women \add there\add*.
\s1 Menahem's reign over Yisrael
\rem /s1 Menahem King of Israel; Menahem Reigns over Israel; King Menahem of Israel
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 17 In the thirty-ninth year of KingВҰ180374 Azaryah'sВҰ180373 \add reign\add* over YehudahВҰ180375, Gadi'sВҰ180380 son MenahemВҰ180377 becameВҰ180376 king over YisraelВҰ180383 \add and he reigned\add* from ShomronВҰ180386 \add (Samaria)\add* for ten yearsВҰ180385.
\v 18 He did what YahwehВҰ180391 \add вүҲhad said was\add* evilВҰ180389вҖ”he didn'tВҰ180392 \add вүҲavoid the kinds of behaviour\add* thatВҰ180400 had been done by Nebat'sВҰ180399 son Yarave'amВҰ180396 who had causedВҰ180402 YisraelВҰ180405 to sinВҰ180402.
\p During his reign,
\v 19 KingВҰ180412 Pul \add (Tiglat-Pileser)\add* of AssyriaВҰ180414 \add вүҲattacked Israel\add*, and Menahem gaveВҰ180418 Pul over thirty tonnes of silverВҰ180424, so \add вүҲhe\add* would \add вүҲsupport Menahem'sВҰ180419 reign\add*.
\v 20 (MenahemВҰ180433 \add вүҲhad taxed all the wealthyВҰ180444 families across YisraelВҰ180439вҖ”fiftyВҰ180448 silverВҰ180450 coins per adult male\add*.) \add вүҲAs a result,\add* the Assyrian king \add вүҲcancelled his plans to attack andВҰ180432 returned home\add*.
\p
\v 21 \add вүҲEverything else that MenahemВҰ180464 said andВҰ180465 did is writtenВҰ180472 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ180478 of YisraelВҰ180479.
\v 22 ThenВҰ180481 MenahemВҰ180482 \add вүҲdied and was buried\add*, and his son PekahyahВҰ180487 \add вүҲreplaced him as\add* kingВҰ180486.
\s1 Pekahyah reigns over Yisrael
\rem /s1 Pekahiah Reigns over Israel; Pekahiah King of Israel; King Pekahiah of Israel; Pekahiah Rules in Israel
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 23 In the fiftieth year of KingВҰ180496 Azaryah'sВҰ180495 \add reign\add* over YehudahВҰ180497, Menahem'sВҰ180502 son PekahyahВҰ180499 becameВҰ180498 king over YisraelВҰ180505 \add and reigned\add* from ShomronВҰ180506 \add (Samaria)\add* for two yearsВҰ180507.
\v 24 He did what YahwehВҰ180512 \add вүҲhad said was\add* evilВҰ180510вҖ”he didn'tВҰ180513 \add вүҲavoid the kinds of behaviour\add* thatВҰ180520 had been done by Nebat'sВҰ180519 son Yarave'amВҰ180516 who had causedВҰ180521 YisraelВҰ180524 to sinВҰ180521.
\v 25 \add вүҲButВҰ180526\add* Pekah the son of RemalyahВҰ180531, \add @Pekahyah's\add* third officer, \add вүҲplotted to assassinate\add* him, and he \add вүҲattackedВҰ180533\add* him in the palace in ShomronВҰ180534 \add вүҲwithВҰ180534 the assistance of\add* Argov and AryehВҰ180545 and fiftyВҰ180547 Gileadites. \add вүҲSoВҰ180526\add* \add @Pekah\add* killedВҰ180551 \add @King Pekahyah\add* and \add вүҲreplaced him as\add* kingВҰ180552.
\v 26 \add вүҲEverything else that PekahyahВҰ180557 said andВҰ180558 did is writtenВҰ180563 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ180569 of YisraelВҰ180570вҖ”\add вүҲlook at it\add*.
\s1 Pekah's reign over Yisrael
\rem /s1 Pekah Rules in Israel; Pekah Reigns over Israel; Pekah King of Israel; King Pekah of Israel
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 27 In the fifty-second year of KingВҰ180578 Azaryah'sВҰ180577 \add reign\add* over YehudahВҰ180579, Remalyah'sВҰ180584 son PekahВҰ180581 becameВҰ180580 king over YisraelВҰ180587 \add and reigned\add* from ShomronВҰ180588 \add (Samaria)\add* for twentyВҰ180589 years.
\v 28 He did what YahwehВҰ180595 \add вүҲhad said was\add* evilВҰ180593вҖ”he didn'tВҰ180596 \add вүҲavoid the kinds of behaviour\add* thatВҰ180605 had been done by Nebat'sВҰ180604 son Yarave'amВҰ180601 who had causedВҰ180606 YisraelВҰ180609 to sinВҰ180606.
\p
\v 29 \add вүҲDuring the reign of\add* King PekahВҰ180612 over YisraelВҰ180615, Assyria'sВҰ180620 King TiglatВҰ180617-Pileser cameВҰ180616, and he captured \add the cities of\add* Iyyon, Avel-Beyt-Maakah, YanoahВҰ180633, KedeshВҰ180636, and Hatsor, and \add the regionsВҰ180647 of\add* GileadВҰ180642, GalileeВҰ180645, and NaftaliВҰ180648, and he exiled \add @their people\add* to Assyria.
\p
\v 30 ThenВҰ180652 Elah'sВҰ180658 son HosheaВҰ180655 \add вүҲplotted to assassinate\add* Remalyah'sВҰ180664 son PekahВҰ180661, and he attackedВҰ180665 him, killing him and \add вүҲreplacing\add* him as king in the twentiethВҰ180670 yearВҰ180669 of \add King\add* Yotam's \add reignВҰ180667 over Yehudah\add*.
\v 31 \add вүҲEverything else that PekahВҰ180679 said andВҰ180680 did is writtenВҰ180685 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ180691 of YisraelВҰ180692.
\s1 Yotam's reign over Yehudah
\rem /s1 Jotham Rules in Judah; Jotham Reigns over Judah; King Jotham of Judah; Jotham King of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 27:1-9)
\p
\v 32 In the second yearВҰ180695 of Remalyah'sВҰ180700 son Pekah'sВҰ180697 \add reign\add* over YisraelВҰ180702, Azaryah's son Yotam \add вүҲbegan to reign\add* over YehudahВҰ180709.
\v 33 He was twenty-five when he becameВҰ180717 kingВҰ180717, and he \add вүҲreignedВҰ180722\add* from YerushalemВҰ180723 for sixteen years. (His mother'sВҰ180725 nameВҰ180724 was YerushaВҰ180726, the daughterВҰ180727 of TsadokВҰ180729.)
\v 34 He did what YahwehВҰ180734 \add вүҲhad said was correct behaviour\add* like his fatherВҰ180740 Azaryah/Uzziyah had done,
\v 35 \add although\add* the \add вүҲhilltop shrines\add* weren't removedВҰ180746вҖ”the peopleВҰ180748 continued to sacrificeВҰ180749 atВҰ180751 them andВҰ180750 burn incense. Yotam builtВҰ180753 the upperВҰ180760 gateВҰ180756 to Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add*.
\p
\v 36 \add вүҲEverything else thatВҰ180765 Yotam said andВҰ180762 did is writtenВҰ180770 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ180776 of YehudahВҰ180777.
\v 37 In thoseВҰ180780 daysВҰ180779, YahwehВҰ180782 beganВҰ180781 to sendВҰ180783 Aram'sВҰ180787 KingВҰ180786 Retsin andВҰ180788 Remalyah'sВҰ180792 son PekahВҰ180789 against YehudahВҰ180784.
\v 38 ThenВҰ180794 YotamВҰ180795 \add вүҲdied\add* and was buriedВҰ180799 in \add вүҲtheir ancestral tomb\add* in the cityВҰ180803 of his ancestor DavidВҰ180804, and his son AhazВҰ180807 \add вүҲreplaced him as\add* kingВҰ180806.
\c 16
\s1 Ahaz's reign over Yehudah
\rem /s1 King Ahaz of Judah; Ahaz Rules in Judah; Downfall of the northern kingdom; Ahaz Reigns over Judah; Ahaz King of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 28:1-27)
\p
\v 1 In the seventeenthВҰ180813 year of Remaliah'sВҰ180820 son Pekah'sВҰ180817 \add reign over Israel\add*, Yotam's son AhazВҰ180822 \add вүҲbegan to reign over\add* YehudahВҰ180827.
\v 2 AhazВҰ180833 was twentyВҰ180831 when he becameВҰ180834 kingВҰ180834 and he \add вүҲreignedВҰ180839\add* from YerushalemВҰ180840 for sixteen years, \add вүҲbutВҰ180835\add* he didn'tВҰ180841 \add вүҲfollow\add* what his godВҰ180847 YahwehВҰ180846 \add вүҲhad said was correct behaviour\add* like his ancestor DavidВҰ180848 had done.
\v 3 \add Actually\add* he \add вүҲfollowed the behaviour\add* of the kingsВҰ180853 of YisraelВҰ180854, and he even \add вүҲsacrificed\add* his son \add вүҲas a burnt offering\add* like \add вүҲthey do inВҰ180852 the nationsВҰ180862 thatВҰ180863 Yahweh hated and\add* whichВҰ180863 Yahweh had driven out \add вүҲof the land as the IsraelisВҰ180854 had entered\add*.\x + \xo 16:3: \xt Deu 12:31.\x*
\v 4 \add вүҲAlso\add* he sacrificedВҰ180871 on the \add вүҲhilltop shrines\add* and burntВҰ180872 incenseВҰ180872 on them, and on the hillsВҰ180876 and underВҰ180877 everyВҰ180878 large treeВҰ180880.
\p
\v 5 Then Aram'sВҰ180888 King Retsin and Yisrael'sВҰ180895 King PekahВҰ180889 (Remalyah'sВҰ180892 son) cameВҰ180884 uphill to \add вүҲattack\add* YerushalemВҰ180896, and they laid siege against \add King\add* AhazВҰ180901 butВҰ180889 they weren't able to conquerВҰ180904 \add the city\add*.\x + \xo 16:5: \xt Isa 7:1.\x*
\v 6 At that timeВҰ180906, Aram'sВҰ180912 KingВҰ180910 Retsin recaptured Elat City for Aram, then he droveВҰ180917 the YehudansВҰ180920 out of Elat and ArameansВҰ180912 \add вүҲmoved in\add* \add instead\add* and they have livedВҰ180927 thereВҰ180928 to this dayВҰ180930.
\v 7 \add вүҲSo\add* AhazВҰ180935 sentВҰ180934 messengersВҰ180936 to Assyria'sВҰ180943 KingВҰ180941 TiglatВҰ180939-Pileser, вҖңI'm your servantВҰ180945 and your son. Come up and rescueВҰ180949 me from the kings of AramВҰ180953 and YisraelВҰ180956 \add вүҲwho are here attacking\add* me.вҖқ
\v 8 AhazВҰ180961 took the goldВҰ180967 and silverВҰ180964 from Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add* and from the \add вүҲpalace\add* treasuriesВҰ180971, and sent it as a giftВҰ180978 to the Assyrian king.
\v 9 The king of AssyriaВҰ180983 listenedВҰ180980 to him and \add вүҲwent in and attacked\add* DamascusВҰ180989, and he capturedВҰ180990 it and exiled \add @its people\add* to KirВҰ180992, and he executed \add KingВҰ180982\add* Retsin.
\p
\v 10 King AhazВҰ181000 wentВҰ180998 to meet the Assyrian King TiglatВҰ181002-Pileser inВҰ181013 DamascusВҰ181007, and he sawВҰ181008 the altar thatВҰ181012 was \add *there\add*. \add вүҲSoВҰ180998\add* he sentВҰ181014 \add вүҲa drawing and the detailed measurements\add* of the altar to the priestВҰ181020 Uriyyah.
\v 11 \add вүҲSoВҰ181032\add* Uriyyah builtВҰ181032 the altarВҰ181037 accordingВҰ181038 to \add *the plans\add* that King Ahaz had sentВҰ181041 from Damascus \add вүҲandВҰ181032 had it finished before King Ahaz returned\add* from Damascus.
\v 12 \add вүҲWhenВҰ181057\add* the king \add вүҲgot back to YerushalemВҰ181059\add* andВҰ181057 saw the altar, he wentВҰ181057 up onto it
\v 13 and made his burntВҰ181076 offering and his grain offering, and he pouredВҰ181080 out his drinkВҰ181083 offering, and he sprinkled the bloodВҰ181087 of his peace offerings onto the altarВҰ181095.
\v 14 HeВҰ181111 got the bronzeВҰ181099 altar thatВҰ181100 \add вүҲhad been dedicated to\add* YahwehВҰ181102 moved \add вүҲback away from the templeВҰ181106\add* andВҰ181097 placed beside the \add newer, bigger\add* altar.\x + \xo 16:14: \xt Exo 27:1-2; 2Ch 4:1.\x*
\v 15 ThenВҰ181120 KingВҰ181122 AhazВҰ181124 orderedВҰ181120 Uriyyah, вҖң\add вүҲUse\add* the large altar for the morningВҰ181138 burnt offerings and the eveningВҰ181142 grain offerings, and for the king's burnt offerings and grain offerings, and for the people'sВҰ181154 burnt offerings and grain offerings and drinkВҰ181157 offerings. \add вүҲUse\add* it for sprinklingВҰ181168 all the blood of the burnt offerings and of the sacrificesВҰ181166 on. \add вүҲButВҰ181120 I will use\add* the bronzeВҰ181170 altar for seeking \add guidance\add*.вҖқ
\v 16 \add вүҲSoВҰ181176\add* UriyyahВҰ181177 the priestВҰ181178 \add вүҲput everything into effect\add* that KingВҰ181183 AhazВҰ181184 had commandedВҰ181182.
\p
\v 17 ThenВҰ181186 KingВҰ181187 AhazВҰ181188 cut the framesВҰ181191 off the standsВҰ181192 \add outside the temple\add*, and he removedВҰ181193 the basinsВҰ181198 off them. He tookВҰ181202 down вҖҳThe SeaвҖҷ \add вүҲthatВҰ181206 had been sitting on top of bronzeВҰ181205 bullsВҰ181204\add* and put it on the stoneВҰ181212 floor.\x + \xo 16:17: \xt 1Ki 7:23-39; 2Ch 4:2-6.\x*
\v 18 He \add вүҲalso\add* removedВҰ181228 the \add вүҲcanopy that had been builtВҰ181221 atВҰ181222 the temple for use onВҰ181222 the Rest Days\add*, andВҰ181214 \add blocked up\add* the king's outerВҰ181227 entranceВҰ181225 to the \add вүҲtemple so that the Assyrian king couldn't use it\add*.
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲEverything else thatВҰ181238 AhazВҰ181237 said andВҰ181235 did is writtenВҰ181243 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ181249 of YehudahВҰ181250.
\v 20 ThenВҰ181252 AhazВҰ181253 \add вүҲdied\add* and was buriedВҰ181257 in \add вүҲtheir ancestral tomb\add* in the cityВҰ181261 of DavidВҰ181262, and his son Hizkiyah \add (HezekiahВҰ181264)\add* \add вүҲreplaced him as\add* king.\x + \xo 16:20: \xt Isa 14:28.\x*
\c 17
\s1 Hoshea's reign over Yisrael
\rem /s1 Hoshea Reigns over Israel; King Hoshea of Israel; Hoshea Rules in Israel; Hoshea Last King of Israel
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 1 In the twelfth year of KingВҰ181273 Ahaz'sВҰ181272 \add reign\add* over YehudahВҰ181274, Elah'sВҰ181279 son HosheaВҰ181276 becameВҰ181275 king over YisraelВҰ181283 \add and he reigned\add* from ShomronВҰ181280 \add (SamariaВҰ181280)\add* for nine yearsВҰ181285.
\v 2 HeВҰ181294 did what YahwehВҰ181290 \add вүҲhad said was\add* evilВҰ181288, \add вүҲalthough nothing like the IsraeliВҰ181293 kingsВҰ181293 who'd preceded himВҰ181297\add*.
\v 3 Assyria'sВҰ181303 KingВҰ181302 ShalmaneserВҰ181301 \add вүҲattacked\add* \add and defeated\add* him, and HosheaВҰ181307 became his servant and paid tributeВҰ181311 to him.
\v 4 \add вүҲButВҰ181313\add* the Assyrian king \add вүҲdiscovered that Hoshea was planning a revolt and\add* had sent messengersВҰ181321 to the Egyptian KingВҰ181314 So and hadn't \add вүҲkept up the annual tributeВҰ181331 payment\add*. \add вүҲSo\add* the Assyrian king arrestedВҰ181336 \add @Hoshea\add* and \add вүҲimprisonedВҰ181341\add* him.
\s1 The fall of Shomron/Samaria
\rem /s1 The Fall of Samaria; Israel Carried Captive to Assyria
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ181343 the AssyrianВҰ181346 kingВҰ181344 \add вүҲattacked the whole country, including\add* besieging ShomronВҰ181351 \add (SamariaВҰ181351)\add* for threeВҰ181354 yearsВҰ181355.
\v 6 In the ninthВҰ181358 yearВҰ181357 of Hoshea'sВҰ181359 \add reign\add*, the Assyrian kingВҰ181361 capturedВҰ181360 ShomronВҰ181366. He exiled the Israelis to AssyriaВҰ181363 and settledВҰ181372 them in HalahВҰ181374, and in HavorВҰ181375 along the GozanВҰ181377 River, and in the citiesВҰ181378 of the MedesВҰ181379.
\rem /s1 Samaria Falls to Assyria; Israel Exiled Because of Sin
\p
\v 7 That happened because the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ181388\add* had sinned against theirВҰ181390 godВҰ181390 YahwehВҰ181389 who had rescued them from KingВҰ181398 Far-oh in EgyptВҰ181394. They had \add вүЎsinned by\add* worshipping otherВҰ181403 godsВҰ181402
\v 8 andВҰ181414 \add вүҲimitating the customsВҰ181406 of the peopleВҰ181412 groups\add* who YahwehВҰ181410 had driven out of the country ahead of them. \add вүҲThey had also followed their kingsВҰ181414\add* \add inВҰ181406 doing evil things\add*.
\v 9 The \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ181422\add* had done thingsВҰ181423 secretlyВҰ181419 thatВҰ181424 their godВҰ181431 YahwehВҰ181430 \add вүҲhad said weren't rightВҰ181427\add*, andВҰ181419 they'd builtВҰ181432 \add вүҲhilltop shrines everywhere from the largest fortifiedВҰ181443 cities to the smallest townsВҰ181437\add*.
\v 10 They'd \add also\add* erected stone pillarsВҰ181447 \add to honour gods\add* and Asherah polesВҰ181448 on every highВҰ181453 hill and underВҰ181454 every large treeВҰ181457,\x + \xo 17:10: \xt 1Ki 14:23.\x*
\v 11 andВҰ181472 they'd burntВҰ181460 incenseВҰ181460 thereВҰ181462 on all \add вүҲthose hilltops\add* \add just\add* like the \add вүҲpeople groups\add* thatВҰ181467 Yahweh \add вүҲhad driven off the land ahead of them\add*вҖ”doing those evilВҰ181474 thingsВҰ181473 had made Yahweh angry.
\v 12 They'd servedВҰ181480 idolsВҰ181481 even when YahwehВҰ181484 had \add вүҲforbidden them\add* from doing thatВҰ181482.
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲSoВҰ181493\add* YahwehВҰ181494 had warnedВҰ181493 YisraelВҰ181495 and YehudahВҰ181496 by the \add вүҲproclamations\add* of all of his prophets who said, вҖңTurn from your evilВҰ181508 waysВҰ181507 and \add вүҲobey\add* my commandsВҰ181510 and statutesВҰ181511, \add вүҲfollowing\add* all of the \add вүҲinstructionsВҰ181516 thatВҰ181515 I gave\add* your ancestorsВҰ181519 and which I delivered to youВҰ181522 \add вүҲthrough\add* my servantsВҰ181524, the prophets.вҖқ
\v 14 \add вүҲHowever,\add* they hadn't listenedВҰ181528 andВҰ181527 had \add вүҲhardened their attitudes\add* \add just\add* like their ancestorsВҰ181534 who \add вүҲwouldn't put their\add* trustВҰ181537 inВҰ181538 their godВҰ181539 Yahweh.
\v 15 They rejectedВҰ181541 his statutesВҰ181544 and the agreement that he \add вүҲmade\add* withВҰ181557 theirВҰ181552 ancestorsВҰ181552, and \add вүҲthe warningВҰ181554 that he gave\add* them. They \add вүҲchose to worship lifeless objects\add*, and they becameВҰ181562 \add вүҲhollow and empty themselves, just like\add* \add the people of\add* the \add вүҲsurrounding\add* countriesВҰ181564 which YahwehВҰ181569 had commandedВҰ181568 them not to \add вүҲimitate\add*.
\v 16 They \add вүҲdisobeyed the instructions given to them by\add* theirВҰ181582 godВҰ181582 YahwehВҰ181581 \add вүҲby molding twoВҰ181586 metal\add* calvesВҰ181588 for themselves and making an AsherahВҰ181590 pole. ThenВҰ181575 they \add вүҲbowed down and worshippedВҰ181591 the sun, moon, and stars\add*, and they servedВҰ181596 BaalВҰ181599.\x + \xo 17:16: \xt 1Ki 12:28.\x*
\v 17 They \add вүҲsacrificed their sonsВҰ181604 and daughtersВҰ181607, and used fortune-tellers and witchcraftвҖ”making themselves slaves to evilВҰ181614\add* by doingВҰ181613 what YahwehВҰ181616 \add вүҲhad forbidden, and so\add* making himВҰ181617 angry.\x + \xo 17:17: \xt Deu 18:10.\x*
\v 18 \add вүҲSoВҰ181619\add* \add that's why\add* YahwehВҰ181620 had become very angryВҰ181619 atВҰ181622 \add the northern kingdom of\add* YisraelВҰ181622 andВҰ181623 \add вүҲcaused them to be removedВҰ181623 from the land\add*. Only \add the Southern kingdom of\add* YehudahВҰ181630 \add вүҲremained\add*,
\v 19 \add вүҲbut even theyВҰ181647\add* didn'tВҰ181636 \add вүҲobey the commandsВҰ181640\add* of theirВҰ181642 godВҰ181642 YahwehВҰ181641, \add вүҲbut copied much of the bad behaviour of the northern kingdom\add*.
\v 20 \add вүҲSoВҰ181649\add* YahwehВҰ181650 rejectedВҰ181649 all the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ181654\add* andВҰ181649 he \add вүҲcaused them to suffer, including being plunderedВҰ181659 by enemy armies, untilВҰ181660 he banishedВҰ181662 them from his presenceВҰ181663\add*.
\p
\v 21 \add вүҲFirstly he'd torn the northern kingdom out from the leadership of David'sВҰ181671 descendants\add* and they'd made Nebat'sВҰ181678 son Yarave'am kingВҰ181672. Then Yarave'am had driven them away from followingВҰ181685 YahwehВҰ181686, and had \add вүҲinduced them into serious sinВҰ181689\add*.
\v 22 \add вүҲSoВҰ181692\add* the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ181694 had followed Yarave'amВҰ181698 into sin\add* andВҰ181692 thenВҰ181692 didn'tВҰ181701 \add вүҲturn away from it\add*,
\v 23 \add вүҲand finally\add* YahwehВҰ181710 had removedВҰ181709 \add the people of the northern kingdom of\add* YisraelВҰ181713 from \add вүҲhis presence just like he'd warned he would through the messages\add* of his servantsВҰ181721, the prophetsВҰ181722. \add вүҲSoВҰ181724 the people\add* were deported to AssyriaВҰ181727 \add where they remain\add* to this dayВҰ181729.
\s1 The Assyrians settle in the northern kingdom
\rem /s1 Foreigners Settle in Israel; Assyria Resettles Samaria; Samaria Resettled; The Assyrians Settle in Israel
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 24 Then the Assyrian king sent peopleВҰ181746 from BabylonВҰ181737 and from Kutah and from Avva and from HamatВҰ181740 and Sefarvayim, and he settledВҰ181742 them in the cities of \add вүҲthe northern kingdom\add* in placeВҰ181745 of the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ181747\add*. And they possessedВҰ181748 Shomron \add (SamariaВҰ181744)\add* and livedВҰ181752 in its towns.
\v 25 \add вүҲAtВҰ181765 firstВҰ181756 the new inhabitants livingВҰ181757 thereВҰ181758 didn'tВҰ181759 respect\add* YahwehВҰ181763, \add вүҲhowever\add* \add *he\add* sentВҰ181764 lionsВҰ181769 among them andВҰ181755 they \add вүҲstarted\add* killingВҰ181771 them.
\v 26 They told the Assyrian kingВҰ181775, вҖңThe \add вүҲpeople groups\add* thatВҰ181779 you exiledВҰ181780 \add from their own countriesВҰ181778\add* and settled inВҰ181782 the towns around ShomronВҰ181783, don't know the customs of the god of the land. \add вүҲSoВҰ181774\add* he's sent lionsВҰ181796 against them, and look atВҰ181782 themвҖ”killingВҰ181798 them because they don't know the customs of the god of the land.вҖқ
\v 27 вҖң\add вүҲSend\add* one of the priestsВҰ181817 back that was brought from there,вҖқ the Assyrian kingВҰ181810 commandedВҰ181809. вҖңHe can goВҰ181821 back there andВҰ181809 settle there \add again\add*, thenВҰ181809 he can teachВҰ181824 them the customsВҰ181827 of the godВҰ181828 of that place.вҖқ
\v 28 \add вүҲSoВҰ181831\add* they found one of the priestsВҰ181833 who had been exiledВҰ181835 from ShomronВҰ181836 and sent him back \add to Israel\add*. He settled in Beyt-El and taughtВҰ181842 the people how YahwehВҰ181848 \add wanted to be\add* served.
\p
\v 29 \add вүҲButВҰ181850 each people group\add* had made theirВҰ181864 own gods andВҰ181855 put them in the \add вүҲhilltop shrines\add* that the \add вүҲIsraelis\add* had made \add before being exiled\add*. \add вүҲEach people group did that in the area whereВҰ181865 they'd been resettled\add*.
\v 30 \add вүҲThose from\add* BabylonВҰ181871 made \add their god\add* SuccotВҰ181875-BenotВҰ181876, \add вүҲthose from\add* Kutah made NergalВҰ181883, \add вүҲthose from\add* HamatВҰ181885 made \add their god\add* AshimaВҰ181889,
\v 31 and the AvvitesВҰ181891 made Nivhaz and TartakВҰ181896. The SefarvitesВҰ181897 \add вүҲsacrificed\add* their \add own\add* sons inВҰ181902 the fireВҰ181902 to \add *their\add* godsВҰ181905 Adrammelek and Anammelek.
\v 32 \add At the same time,\add* they \add вүҲtried placating\add* YahwehВҰ181914, \add вүҲbutВҰ181910\add* they \add also\add* made their own priestsВҰ181918 to make sacrifices for them in their \add вүҲhilltop shrines\add*.
\v 33 \add вүҲSo\add* they were \add вүҲworshipping\add* YahwehВҰ181928 along with theirВҰ181933 \add own\add* godsВҰ181933вҖ”they'd brought those customsВҰ181936 with them from the countriesВҰ181937 they'd been exiledВҰ181940 from
\v 34 and whichВҰ181962 they \add still\add* followВҰ181958 to this dayВҰ181945.\x + \xo 17:34: \xt Gen 32:28; 35:10.\x*
\p They're not \add actually\add* \add вүҲobeying\add* Yahweh \add вүҲbecause\add* they're not \add вүҲobeying the statutesВҰ181958 or laws, or instructionsВҰ181963 or behaviour\add* thatВҰ181962 Yahweh commandedВҰ181961 the descendantsВҰ181967 of Yakob (who he'd renamed to вҖҳYisraelВҰ181973вҖҷ).
\v 35 YahwehВҰ181976 had \add вүҲmade an agreement with them\add* andВҰ181975 had commandedВҰ181979 them, вҖңYou all must not \add вүҲhonour\add* otherВҰ181984 godsВҰ181983 or \add вүҲbow\add* to them. You all must not serveВҰ181990 them or sacrificeВҰ181992 to them.\x + \xo 17:35: \xt Exo 20:5; Deu 5:9.\x*
\v 36 \add Only\add* \add вүЎserve\add* YahwehВҰ182000 who \add вүҲused his incredible powerВҰ182006 to rescue\add* you all out of EgyptВҰ182005. \add вүҲHonour\add* him, and \add only\add* bow to him and sacrificeВҰ182015 to him.\x + \xo 17:36: \xt Deu 6:13.\x*
\v 37 \add вүҲAlways\add* take care to obey the statutesВҰ182019 and customs, and the law and the instructions thatВҰ182025 he wroteВҰ182026 for you, and you all must not \add вүҲhonour\add* otherВҰ182036 godsВҰ182035.
\v 38 Don't forgetВҰ182044 the agreement thatВҰ182039 I made with you all, andВҰ182045 don'tВҰ182043 \add вүҲhonour\add* otherВҰ182048 godsВҰ182047вҖ”
\v 39 \add only\add* your godВҰ182056 YahwehВҰ182055, and then he himself will rescue you from all your enemiesВҰ182064.вҖқ
\v 40 \add вүҲHowever,\add* they didn'tВҰ182066 listenВҰ182067, \add вүҲpreferring to follow the customsВҰ182071 from theirВҰ182071 formerВҰ182072 places of residence\add*.
\p
\v 41 \add вүҲSoВҰ182076\add* those \add вүҲpeople groups honoured\add* YahwehВҰ182083, butВҰ182076 also served their idolsВҰ182086. \add вүҲThis continued through the generations with their descendants continuing the same behaviour\add*.
\c 18
\s1 Hizkiyah's reign over Yehudah
\rem /s1 Hezekiah King of Judah; Hezekiah's Reign over Judah; Judah under Hezekiah; Hezekiah Rules in Judah; King Hezekiah of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 29:1-2; 31:1)
\p
\v 1 In the third year of Elah'sВҰ182111 son KingВҰ182112 Hoshea'sВҰ182108 \add reign\add* over YisraelВҰ182113, Ahaz'sВҰ182118 son Hizkiyah \add (HezekiahВҰ182115)\add* becameВҰ182114 king of YehudahВҰ182120.
\v 2 He was twenty-five when he becameВҰ182128 kingВҰ182128 and he reignedВҰ182132 from YerushalemВҰ182133 for twenty-nine years. (His motherВҰ182135 was Zekaryah's daughterВҰ182137 AbiВҰ182136.)
\v 3 He did what YahwehВҰ182144 \add вүҲhad said was correct behaviour\add* like his ancestor \add King\add* DavidВҰ182149 had done.
\v 4 He \add вүҲdemolished the hilltop shrines\add* and shattered their pillarsВҰ182161, and he cut down the Asherah \add #poles\add*. He crushed the bronzeВҰ182168 serpent thatВҰ182169 MoshehВҰ182172 had made, because the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ182181\add* had named it вҖҳNehushtanВҰ182187вҖҷ and had been offering incense to it untilВҰ182174 then.\x + \xo 18:4: \xt Num 21:9.\x*
\v 5 \add @Hizkiyah\add* \add fully\add* trustedВҰ182193 inВҰ182199 Yisrael'sВҰ182192 godВҰ182190 Yahweh, and no other \add king\add* was like him among all the kingsВҰ182200 of YehudahВҰ182201 thatВҰ182202 \add вүҲeither preceded or followed\add* him.
\v 6 He \add вүҲrelied completely\add* onВҰ182207 YahwehвҖ”not turning away from \add вүҲfollowingВҰ182211\add* him, andВҰ182206 he \add вүҲobeyed\add* the \add вүҲinstructionsВҰ182216\add* thatВҰ182214 Yahweh had commandedВҰ182213 MoshehВҰ182220.
\v 7 \add вүҲSoВҰ182222\add* YahwehВҰ182223 \add вүҲhelped\add* him and he \add вүҲwas successful inВҰ182225 everything he did\add*. He rebelledВҰ182230 against the Assyrian kingВҰ182231 and \add refused to submit to his demands\add*.
\v 8 He \add вүҲattacked and defeatedВҰ182239\add* the PhilistinesВҰ182242 as far as GazaВҰ182245 and itsВҰ182248 bordersвҖ”\add вүҲboth the smaller towns\add* and the fortifiedВҰ182254 cityВҰ182253.
\p
\v 9 Then inВҰ182258 the fourthВҰ182259 year of King Hizkiyah's reign (it was the seventhВҰ182264 year of Elah'sВҰ182268 son Hoshea'sВҰ182265 \add reign\add* over YisraelВҰ182270), the Assyrian King ShalmaneserВҰ182272 \add вүҲhad attacked\add* ShomronВҰ182278 \add (Samaria)\add* and \add вүҲbesieged\add* it.
\v 10 They \add had finally\add* captured \add @the city\add* \add вүҲafter\add* threeВҰ182284 yearsВҰ182285. That was the sixth year of Hizkiyah's \add reign over Yehudah\add* andВҰ182282 the ninth year of Hoshea'sВҰ182294 \add reign\add* over YisraelВҰ182296.
\v 11 \add вүҲSoВҰ182300\add* that was when the Assyrian kingВҰ182301 had exiled \add the people of\add* \add вүҲthe northern kingdom of YisraelВҰ182306\add* to HalahВҰ182309 and to Havor along the GozanВҰ182312 River, and to the citiesВҰ182313 of the MedesВҰ182314.
\v 12 \add That happened\add* because they didn't \add вүҲobey\add* theirВҰ182324 godВҰ182324 Yahweh, butВҰ182325 \add instead\add* they \add вүҲbroke the agreement withВҰ182322 him\add*вҖ”everything that Yahweh's servantВҰ182335 MoshehВҰ182334 had commandedВҰ182333. They didn't take \add вүҲnotice of it\add* and they didn't \add вүҲobey it\add*.
\s1 Sanheriv invades Yehudah
\rem /s1 Sennacherib Invades Judah; Assyria Invades Judah; The Assyrians Threaten Jerusalem
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 32:1-19; Isa 36:1-22)
\p
\v 13 In the fourteenth yearВҰ182345 of King Hizkiyah's \add reign\add*, Assyrian King SanherivВҰ182349 \add вүҲattacked\add* all the fortifiedВҰ182358 citiesВҰ182356 inВҰ182343 YehudahВҰ182357 and capturedВҰ182359 them.
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ182361\add* KingВҰ182363 Hizkiyah of YehudahВҰ182365 sent \add messengers\add* to the Assyrian king at Lakish, saying, вҖңI \add вүҲapologise for my mistake\add*. \add вүҲStop attacking\add* me \add and\add* \add вүҲI'll give you whatever you demand of us\add*.вҖқ ThenВҰ182361 the Assyrian king \add вүҲdemanded a tribute\add* of \add вүҲten tonnes of goldВҰ182402 and ten tonnes of silverВҰ182399\add*.
