\v 10 вҖңIt's easy for the shadows go forward,вҖқ said Hizkiyah. вҖң\add вүҲSoВҰ183833 make them\add* go backwardsВҰ183844 ten steps.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲSoВҰ183848\add* the prophetВҰ183850 YeshayahВҰ183849 calledВҰ183848 to YahwehВҰ183853, andВҰ183848 he made the shadow go back onВҰ183858 the steps \add made by King\add* AhazВҰ183862вҖ”the shadow went tenВҰ183864 steps backwardВҰ183863.
\s1 Hizkiyah shows off his treasures
\rem /s1 Envoys from Babylon; Envoys From Babylon; Messengers from Babylonia
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (Isa. 39:1-8)
\p
\v 12 At that timeВҰ183868, Baladan'sВҰ183875 son \add former\add* KingВҰ183876 Berodak-Baladan of BabylonВҰ183878 heardВҰ183885 that Hizkiyah was sickВҰ183887 and sentВҰ183870 him lettersВҰ183879 and a giftВҰ183880.
\v 13 \add WhenВҰ183890 the messengers arrived,\add* Hizkiyah listenedВҰ183890 to them, thenВҰ183890 he showedВҰ183893 them his entireВҰ183896 treasure house: the goldВҰ183906 and silverВҰ183903, the spicesВҰ183909 and the best oil, the house of his armour, and everything thatВҰ183927 was in his treasuries. He \add вүҲdidn'tВҰ183923 keep anythingВҰ183926 in his palaceВҰ183932 or in his kingdom secret from\add* them.
\v 14 \add вүҲLater\add* the prophetВҰ183939 Yeshayah came to KingВҰ183942 HizkiyahВҰ183943 and he \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖңWhere were those menВҰ183949 from and what did they say?вҖқ
\p вҖңThey came from a distantВҰ183957 landвҖ”from BabylonВҰ183959,вҖқ \add *he\add* \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 15 вҖңWhat did they seeВҰ183963 in your house?вҖқ \add @Yeshayah\add* \add вүҲasked\add*.
\p вҖңThey sawВҰ183972 everything that's in my house,вҖқ \add *he\add* \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖңThere wasn't anythingВҰ183976 in my treasuriesВҰ183981 that I didn'tВҰ183973 show them.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 ThenВҰ183983 YeshayahВҰ183984 told Hizkiyah, вҖңListen to Yahweh's messageВҰ183989:
\v 17 He saysВҰ184014 that daysВҰ183994 are comingВҰ183995 when everything inВҰ184001 your house, and \add вүЎeverything\add* that your ancestorsВҰ184004 storedВҰ184003 \add carefully\add* away untilВҰ184005 this dayВҰ184007 will be \add вүҲcarriedВҰ183996\add* to BabylonВҰ184009. \add вүҲNothing will be left behind\add*.\x + \xo 20:17: \xt 2Ki 24:13; 2Ch 36:10.\x*
\v 18 \add What's more,\add* some of yourВҰ184017 own biological descendants will be taken andВҰ184026 they'll \add вүҲbe castrated to become servants\add* of the Babylonian kingВҰ184029.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 вҖң\add вүҲWhat you said from YahwehВҰ184040 is fine\add*,вҖқ Hizkiyah \add вүҲreplied\add* to YeshayahВҰ184036. вҖң\add вүҲAt least I might have peaceВҰ184047 andВҰ184032 stability\add* inВҰ184050 my time.вҖқ
\s1 Hizkiyah's death
\rem /s1 Death of Hezekiah; The End of Hezekiah's Reign
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 32:32-33)
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲEverything else thatВҰ184058 Hizkiyah said and did, including his making the pool and tunnel to bring waterВҰ184069 into the cityВҰ184070, is writtenВҰ184074 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ184080 of YehudahВҰ184081.
\v 21 \add вүҲIn due course,\add* Hizkiyah \add вүҲdied\add* andВҰ184088 his son Menashsheh \add вүҲreplaced him as\add* kingВҰ184088.
\c 21
\s1 Menashsheh's reign over Yehudah
\rem /s1 Manasseh Rules in Judah; Manasseh Reigns over Judah; King Manasseh of Judah; Manasseh King of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 33:1-20)
\p
\v 1 Menashsheh was twelve when he becameВҰ184100 kingВҰ184100, and he reignedВҰ184104 \add over Yehudah\add* from YerushalemВҰ184105 for fifty-five years. (His motherВҰ184107 was Heftsivah.)
\v 2 He did \add вүҲwhat Yahweh had said was evil\add* like the \add вүҲevil behaviour\add* of the peopleВҰ184122 groups thatВҰ184118 Yahweh had driven out \add of the region\add* ahead of the IsraelisВҰ184123.\x + \xo 21:2: \xt Jer 15:4.\x*
\v 3 \add In fact\add* he \add вүҲwent backwards\add* from his fatherВҰ184133 and rebuilt the \add вүҲhilltop shrines\add* thatВҰ184130 Hizkiyah had destroyedВҰ184131, and he made altarsВҰ184135 for BaalВҰ184136, and he made an AsherahВҰ184138 pole, just like Yisrael'sВҰ184143 KingВҰ184142 AhabВҰ184141 had, and he \add вүҲworshippedВҰ184144 the constellations\add* and \add вүҲfollowed astrology\add*.
\v 4 \add вүҲAlso\add* heВҰ184157 builtВҰ184152 altarsВҰ184153 in Yahweh's residence, where Yahweh had saidВҰ184157, вҖңI will \add вүҲestablish\add* my \add вүҲreputation\add* in YerushalemВҰ184159.вҖқ\x + \xo 21:4: \xt 2Sam 7:13.\x*
\v 5 \add @Menashsheh\add* builtВҰ184165 altarsВҰ184166 to all the \add вүҲconstellations\add* inВҰ184171 the twoВҰ184171 courtsВҰ184172 of the \add вүҲtemple\add*.
\v 6 He \add вүҲeven sacrificed his own son as a burnt offering\add*. He practisedВҰ184182 divinationВҰ184183 and read omens, and consulted mediums and fortune-tellers. He did \add вүҲso much that Yahweh had said was\add* evilВҰ184189, provokingВҰ184192 Yahweh to get angry.
\v 7 He placed the Asherah idol thatВҰ184199 he'd made in the \add вүҲtemple\add* about which YahwehВҰ184204 had said to DavidВҰ184207 and to his son Shelomoh \add (SolomonВҰ184210)\add*, вҖңI will \add вүҲestablish\add* my \add вүҲreputation forever\add* in this house and in YerushalemВҰ184214 \add in Yehudah\add*, which I've chosenВҰ184216 out of all the tribesВҰ184218 of YisraelВҰ184219.\x + \xo 21:7-8: \xt 1Ki 9:3-5; 2Ch 7:12-18.\x*
\v 8 If only the IsraelisВҰ184230 will take care to obey everything that I've commanded them, andВҰ184226 all the instructionsВҰ184245 that my servantВҰ184253 MoshehВҰ184254 gave them, thenВҰ184226 I won'tВҰ184226 continue to \add вүҲcause them to leave the area\add* that I gave to theirВҰ184236 ancestorsВҰ184236.вҖқ
\v 9 \add вүҲButВҰ184256\add* they didn'tВҰ184256 listenВҰ184257 andВҰ184256 Menashsheh led them astrayВҰ184258 to do more evil things \add even\add* than the people groups thatВҰ184267 YahwehВҰ184269 had destroyedВҰ184268 as the people had entered the region.
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ184274\add* YahwehВҰ184275 announced via his servantsВҰ184278 the prophetsВҰ184279,
\v 11 вҖңBecauseВҰ184282 Yehudah'sВҰ184288 KingВҰ184286 Menashsheh has done \add вүҲsuch terribly evilВҰ184291 things\add*, \add вүҲworse even than the AmoritesВҰ184296 who were there beforeВҰ184298 himВҰ184298\add*, andВҰ184299 \add вүЎbecause\add* he's even made Yehudah sinВҰ184299 withВҰ184305 his idolsВҰ184305,
\v 12 then Yisrael'sВҰ184314 godВҰ184313 YahwehВҰ184312 saysВҰ184311: Listen, \add вүҲI'll bringВҰ184316 such terrible disaster to Yehudah including YerushalemВҰ184320 thatВҰ184322 people won't even be able to handle hearing the news aboutВҰ184316 itВҰ184325\add*.
\v 13 I'll \add вүҲuse the same tape measureВҰ184336 for Yerushalem that I used for\add* ShomronВҰ184337 \add (SamariaВҰ184337)\add*, and \add вүЎI'll use the same\add* plumb line \add вүЎthat I used for\add* Ahab'sВҰ184342 \add вүҲextended family\add*. I'll wipe Yerushalem away, just like someoneВҰ184349 \add вүҲdries\add* a bowlвҖ”they wipe \add it dry\add* and thenВҰ184331 turn it \add вүҲupside down\add*.
\v 14 I'll abandonВҰ184359 the \add вүҲsmall remainder of my people here\add*, and I'll \add вүҲhandВҰ184364 them over to\add* their enemiesвҖ”they'll become the spoilВҰ184368 and plunder of all their enemies,
\v 15 because they've done what \add вүҲI told them was evil\add*, and they've been making me angry from the time that theirВҰ184388 ancestorsВҰ184388 \add вүҲwere brought out of\add* EgyptВҰ184389 \add вүҲright up\add* to this day.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 MenashshehВҰ184398 even poured out so much innocentВҰ184396 bloodВҰ184395 that he filledВҰ184404 YerushalemВҰ184407 \add with it\add* \add вүҲfrom one side to the other\add*, \add вүҲandВҰ184394 that was on top of his other\add* sin of leading YehudahВҰ184416 into doingВҰ184417 what YahwehВҰ184420 \add вүҲhad said was\add* evil.
\p
\v 17 \add вүҲEverything else that Menashsheh said andВҰ184422 did, including the sins that he committed, is writtenВҰ184435 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ184441 of YehudahВҰ184442.
\v 18 ThenВҰ184444 Menashsheh \add вүҲdied\add* and was buriedВҰ184449 inВҰ184450 the palace garden (made by Uzza), and his son AmonВҰ184457 \add вүҲreplaced him as\add* kingВҰ184456.
\s1 Amon's reign over Yehudah
\rem /s1 King Amon of Judah; Amon Reigns over Judah; Amon Rules in Judah; Amon King of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\rem /r (2 Chronicles 33.21-25)
\p
\v 19 AmonВҰ184467 was twenty-two when he becameВҰ184468 kingВҰ184468, and he reignedВҰ184471 from YerushalemВҰ184472 for two yearsВҰ184470. (His motherВҰ184474 was Haruts's daughterВҰ184476 MeshullemetВҰ184475 from Yotvah.)
\v 20 He did what YahwehВҰ184486 \add вүҲhad said was\add* evilВҰ184484, just like his fatherВҰ184490 Menashsheh had done.
\v 21 \add In fact,\add* he followed everything thatВҰ184496 his father had done, \add including\add* serving the \add вүҲsame idolsВҰ184503\add* andВҰ184492 bowing to them.
\v 22 HeВҰ184519 abandonedВҰ184510 YahwehВҰ184513, the godВҰ184514 of his ancestorsВҰ184515, andВҰ184516 didn'tВҰ184516 \add вүҲobey his instructions\add*.
\p
\v 23 \add вүҲButВҰ184521\add* Amon'sВҰ184524 servantsВҰ184522 \add вүҲplotted to assassinate\add* him, andВҰ184526 they killedВҰ184526 him inВҰ184530 the \add вүҲpalace\add*.
\v 24 \add вүҲHowever,\add* the people \add вүҲexecuted everyoneВҰ184533 who'd been involved in the conspiracyВҰ184539\add* against KingВҰ184542 AmonВҰ184543, andВҰ184532 they \add вүҲinstalled\add* his son Yoshiyyah as king in his placeВҰ184552.
\p
\v 25 \add вүҲEverything else thatВҰ184557 AmonВҰ184556 said andВҰ184554 did is writtenВҰ184562 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ184568 of YehudahВҰ184569.
\v 26 He was buriedВҰ184571 in his tombВҰ184574 in the gardenВҰ184575 \add made by\add* UzzahВҰ184577, andВҰ184578 his son Yoshiyyah \add вүҲreplaced himВҰ184581 as\add* kingВҰ184578.
\c 22
\s1 Yoshiyyah's reign over Yehudah
\rem /s1 Josiah Reigns over Judah; Josiah's reform; The Book of the Law Found; King Josiah of Judah; Josiah Rules in Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 34:1-2)
\p
\v 1 Yoshiyyah was eightВҰ184586 when he becameВҰ184589 kingВҰ184589, and he reignedВҰ184593 from YerushalemВҰ184594 for thirty-one years. (His motherВҰ184596 was Adayah'sВҰ184600 daughterВҰ184598 YedidahВҰ184597 from Batskat.)\x + \xo 22:1: \xt Jer 3:6.\x*
\v 2 He did what Yahweh \add вүҲhad said was correct behaviour\add*, \add вүҲfollowing all the customs\add* of his ancestor \add King\add* DavidВҰ184611, andВҰ184603 \add вүҲobeying Yahweh's instructions\add*.
\s1 A scroll is discovered in the temple
\rem /s1 The Book of the Law Is Discovered; Hilkiah Finds the Book of the Law
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 34:8-28)
\p
\v 3 In the eighth month of the eighteenth yearВҰ184623 of KingВҰ184624 Yoshiyyah's reign, \add *he\add* sentВҰ184626 the scribe ShafanВҰ184630 (the son of Atsalyah the son of MeshullamВҰ184636) to the \add вүҲtemple\add*, saying
\v 4 вҖңGo to the highВҰ184647 priestВҰ184646 Hilkiyyah andВҰ184648 \add вүҲget him to\add* countВҰ184648 the silver thatВҰ184655 was broughtВҰ184652 into Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add*, whichВҰ184655 the \add вүҲdoor-keepers\add* collected from the peopleВҰ184660.
\v 5 ThenВҰ184662 \add вүҲhave it givenВҰ184662 to the supervisors of the temple repairsВҰ184680, andВҰ184662 thenВҰ184662 they can pay the workers who are repairing\add* the damageВҰ184681вҖ”
\v 6 the craftsmen, buildersВҰ184685, and masonsВҰ184686, as well as buying wood and quarried stonesВҰ184689 \add вүҲfor the repairsВҰ184691\add*.вҖқ
\v 7 They won'tВҰ184697 need \add вүҲto submit detailed accountsВҰ184699\add* for itВҰ184699 because \add вүҲthey're trustworthy people\add*.\x + \xo 22:7: \xt 2Ki 12:15.\x*
\rem /s1 Hilkiah Discovers God's Law
\p
\v 8 \add During the repairs,\add* the hight priestВҰ184713 Hilkiyyah told the scribe Shafan, вҖңI foundВҰ184721 a scroll in the temple \add вүҲwith Yahweh's instructions written on it\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ184711\add* Hilkiyyah gave the scroll to Shafan \add вүҲto\add* read.
\v 9 ThenВҰ184734 ShafanВҰ184735 the scribe wentВҰ184734 to the king \add вүҲwithВҰ184752 this report\add*, вҖңYourВҰ184761 servantsВҰ184747 \add вүҲhanded over the moneyВҰ184750 that had been collected inВҰ184752 the temple\add*, andВҰ184734 they gave it to the \add вүҲsupervisors of the workers doing the repairs\add*.вҖқ
\v 10 Then he \add вүҲadded\add*, вҖңAnd the priestВҰ184772 Hilkiyyah gaveВҰ184769 me a scrollВҰ184768.вҖқ Then he read it \add out loud\add* to KingВҰ184766 \add Yoshiyyah\add*.
\p
\v 11 WhenВҰ184778 the kingВҰ184780 heardВҰ184779 the contents of the scrollВҰ184784, he tore his clothesВҰ184789
\v 12 and commandedВҰ184791 the priestВҰ184796 Hilkiyyah, Shafan'sВҰ184802 son AhikamВҰ184799, Mikayah's son Akbor, the scribe Shafan, and the king's servantВҰ184815 AsayahВҰ184814,
\v 13 вҖңGo \add and\add* \add вүҲinquire from\add* Yahweh on my behalf and on behalf of the peopleВҰ184828 and all YehudahВҰ184832, concerningВҰ184864 the words of this scroll thatВҰ184844 was foundВҰ184837. Because \add it sounds like\add* Yahweh \add вүҲmust be very angry atВҰ184848 us because our predecessors\add* didn't listenВҰ184853 to \add вүҲwhat's writtenВҰ184863 on\add* this scroll \add вүҲand didn't do what was expected of\add* us.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ184866\add* HilkiyyahВҰ184867 the priest and AhikamВҰ184869, AkborВҰ184870, ShafanВҰ184871, and AsayahВҰ184872 wentВҰ184866 to the prophetessВҰ184876 HuldahВҰ184875 (the wifeВҰ184877 of ShallumВҰ184879, the son of TikvahВҰ184882, the son of HarhasВҰ184885, the \add вүҲone in charge of looking after the priests' uniforms\add* who lived in \add вүҲthe newer part of\add* YerushalemВҰ184890), and theyВҰ184892 spokeВҰ184892 to herВҰ184893.
\v 15 She told them that Yisrael'sВҰ184902 godВҰ184901 YahwehВҰ184900 had saidВҰ184895, вҖңTell the manВҰ184904 who sentВҰ184907 youВҰ184908 all to me
\v 16 that YahwehВҰ184913 saysВҰ184912 this: I'm going to bringВҰ184915 disaster to this placeВҰ184919 andВҰ184921 itsВҰ184923 inhabitantsВҰ184923, \add вүҲjust like it's written\add* in the scroll that the kingВҰ184931 read
\v 17 because they abandonedВҰ184937 me. They \add вүҲoffered sacrifices\add* to otherВҰ184940 godsВҰ184939 inВҰ184943 order to make me angry \add вүҲatВҰ184943 everything they do, so now my angerВҰ184947 will be directed\add* against this placeВҰ184948 and it's \add вүҲnot stoppable\add*.
\v 18 ButВҰ184953 to the kingВҰ184955 of YehudahВҰ184956 who sentВҰ184957 you all to seek Yahweh, tell him that Yisrael'sВҰ184971 godВҰ184970 Yahweh saysВҰ184968: The wordsВҰ184972 that you heardВҰ184974 \add from the scroll\add*,
\v 19 because \add вүҲyou're open to learn\add* and \add вүЎbecause\add* you humbledВҰ184980 yourself \add вүҲin front\add* of Yahweh when you heard \add вүҲmyВҰ185002 promise that\add* this placeВҰ184989 and its inhabitantsВҰ184993 would become a horror and a curseВҰ184996, and \add вүЎbecause\add* you've torn your clothesВҰ185000 and wept \add вүҲin front of me\add*, then Yahweh \add вүҲsaid that he's taken notice of you\add*.
\v 20 \add вүҲBecause of that, he'll allow you to die and be buried peacefullyВҰ185020, and you yourself won'tВҰ185021 witness the destruction that will come\add* to this placeВҰ185033.вҖқ
\p \add вүҲSo they relayed those messagesВҰ185039\add* back to KingВҰ185038 \add Yoshiyyah\add*.
\c 23
\s1 Yoshiyyah removes false gods
\rem /s1 Josiah Renews the Covenant; Josiah's Religious Reforms; Josiah's Reformation; Josiah Does Away with Pagan Worship
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 34:3-7,29-33)
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ185041 KingВҰ185042 \add Yoshiyyah\add* \add вүҲsummoned\add* all the eldersВҰ185047 of YerushalemВҰ185049 andВҰ185041 \add across\add* YehudahВҰ185048,
\v 2 and \add *he\add* went to the \add вүҲtemple\add*, and all the inhabitantsВҰ185062 of YerushalemВҰ185063 and from all across YehudahВҰ185059 went with him, along with the priestsВҰ185065 and prophetsВҰ185066, and all the peopleВҰ185069 from the \add вүҲmost to the least important\add*. ThenВҰ185051 he read \add вүҲto them every word\add* onВҰ185075 the scrollВҰ185081 of the agreement that had been foundВҰ185083 inВҰ185075 Yahweh's residence.
\v 3 ThenВҰ185087 the kingВҰ185088 stoodВҰ185087 by the pillarВҰ185091 and he \add вүҲmade a commitment in frontВҰ185097\add* of Yahweh to \add вүҲfollow\add* Yahweh and to \add вүҲobey\add* his commandsВҰ185103 and testimonies and statutesВҰ185109 with all \add вүҲsincerity\add*, and with \add вүҲevery desire to respect\add* the wordsВҰ185119 of that agreement that had been writtenВҰ185122 onВҰ185131 that scroll. All the peopleВҰ185130 \add вүҲwere also included in that commitment\add*.
\p
\v 4 ThenВҰ185133 the kingВҰ185134 commandedВҰ185133 the highВҰ185139 priest Hilkiyyah and the \add вүҲother\add* priestsВҰ185142, and the \add вүҲtempleВҰ185149\add* guards to bringВҰ185148 out all the utensils that were made for BaalВҰ185156 and Asherah and for all the \add вүҲconstellations\add*, and he burntВҰ185161 them outsideВҰ185162 YerushalemВҰ185163 inВҰ185164 the KidronВҰ185165 countryside, and carriedВҰ185166 theirВҰ185169 ashesВҰ185169 to Beyt-El.
\v 5 He \add вүҲgot rid of\add* the pagan priestsВҰ185177 that the kingsВҰ185180 of Yehudah had appointedВҰ185179 to burnВҰ185182 incense inВҰ185183 the \add вүҲhilltop shrines\add* aroundВҰ185186 YerushalemВҰ185187 and across \add the rest of\add* Yehudah, and the ones who burntВҰ185190 incense to BaalВҰ185191, and to the sunВҰ185192 and moonВҰ185193 and to the planets and constellationsВҰ185194.
\v 6 He got the Asherah pole out from Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add* and burnt it inВҰ185213 the KidronВҰ185210 valley outsideВҰ185205 YerushalemВҰ185206, thenВҰ185199 he \add вүҲpounded the ashes\add* to dust and threwВҰ185217 it over \add вүҲpeople'sВҰ185225\add* graves.
\v 7 He \add вүҲdemolished\add* the \add вүҲcubicles\add* of the maleВҰ185231 temple prostitutesВҰ185231 thatВҰ185232 were inside Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add* where the womenВҰ185236 were weavingВҰ185237 Asherah \add вүҲcoverings\add*.\f + \fr 23:7 \ft It's not exactly clear what these woven objects were, or how or where they were used.\f*
\v 8 He broughtВҰ185242 all the priests \add to Yerushalem\add* from the citiesВҰ185248 of YehudahВҰ185249, andВҰ185242 he desecrated the \add вүҲhilltop shrines\add* where the priests had burnt incense, from GebaВҰ185259 to BeerВҰ185262-Sheva. He \add вүҲdemolished\add* the \add вүҲhilltop shrines\add* thatВҰ185269 Yehoshua (a city official) had built near the city gate (onВҰ185283 the left of the gate as you entered the city).
\v 9 HoweverВҰ185294 those priests \add вүҲfrom those hilltop shrines\add* weren't allowed to \add вүҲserve atВҰ185295\add* the altarВҰ185293 inВҰ185295 YerushalemВҰ185295, \add вүҲbut they were allowed to\add* eat unleavenedВҰ185300 breadВҰ185300 \add вүҲlike the other priests\add*.
\p
\v 10 \add @Yoshiyyah\add* \add also\add* desecrated the TofetВҰ185307, whichВҰ185308 was inВҰ185323 the BenВҰ185313-HinnomВҰ185309 valley, so thatВҰ185308 \add вүҲthe people couldn't sacrifice their children\add* to MolekВҰ185324.
\v 11 The horsesВҰ185329 that the kingsВҰ185332 of YehudahВҰ185333 \add вүҲhad offered\add* to the sun, he \add вүҲprevented\add* from approaching the hall of the \add вүҲofficial\add* NatanВҰ185344-Melek that was inВҰ185347 the courtyards of Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add*, andВҰ185326 he \add вүҲset fireВҰ185353 to\add* the chariotsВҰ185350 of the sun.
\v 12 ThenВҰ185355 the kingВҰ185383 tore down the altars that were onВҰ185377 the roofВҰ185361 in Ahaz'sВҰ185363 upperВҰ185362 chamber that the kingsВҰ185368 of YehudahВҰ185369 made, and the altars that MenashshehВҰ185376 made in the twoВҰ185377 courtsВҰ185378 of Yahweh'sВҰ185381 \add вүҲtemple\add* and he threwВҰ185386 \add вүҲthe rubble\add* into the KidronВҰ185393 valley.
\v 13 The king desecrated the \add вүҲhilltop shrines thatВҰ185398 faced\add* YerushalemВҰ185403вҖ”they were \add вүҲsouthВҰ185405\add* of the Mt. of DestructionвҖҷ \add (the Mt. of Olives)\add*. KingВҰ185412 Shelomoh had builtВҰ185410 \add вүЎshrines\add* for Ashtarot (the disgusting \add god\add* of the SidoniansВҰ185418) and for Kemosh (the disgusting \add god\add* of MoabВҰ185421) and for Molek (the disgusting \add god\add* of the \add вүҲAmmonites\add*).
\v 14 He \add also\add* smashed the \add sacredВҰ185433\add* pillarsВҰ185433 andВҰ185430 cut down the Asherah polesВҰ185437, thenВҰ185430 he \add desecrated\add* those places \add вүҲby filling them\add* with humanВҰ185443 bonesВҰ185442.
\p
\v 15 He also \add вүҲdemolished\add* the altar that was in Beyt-ElвҖ”the \add вүҲhilltop shrine\add* that Nebat'sВҰ185459 son Yarave'am had made when he'd causedВҰ185461 YisraelВҰ185464 to sinВҰ185461. He \add вүҲdemolished\add* both that altar and the \add вүҲhilltop shrine\add*, thenВҰ185445 he burnt the \add вүҲshrine\add*. He crushed \add вүҲeverything\add* to dust, and he burnt the AsherahВҰ185481 pole.
\v 16 \add вүҲAs\add* Yoshiyyah turnedВҰ185483 \add around\add*, he \add вүҲnoticedВҰ185485 some\add* graves thatВҰ185489 were thereВҰ185491 on the hillside, \add вүҲso\add* he \add вүҲhad some bonesВҰ185497 removed\add* from the graves, andВҰ185483 he burnt them on the altarВҰ185504 \add вүҲto\add* desecrate it. \add вүҲThis fulfilled what YahwehВҰ185507 had said through\add* the manВҰ185510 of God who'd proclaimed theseВҰ185517 thingsВҰ185516.\x + \xo 23:16 \xt 1Ki 13:2-3.\x*
\v 17 \add @Yoshiyyah\add* \add turned again and\add* \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖң\add вүҲWhose tomb is that\add*?вҖқ
\p вҖңIt's the prophet's tomb,вҖқ the peopleВҰ185528 of Beyt-El replied, вҖң\add The one\add* who came from YehudahВҰ185537 and predicted that \add вүҲwhat you just did to that\add* altarВҰ185546 would happen.вҖқ
\v 18 вҖң\add вүҲDon't disturbВҰ185557 it thenВҰ185551\add*,вҖқ \add @the king\add* \add вүҲordered\add*. вҖңDon't let anyoneВҰ185554 \add вүҲremove\add* his bones.вҖқ
\p \add вүҲSoВҰ185551\add* they \add вүҲleft\add* his bones \add вүҲaloneВҰ185552\add*, \add along with\add* the bones of the \add other\add* prophetВҰ185563 who came from ShomronВҰ185567.
\v 19 \add вүҲSoВҰ185569\add* \add King\add* Yoshiyyah removedВҰ185585 all the \add вүҲhilltop shrines\add* thatВҰ185576 the IsraeliВҰ185583 kingsВҰ185582 had made in the cities of ShomronВҰ185579, provokingВҰ185584 \add Yahweh's\add* angerВҰ185584. \add @The king\add* \add вүҲdestroyed them just\add* like he'd done \add вүҲto the ones\add* in Beyt-El.
\v 20 He \add вүҲexecuted\add* all the priestsВҰ185603 \add вүҲfrom those hilltop shrines\add* on the altarsВҰ185610 thereВҰ185607, andВҰ185598 thenВҰ185598 he burnt humanВҰ185615 bonesВҰ185614 on them \add to desecrate them\add*. ThenВҰ185598 he returnedВҰ185617 to YerushalemВҰ185618.
\s1 The celebration of вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ
\rem /s1 Josiah Celebrates Passover; The Passover Celebrated; Josiah Celebrates the Passover
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 35:1-19)
\p
\v 21 ThenВҰ185620 the kingВҰ185621 commandedВҰ185620 all the peopleВҰ185626, вҖң\add вүҲCelebrate\add* вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ for yourВҰ185631 godВҰ185631 YahwehВҰ185630 according to what's writtenВҰ185632 on this scrollВҰ185634 with the agreement.вҖқ
\v 22 Since the days of the leaders who judgedВҰ185644 Yisrael, or in all the days of the kings of Yisrael and YehudahВҰ185655, \add вүҲa вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ had never been celebrated like that one\add*
\v 23 in the eighteenthВҰ185660 yearВҰ185662 of KingВҰ185663 Yoshiyyah's \add reign\add*. That вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ \add celebration\add* in YerushalemВҰ185669 was \add to honour\add* YahwehВҰ185668.
\s1 King Yoshiyyah's other activities
\s4 Southern kingdom
\rem /s1 Other Changes Made by Josiah
\p
\v 24 \add King\add* Yoshiyyah also removedВҰ185693 the ritual pits and the soothsayers, and the images and idolsВҰ185683, and all the abhorrences that were seenВҰ185689 in YerushalemВҰ185692 and in the YehudahВҰ185691 \add вүҲregionВҰ185690\add*, \add вүҲin his diligence to obey everything\add* that was writtenВҰ185701 onВҰ185692 the scroll that the priestВҰ185708 Hilkiyyah foundВҰ185706 in \add вүҲthe temple\add*.
\v 25 No other king had been like \add @Yoshiyyah\add* who'd \add вүҲled the people back to obeying\add* YahwehВҰ185723вҖ”\add вүҲfollowing Mosheh'sВҰ185735 written instructions\add* with all his heartВҰ185726 and all his spirit and all his \add вүҲenergy\add*. \add What's more,\add* there's never been \add a king\add* like him since thenВҰ185712 either.
\p
\v 26 However, \add вүҲYahweh's anger against YehudahВҰ185755 hadn't cooled down after everything thatВҰ185751 King Menashsheh had done\x + \xo 23:26 \xt 2Ki 21:1-18.\x* to\add* make him angry,
\v 27 andВҰ185764 YahwehВҰ185765 said, вҖңI will also removeВҰ185770 YehudahВҰ185769 \add вүҲout of my sightВҰ185772\add*, just like I removedВҰ185774 YisraelВҰ185777. I'll \add вүҲalso\add* rejectВҰ185778 this cityВҰ185781 of YerushalemВҰ185788 that I choseВҰ185785, as well as the houseВҰ185791 where I'd said that my nameВҰ185795 would be \add вүҲestablished\add*.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Josiah Dies in Battle; The End of Josiah's Reign
\rem /r (2 Chronicles 35.20вҖ”36.1)
\p
\v 28 \add вүҲEverything else that Yoshiyyah said andВҰ185801 did is writtenВҰ185808 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ185814 of YehudahВҰ185815.
\v 29 \add вүҲWhile he was still king\add*, the Egyptian king Far-oh Nekoh \add вүҲattacked\add* the Assyrian king near the EuphratesВҰ185832 River. KingВҰ185821 Yoshiyyah went to meet him, butВҰ185833 \add @Nekoh\add* killedВҰ185837 him atВҰ185838 MegiddoВҰ185838 when he saw him.
\v 30 HisВҰ185859 servantsВҰ185843 \add вүҲbroughtВҰ185846 his body back\add* to YerushalemВҰ185847 from MegiddoВҰ185845, and they buriedВҰ185848 him in his own tombВҰ185849. ThenВҰ185842 the peopleВҰ185851 got \add *his\add* son YehoahazВҰ185856, and they anointedВҰ185860 him and made him kingВҰ185862 in placeВҰ185864 of his fatherВҰ185865.
\s1 Yehoahaz's reign over Yehudah
\rem /s1 Reign and Captivity of Jehoahaz; Jehoahaz Rules in Judah; King Joahaz of Judah; Jehoahaz King of Judah; Downfall of the Southern kingdom
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 36:2-4)
\p
\v 31 YehoahazВҰ185873 was twenty-three when he becameВҰ185874 kingВҰ185874, and he \add reignedВҰ185877\add* from YerushalemВҰ185878 for \add only\add* three monthsВҰ185876. (His motherВҰ185880 was Yirmeyah's daughterВҰ185882 HamutalВҰ185881 from Livnah.)
\v 32 He did what YahwehВҰ185890 \add вүҲhad said was evilВҰ185888\add* like \add many of\add* his ancestorsВҰ185895 had done.
\v 33 Far-oh Nekoh took him from YerushalemВҰ185906 and imprisoned him atВҰ185900 Rivlah inВҰ185900 the HamatВҰ185902 \add вүҲregionВҰ185901\add*, and he \add вүҲforced the residents of Yehudah to pay him\add* thirty kilograms of goldВҰ185918 and three tonnes of silverВҰ185916.
\v 34 Then Nekoh appointed \add @Yoshiyyah's\add* son Elyakim as the new kingВҰ185920 \add вүҲbutВҰ185920\add* changedВҰ185932 his nameВҰ185935 to Yehoyakim. Then he tookВҰ185940 YehoahazВҰ185939 to EgyptВҰ185942 \add вүҲwhere he eventually diedВҰ185943\add*.
\rem /s1 Jehoiakim Rules in Judah; King Jehoiakim of Judah
\rem /r (2 Chronicles 36.5-8)
\v 35 \add вүҲSoВҰ185946\add* Yehoyakim paid the gold and silver to Far-oh \add вүҲby assessingВҰ185965 the wealth of the peopleВҰ185975 and thenВҰ185946\add* forcibly collecting the gold and silver \add вүҲfrom them\add* to \add вүҲsend\add* to Far-oh Nekoh.
\s1 Yehoyakim's reign over Yehudah
\rem /s1 Jehoiakim King of Judah; Jehoiakim Reigns over Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 36:5-8)
\p
\v 36 Yehoyakim was twenty-five when he becameВҰ185988 kingВҰ185988, and he \add reignedВҰ185992\add* from YerushalemВҰ185993 for eleven years. (His motherВҰ185995 was Pedayah'sВҰ186000 daughterВҰ185998 ZebudahВҰ185996 from RumahВҰ186003.)
\v 37 He did what YahwehВҰ186008 \add вүҲhad said was evilВҰ186006\add* like \add many of\add* his ancestorsВҰ186013 had done.
\c 24
\rem /s1 Judah Overrun by Enemies
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲDuring his reign\add*, the Babylonian KingВҰ186018 Nevukadnetstsar \add вүҲattacked\add*, and Yehoyakim \add вүҲruled under him\add* for threeВҰ186025 yearsВҰ186026 \add вүҲbefore\add* rebellingВҰ186028 against him.
\v 2 ThenВҰ186032 Yahweh sent troops of Chaldeans, troops from AramВҰ186043, troops from MoabВҰ186047, andВҰ186032 \add вүҲAmmonite\add* troops against YehudahВҰ186054 \add atВҰ186054 different times\add* to destroyВҰ186055 them, \add вүҲjust as Yahweh had said through\add* his servantsВҰ186061 the prophetsВҰ186062.
\v 3 \add вүҲThose things troubled YehudahВҰ186071 atВҰ186071 Yahweh's command\add* to removeВҰ186072 them \add вүҲout of his sight\add* because of all of \add King\add* Menashsheh's sinsВҰ186075
\v 4 andВҰ186081 \add вүҲbecause he'd killed innocent people\add*вҖ”YahwehВҰ186096 wouldn't forgiveВҰ186097 him because he'd filledВҰ186087 YerushalemВҰ186090 with innocent blood.
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲEverything else that Yehoyakim said andВҰ186102 did is writtenВҰ186109 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ186115 of YehudahВҰ186116.
\v 6 ThenВҰ186118 Yehoyakim \add вүҲdied\add* andВҰ186123 his son Yehoyakin \add вүҲreplaced him as\add* kingВҰ186123.
\p
\v 7 The Egyptian king didn'tВҰ186128 continue \add вүҲhis attacks on other countries\add*, because the Babylonian king \add вүҲcaptured land all the way\add* from the Egyptian riverВҰ186145 as far as the EuphratesВҰ186147 RiverвҖ”everything that had \add вүҲbeen controlled by\add* EgyptВҰ186133.
\s1 Yehoyakin's reign over Yehudah
\rem /s1 Reign and Captivity of Jehoiachin; Jehoiachin Rules in Judah; Jehoiachin King of Judah; King Jehoiachin of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 36:9-10)
\p
\v 8 Yehoyakin was eighteenВҰ186157 when he becameВҰ186161 kingВҰ186161, \add вүҲbutВҰ186162\add* he reignedВҰ186164 from YerushalemВҰ186165 for \add only\add* threeВҰ186162 monthsВҰ186163.
\v 9 He did what YahwehВҰ186177 \add вүҲhad said was\add* evilВҰ186175 just like his fatherВҰ186182 had done.
\p
\v 10 At that timeВҰ186184, the Babylonian kingВҰ186190 Nevukadnetstsar \add вүҲsent his army to besiege\add* YerushalemВҰ186193,
\v 11 andВҰ186206 Nevukadnetstsar \add вүҲhimself travelled there to observe the operation\add*.
\v 12 Yehudah'sВҰ186214 KingВҰ186212 Yehoyakin went out \add to surrender\add* to the Babylonian king, along with his motherВҰ186220, his servantsВҰ186221, his captains, andВҰ186210 his \add вүҲofficialsВҰ186223. SoВҰ186210\add* the Babylonian king took him \add captive\add* in the eighthВҰ186229 year of his \add вүҲreignВҰ186230\add*.
\rem /s1 Capture of Jerusalem
\v 13 ThenВҰ186232 all the valuables were brought out of Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add* andВҰ186232 the \add вүҲpalaceВҰ186257\add*. All the goldВҰ186250 \add вүҲfurnishings\add* thatВҰ186251 had been made for the \add вүҲtemple\add* by KingВҰ186243 Shelomoh were cut into piecesВҰ186244.
\v 14 ThenВҰ186263 all the army leaders and officials, and all the craftsmenВҰ186286 and blacksmiths from YerushalemВҰ186268 (some ten thousandВҰ186282 people) were taken into exileВҰ186283, leaving only the poorer people behind.
\p
\v 15 KingВҰ186304 Yehoyakin was exiledВҰ186317 from YerushalemВҰ186318 to BabylonВҰ186300, along with his motherВҰ186303 andВҰ186296 wivesВҰ186307, his officialsВҰ186311,
\v 16 sevenВҰ186326 thousand top soldiers, and a thousand skilled craftsmenВҰ186328 and blacksmithsвҖ”\add вүҲleaving no one behind to fight or make weapons\add*.
\p
\v 17 ThenВҰ186342 the Babylonian king \add вүҲappointed\add* Yehoyakin's uncleВҰ186349 MattanyahВҰ186348 as king in his placeВҰ186350 andВҰ186342 he changedВҰ186351 his name to Tsedkiyyah \add (ZedekiahВҰ186355)\add*.
\s1 Tsedkiyyah/Zedekiah's reign over Yehudah
\rem /s1 King Zedekiah of Judah; Zedekiah Rules in Judah; Zedekiah Reigns over Judah; Zedekiah King of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 36:11-12; Jer. 52:1-3a)
\p
\v 18 Tsedkiyyah \add (ZedekiahВҰ186363)\add* was twenty-one when he becameВҰ186364 kingВҰ186364 and he reignedВҰ186368 from YerushalemВҰ186369 for eleven years. (His motherВҰ186371 was Yirmeyah's daughterВҰ186374 HamutalВҰ186372 from Livnah.)
\v 19 He did what YahwehВҰ186382 \add вүҲhad said was\add* evilВҰ186380, just like Yehoyakin had done.
\v 20 Because YahwehВҰ186394 \add вүҲwas still very angry, he had the people of YerushalemВҰ186396 and all YehudahВҰ186397 driven away out of his sight\add*.
\rem /s1 The Fall of Jerusalem; The Fall and Captivity of Judah
\p Then Tsedkiyyah rebelledВҰ186404 against the Babylonian kingВҰ186406.
\c 25
\s1 Yerushalem's defeat
\rem /s1 The Fall of Jerusalem
\s4 Southern kingdom
\rem /r (2 Chronicles 36.13-21; Jeremiah 52.3b-11)
\p
\v 1 In the ninthВҰ186412 yearВҰ186411 of Tsedkiyyah's reignВҰ186413, onВҰ186411 the tenth day of the tenth month, the Babylonian KingВҰ186420 Nevukadnetstsar brought all his army to YerushalemВҰ186429. \add вүҲThey made their camp outside the city, and then builtВҰ186432 attack structures\add* all aroundВҰ186435 it
\v 2 andВҰ186437 \add вүҲbesieged the cityВҰ186438 for two years\add*.
\v 3 The peopleВҰ186456 \add вүҲdidn'tВҰ186452 have enough to eat\add* and the famineВҰ186450 became severeВҰ186449.
\v 4 ThenВҰ186459 the \add вүҲBabyloniansВҰ186477 began breaking into the city, butВҰ186459 the local fighters sneaked out\add* at nightВҰ186466 through a gate betweenВҰ186470 two wallsВҰ186471 near the king's gardenВҰ186475 andВҰ186459 \add вүҲescaped\add* \add down\add* to the desertВҰ186484 plainВҰ186484.
\v 5 \add вүҲHowever,\add* the \add вүҲBabylonian soldiers\add* chased afterВҰ186490 the kingВҰ186491 and theyВҰ186499 overtookВҰ186492 himВҰ186500 onВҰ186494 the YerichoВҰ186495 plainsВҰ186494, and his army scatteredВҰ186499.
\v 6 KingВҰ186505 \add Tsedkiyyah\add* \add вүҲwas capturedВҰ186502\add* andВҰ186502 taken to the Babylonian king at Rivlah, where \add вүҲhe was sentenced\add*вҖ”
\v 7 \add *He\add* \add вүҲwas forced to watch as\add* his sons were slaughteredВҰ186521, thenВҰ186517 \add вүҲhis eyes were gouged out\add* andВҰ186517 he was taken to BabylonВҰ186531 restrained withВҰ186529 two bronzeВҰ186529 chains.
\s1 The demolition of the temple
\rem /s1 The Temple Destroyed; The Destruction of the Temple
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (Jer. 52:12-33)
\p
\v 8 On the seventhВҰ186536 day of the fifthВҰ186535 month of Babylonian KingВҰ186544 Nevukadnetstsar's nineteenth year as king, his servantВҰ186554 Nevuzaradan, who was his chiefВҰ186551 bodyguardВҰ186553, wentВҰ186549 to YerushalemВҰ186558.
\v 9 He \add вүҲset fireВҰ186582\add* to Yahweh's temple and the palace, and all of Yerushalem'sВҰ186574 housesВҰ186573, \add вүҲso no important building remained\add*.
\v 10 ThenВҰ186584 the army \add вүҲunder the command of\add* \add @Nevuzaradan\add* \add вүҲtore down the wallsВҰ186586 surrounding\add* YerushalemВҰ186587.
\v 11 \add *He\add* exiledВҰ186616 all the rest of the peopleВҰ186601 from the cityВҰ186603, \add вүҲall the surrendered soldiers\add*, andВҰ186599 the rest of the populationВҰ186615,
\v 12 \add вүҲbutВҰ186622\add* \add *he\add* let some of the poorestВҰ186622 people \add вүҲremain on the land to look after the vineyards\add* andВҰ186622 as farmers.
\p
\v 13 The Babylonians smashed the bronze pillarsВҰ186633 and the bases and the bronze вҖҳseaВҰ186644вҖҷ from the \add вүҲtemple\add*, and took all the bronze to BabylonВҰ186656.
\v 14 They also tookВҰ186679 the pots and shovelsВҰ186663, the snuffersВҰ186666 and spoons, and all the bronzeВҰ186674 utensils \add вүҲused inВҰ186678 the temple activities\add*.
\v 15 \add #They\add* took the fire-pans and the gold and silver bowls.
\v 16 \add The bronzeВҰ186715 from\add* the twoВҰ186701 pillarsВҰ186699, the вҖҳseaВҰ186702вҖҷ, andВҰ186704 the bases thatВҰ186705 had been made for the \add вүҲtemple\add* by Shelomoh \add (SolomonВҰ186708)\add* was \add вүҲtoo heavy to be weighedВҰ186714\add*.
\v 17 \add вүҲEach pillar was over eightВҰ186721 metresВҰ186735 high, plus a bronze capital on top that was over a metre high. They were decorated with latticework with bronze pomegranatesВҰ186738 all aroundВҰ186742\add*.
\s1 The people of Yehudah get exiled to Babylon
\rem /s1 The People of Judah Are Taken to Babylonia
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (Jer. 52:24-27)
\p
\v 18 \add @Nevuzaradan\add* \add вүҲexiled\add* \add to Babylon\add* the high priest SerayahВҰ186758, the secondВҰ186765 priest Tsefanyah, andВҰ186752 the threeВҰ186768 \add temple\add* entrance guards.
\v 19 From the city, he took one officialВҰ186781 who was a \add вүҲmilitary\add* inspector, five \add вүҲof the king's advisors\add*, andВҰ186772 the army commander'sВҰ186798 secretaryВҰ186797 \add вүҲinВҰ186795 charge of recruitment\add*, plus sixtyВҰ186805 \add вүҲother important\add* men.
\v 20 Nevuzaradan tookВҰ186812 them all to the Babylonian kingВҰ186822 at Rivlah
\v 21 inВҰ186831 \add вүҲthe HamatВҰ186833 regionВҰ186832\add*, \add вүҲbutВҰ186826\add* the kingВҰ186828 \add вүҲhad them all executed\add* there.
\s1 The governor there to Yehudah Gidaliyas www
\rem /s1 Gedaliah Made Governor of Judah; Gedaliah, Governor of Judah; Gedaliah Governs in Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (Jer. 40:7-9; 41:1-3)
\p \add вүҲSoВҰ186826\add* \add the large majority\add* of the people of YehudahВҰ186835 were exiledВҰ186834 \add вүҲout of theirВҰ186828 country\add*.
\v 22 From those who the Babylonian KingВҰ186846 Nevukadnetstsar allowed to remainВҰ186840, he appointedВҰ186848 GedalyahВҰ186852 (son of Shafan'sВҰ186858 son AhikamВҰ186855) over them.
\v 23 \add вүҲWhen\add* all the army captains and their men heardВҰ186861 that the Babylonian kingВҰ186871 had appointedВҰ186870 GedalyahВҰ186876, they came to GedalyahВҰ186876 at Mitspah. \add This was\add* Netanyah's son YishmaelВҰ186882, Kareah'sВҰ186889 son YohananВҰ186886, Tanhumet'sВҰ186893 son SerayahВҰ186890 the Netofatite, and the Maakatite's son YaazanyahВҰ186895, \add вүҲalong with\add* their men.
\v 24 GedaliahВҰ186904 \add вүҲmade an agreement with\add* them and theirВҰ186905 menВҰ186905, \add вүҲtelling\add* them, вҖңDon't be afraidВҰ186910 of the \add вүҲBabylonian officialsВҰ186911\add*. Stay in the land and serveВҰ186915 the Babylonian kingВҰ186918, and he'll be good to youВҰ186921.вҖқ
\v 25 \add вүҲButВҰ186924\add* inВҰ186926 the seventhВҰ186927 monthВҰ186926, YishmaelВҰ186929 (the son of Netanyah, the son of Elishama \add вүҲwho was a descendant of King David\add*) brought tenВҰ186938 menВҰ186939 with him and attacked GedalyahВҰ186944, and \add вүҲkilled him\add*, along with the Yehudans and the Chaldeans who were with him atВҰ186926 Mitspah.
\v 26 \add вүҲAfter that\add*, all the peopleВҰ186961, \add вүҲwith or without any official status\add*, along with the army commanders \add вүҲfled\add* to EgyptВҰ186969 because they were afraidВҰ186971 \add вүҲof what the Babylonians might do to them\add*.
\s1 Yehoyakin gets released from prison
\rem /s1 Jehoiachin Released; Jehoiachin Released from Prison; Hope for Israel's Royal Line; Jehoiachin Is Released from Prison
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (Jer. 52:31-34)
\p
\v 27 Thirty-seven years after Yehudah'sВҰ186984 KingВҰ186982 Yehoyakin had been exiledВҰ186980 \add to Babylon\add*, Evil-MerodakВҰ186993 \add вүҲhad just become the new\add* king of Babylon \add вүҲand he released\add* Yehoyakin from prison onВҰ186977 the 27th of the twelfth month.
\v 28 He \add вүҲspokeВҰ187008 kindly\add* to \add @Yehoyakin\add* andВҰ187011 \add вүҲhonoured himВҰ187014 more than the other kingsВҰ187017 who'd been taken to\add* BabylonВҰ187020.
\v 29 He \add вүҲwas allowed to changeВҰ187022 out of his prisonВҰ187025 clothesВҰ187024, andВҰ187026 was permitted to eatВҰ187026 at the king's table for the rest\add* of his lifeВҰ187033,
\v 30 \add вүҲas well as being givenВҰ187038 a daily monetary allowance\add*.
